title: hamburger beans
directions: Brown ground beef; add other ingredients and stir.
Cook slowly for 30 to 40 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: ham chowder
directions: Mix all ingredients together and simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: mocha mousse
directions: Combine milk and coffee crystals.
Let set 5 minutes.
Stir in pudding mix and whip.
Let set 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer to blend flavors. Serve topped with a bit of sour cream and pass the chips!

title: mexican tacos
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and green peppers.
Add soups and chili peppers.
Cook on low heat 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: white bean and chicken chili
directions: Measure 1 cup beans; place in medium saucepan.
Mash slightly with fork.
Add remaining beans, chicken, jalapeno, broth and pepper; bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream and cilantro.
(Top each serving with guacamole.)

title: taco soup
directions: Dissolve package of taco seasoning with water and add to soup. Simmer slowly.
Very good, low calorie.

title: baked beans for large crowd
directions: Cut bacon in small pieces.
Fry bacon and onions.
Mix all ingredients.
Add a touch of various seasonings (salt, pepper, oregano, thyme, celery salt, garlic powder, horseradish and paprika).
Cook at 300° until heated throughout.
Serves approximately 25 people.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Put sliced mushrooms in greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Melt oleo and add to stuffing mix.
Sprinkle on top of mushrooms. Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Mix flour and cream together and add to bouillon.
Stir together.
Pour over top of stuffing.
Bake 350 degrees for 20 - 25 minutes.

title: creamy bean tacos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread taco shells on baking sheet and bake for 5 minutes or until shells turn golden brown.
Remove from oven and cool.
In small mixing bowl, stir together salsa and bean dip.
Divide evenly between shells and coat insides of shells with mixture.
Stir together sour cream and taco seasoning in small bowl.
Spread evenly in shells over bean mixture.
Divide remaining ingredients in order given, the same way in the shells. Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake according to instructions on package.
Let cool, then poke holes in top of cake with handle of wooden spoon. Dribble sweetened condensed milk over cake.
Then dribble caramel sauce over cake.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Cover entire cake with Cool Whip, then sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in saucepan. Cook until mixture comes to a boil. Boil rapidly for 2 minutes, then remove from heat. Add in order the remaining ingredients and stir each thoroughly.
Spoon onto waxed paper until firm.
Makes approximately 2 dozen.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix together and form into rolls.
Wrap in foil.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Layer potatoes, onion and soup.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350° or until potatoes are done.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil using medium heat.
Stir constantly for about 30 minutes.
Cool and frost cake layers.

title: quick caramel coffee ring
directions: Melt margarine.
Grease bottom and sides of a tube pan with 2 tablespoons of melted margarine.
Sprinkle a few nuts in bottom of pan.
Add brown sugar, nuts and water to margarine.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Cut biscuits in half and roll into balls.
Place balls in bottom of tube pan. Drizzle half of the caramel sauce over dough.
Repeat layers. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked onions
directions: Cut onions in halves.
Peel outer skin off.
Place onions, cut side up, in a large covered baking dish.
Mix water, butter, honey and Worcestershire sauce together and spoon over onions. Top with remaining ingredients and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Baste occasionally with sauce. Serves 6.

title: great-grandma gracie's german potato salad
directions: Dice potatoes.
Add celery, hard-boiled eggs and onion.
Beat 2 eggs.
Add sugar, dry mustard, vinegar, water, salt and pepper. Pour this mixture into hot bacon and fat and stir until it thickens (about 10 minutes).
Pour onto potato mixture and toss lightly.

title: brandied peach shortcake
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 2 cups syrup.
Place peaches in glass bowl or jar.
Heat syrup and 1/2 cup brandy to boil.
Pour over peaches.
Cover and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Beat whipping cream, powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon brandy in chilled bowl until stiff.
Serve cake with peaches and whipping cream.
Serves 12.

title: christiana campbell's tavern rum cream pie
directions: Prepare Crumb Crust.
Soften the gelatin in 1/2 cup of cold water.
Place over low heat and bring almost to a boil, stirring to dissolve.
Beat the egg yolks and sugar until very light.
Stir the gelatin into the egg mixture; cool.
Gradually add the rum, beating constantly.
Whip the cream until it stands in soft peaks and fold it into the gelatin mixture.

title: spicy steak fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread oil on a jelly-roll pan.
Place potatoes wedges on pan.
Sprinkle with seasoning; toss gently to coat.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until tender.
Sprinkle with salt.
Yields 4 servings of
wedges.

title: zesty chicken oregano(greek)
directions: Place chicken in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients except lemon slices; pour over chicken.
Cook uncovered in a 375° oven, spooning mixture over chicken occasionally, 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; cook about 30 minutes longer.
Garnish with lemon slices.

title: fruit and pudding dessert
directions: Add dry pudding mix to fruit and mix well.
Add enough fruit juice to make some pudding form around your fruit.
You can use any fruit combination.
I like large chunk mixed fruit, mandarin oranges and pineapple chunks.
Refrigerate.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Grate vegetables coarsely, except onion, which is finely grated.
Squeeze out the natural juices, saving 2 tablespoons. Soften gelatin in the reserved juice.
Melt in a double boiler until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Add to grated vegetables. Add mayonnaise; mix well.
Add seasonings to taste.
Refrigerate overnight before using.
Makes 3 dozen party sandwiches.

title: children's delight(candles)
directions: Place pineapple slice on each salad plate.
Put a rounded tablespoon whipped cream in the center and stand a half of banana in the pineapple candle holder to hold the "candle" upright.
Top with a dab of whipped cream and a maraschino cherry (the flame). Place the quarter pineapple slice in position to be the handle to the candle holder.

title: chicken salad balls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Chill several hours. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: carrot salad
directions: Grate carrots.
Mix all ingredients in medium size bowl. Chill.
Serve on fresh salad greens.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix the pudding with the milk and blend in cool whip.
Place a layer of graham crackers evenly in a 13x9-inch pan.
Pour on half of the pudding mix.
Top with another layer of graham crackers. Pour on remaining pudding.
Top with a final layer of crackers.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put the cornflakes into a plastic bag and crush them with a rolling pin.
Then dump them into a pie tin.

title: pepper rice casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
and
put in baking dish.
Cook in 350° oven about 45 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir a few times while cooking.

title: western foods punch
directions: Mix together in blender; add Sprite and serve.

title: holiday punch
directions: Spoon sherbet into punch bowl. Pour chilled pineapple juice over sherbet. Pour chilled diet Sprite (will foam). Stir.

title: turtle cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed on box. Pour half of the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt margarine, milk and caramels until smooth.
Pour over baked layer. Sprinkle nuts and chips over mixture on the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Cool and cover with chocolate frosting.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut meat with the grain in 1 inch wide strips. Brown quickly in hot oil. Season and push aside.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until batter is smooth.
Drop by teaspoon on baking pan that has been lightly sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt together well.
Beat egg yolks, then add to mixture.
Beat egg whites for topping.

title: red beans and rice with sausage
directions: Fry sausage and all the other ingredients.
Cover and cook for 45 minutes, until rice is tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: grandma's cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix milk, salt, sugar and flour.
Pour into pan in which margarine "about the size of an egg" (1 tablespoon) has been melted.
Empty quart of fruit on top of batter.
Bake for 1 hour or until batter forms crust.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Blend well together.
Use lemon juice to keep fruits like apples and bananas from turning brown.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix the salad dressing, sugar, mustard and sour cream.
Mix with the first five ingredients.
Serve with a sprig of parsley and wedges of red apples.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Generously grease and lightly flour a 10-inch tube pan.
In a large mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, water and eggs.
Blend and beat as directed on package.
Pour about half of batter into prepared pan.
In small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese, milk and powdered sugar until smooth.
Spoon over batter in pan, not touching sides of pan.
Spoon one cup cherries over cream mixture. Spread with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until toothpick tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Serve with remaining cherries.
Store leftover cake in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix mayonnaise, soups, lemon
juice and salt and pepper together.
Put a layer of
broccoli,
a layer of chicken, half of sauce, then fix another
layer.
Pour rest of sauce and put bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: basic dough recipe
directions: Soften yeast in warm water (110°).
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt; cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 1/2 cups of flour; beat well.
Beat in yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough, beating well.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise until double (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Turn out on lightly floured surface and shape as desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly, but well.
Add dry ingredients and mix together.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: herb chicken
directions: Melt margarine in microwave. Add mayonnaise and mustard; blend. Dip chicken in mixture; coat generously. Next coat chicken with stuffing mix. Place chicken in large baking dish. Bake, covered, for 1 1/2 hours at 300°. Remove foil and bake for 20 to 25 more minutes or until chicken is crispy.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine and mix well all ingredients and make into patties. Fry in cooking oil on medium heat until brown.
May be served with saltine crackers.

title: pralines
directions: Mix milk, sugar and soda in heavy saucepan.
Cook until forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat; beat until starts to harden, then add vanilla, butter and pecans.
Drop by spoon onto wax paper.

title: green split pea soup
directions: Boil until peas are puree consistency.

title: date cookies(sugar-free)
directions: Boil raisins, chopped dates and water 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add margarine, eggs, liquid sugar sweetener and vanilla.
Mix together cinnamon, flour and soda, then add.
Mix well together.
Chill several hours.
Drop from teaspoonfuls onto greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 48 cookies.

title: laurine's refrigerator oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt and soda 3 times.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Gradually add flour, oatmeal, nuts and raisins.
Make 2 rolls.
Roll in wax paper and put in refrigerator for at least 6 hours.
Cut into thin slices and bake at 375°.

title: irish tacos
directions: Brown together the beef and onion.
Drain.
Add the tomato sauce, salt, chili powder, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.

title: cheese ring
directions: Combine all ingredients, except preserves and crackers.
Mix well.
Put cheese mixture into ring or mold, sprayed with Pam. Chill overnight.
Unmold, by dipping into hot water, onto serving plate.
Put preserves in center of ring or on top of mold.
Serve with crackers.

title: seafood elegance(serves 12 plus)
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in pan.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into shells.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: creamy vegetable dip
directions: Blend Campbell's soup and recipe mix and sour cream.
Cover; refrigerate 2 hours.
Serve with vegetables or chips.
Makes 2 cups and may be doubled.

title: lemon chicken wings
directions: Grate 1 1/2 teaspoons lemon peel and squeeze 2 tablespoons juice. Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Let stand 15 minutes. Save marinade. Bake wings at 350° until done, 40 to 50 minutes. Brush wings with marinade several times during baking.

title: strufoli(italian finger dessert)
directions: Day before or up to 2 weeks before serving, in large bowl, whisk eggs, 1/2 cup oil and salt.
Gradually stir in 2 cups flour and baking powder; mix well.
With hands, knead in remaining flour.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface and cut into 20 equal portions.
With hands, roll into pencil-shaped sticks.
With floured knife, cut sticks into 1/4-inch pieces.

title: meatballs and rice in consomme
directions: Mix ground beef, salt and pepper; shape into 12 balls.
Brown slowly on all sides in skillet, using a small amount of fat, if necessary.
Add green pepper, celery and onion.
Cook for 5 minutes longer.
Add rice, consomme and water.
Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer gently, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Soak oats in boiling water for 20 minutes.
Combine sugar to oats.
Add butter and cream this together.
Mix eggs into mixture. Add last 5 ingredients.
Finally, stir in oats.
Bake in a loaf pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Mix sugar,
vinegar, salad oil and salt.
Pour over the vegetables.
Refrigerate
in closed container at least 4 hours before serving; overnight is best.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut onion and pepper in long strips.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Cover; chill overnight.
Keeps 2 weeks.

title: egg nog
directions: Break eggs into mixing bowl.
Add sugar and salt; mix on high or whip setting for 2 minutes or until lemon in color.
Add milk and vanilla; mix until well blended.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: pineapple pie *
directions: Sift sugar and flour together.
Add to crushed pineapple, 1 beaten egg yolk, milk and butter.
Thoroughly mix and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Put in very hot oven until crust is brown, then reduce heat and cook until set.
Take from oven and let cool. Cover with meringue and brown.
Cover with coconut before browning for added flavor.

title: invisible ink
directions: You will need a knife, small jar lid, toothpick, writing paper and a light bulb.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook fryer in salted water, until tender.
Cool to remove bones and skin.
Cut meat into bite size pieces.
Mix flour with part of the broth until smooth.
Add to the rest of the broth (about 3 cups).
Add chicken.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened and smooth.
Pour into casserole or pan and cover with biscuits.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until biscuits are brown.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute chopped bell pepper and onion in butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook until tender.

title: easy cheez-it chicken
directions: Wash chicken strips and pat dry.
Dip in milk.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Melt butter.
Layer chicken in a single layer in pyrex dish.
Pour butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until chicken is thoroughly cooked.

title: easy bake forest torte
directions: Sprinkle marshmallows in greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Prepare cake mix according to package directions and pour over marshmallows. Spoon pie filling over batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with Cool Whip. Store in refrigerator.

title: blackberry cream cheese pie
directions: Bake pie crust at 450° for 9 to 11 minutes (cool completely).

title: orange ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.

title: quick monkey bread
directions: Sprinkle pecans evenly in the bottom of a well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Set aside.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Roll each piece in sugar mixture and layer in pan. Combine brown sugar and butter.
Pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Turn on cake plate.

title: cherry tort
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple and into juice, add sugar and tapioca.
Cook; cool and add fruit.
Mix like pie crust the remaining ingredients.
Put half of this mixture on bottom of pan, then the filling and remaining mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 20.
(Recipe easily cut in half.)

title: mints
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Using a mint mold, make roses, leaves, etc.
Roll small ball in granulated sugar before putting into mold.
Freeze ahead; store in refrigerator.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Brown beef.
Grind bologna and cheese.
Mix together the browned meat, bologna and cheese.
Add remaining ingredients. Scoop mixture on each bun half.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: pickled corn
directions: Cook corn about half done.
Either cut off cob or leave on cob.
Add 1 teaspoon salt to a quart.
Fill with water.
Place a small piece of hot pepper on top of corn.
Seal.
Be sure to pickle when signs are in the knees and on light of moon.

title: sausage sauce piquant
directions: Combine flour and oil in a heavy skillet and brown, stirring constantly.
Add diced sausage, onion and bell pepper; cook until wilted.
Add tomatoes, 1/4 cup water, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: egg in a nest
directions: Spread butter on both sides of the bread.
Cut 1 1/2 to 2-inch hole in center of bread.
Place bread and cut out center in heated skillet.
Drop egg in center of bread.
When browned, flip over and cook until desired doneness.

title: greek broiled whole flounder
directions: Score whole cleaned flounder as you would a ham.
Mix with wire whisk all remaining ingredients.
Pour over scored flounder and rub into flounder well.
Shake on crushed oregano.
Broil for about 20 minutes or until meat flakes with fork.
Do not turn. Garnish with lemon slices and parsley.

title: low-fat - low sugar banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk well.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip and stir. Pour into bowl.
Slice bananas and push into pudding with knife point.
Break crackers into pieces and push into pudding and around edges.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.

title: grape ice
directions: Combine water and sugar in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring until grape juice melts.
Pour mixture into freezer trays or sheet cake pan.
Freeze until firm.
Stir several times during freezing process.

title: cindy's broccoli casserole
directions: Cut and steam broccoli for 5 minutes.
Uncover and let cool until cool enough to handle.
Cut up into small pieces.
Set aside in a large mixing bowl.
Broccoli should be crisp, but tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix cheese and cracker crumbs together and spread 1/2 of crumb mixture in bottom of greased casserole.
Cook broccoli; drain and reserve liquid.
Spread broccoli evenly over crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Mix mushroom soup with 1/2 cup liquid drained from broccoli.
Pour over broccoli and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, salt, white syrup and water to 275°.
Add butter and vanilla.
Boil to 290°.
Add Spanish peanuts.
Boil to 300°. Remove from heat and add soda.
Pour in buttered cookie sheet. Let cool and break in pieces.

title: frankfurter mix-up
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 3-quart casserole.
Cover. Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soak dry onion in 1 tablespoon of pineapple juice.
Mix all ingredients together with hands (except nuts).
Shape into a ball and roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, gelatine, salt and spices. Combine egg yolks and milk.
Stir into brown sugar mixture.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pumpkin.
Chill until mixture mounds slightly when spooned. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gradually add granulated sugar, beating to stiff peaks.
Fold pumpkin mixture thoroughly into egg whites.
Turn into crust.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: chocolate coconut pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and salt.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in vanilla and milk.
Add melted magarine, then add coconut and nuts. Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells and bake for 40 minutes at 350°. This pie freezes well.

title: tuna bake
directions: Blend cheese into soup with electric mixer. Add tuna, onion, mustard, milk and macaroni.
Pour into 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix crumbs and oleo. Sprinkle on top.

title: coconut date nut quick bread(diabetic)
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl; set aside.
Beat eggs in bowl.
Blend in apple juice, margarine, milk and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Stir in dates, nuts and coconut.
Spread in greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes in pan.
Remove.
Cool. Slice and serve with cream cheese. Makes 12 servings.

title: mom's country fried steak
directions: Wash and drain steak.
Cut in serving pieces.
Pat dry with paper towel.
Mix flour, salt and pepper in flat dish.
Put oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Coat each piece of steak with flour mixture.
Place in hot oil.
Brown on each side. Remove from skillet to small roaster or baking dish.
Add 2 cups water to skillet.
Let it come to boil.
Pour over steak.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes, depending on thickness of steak.
This is real tender.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer 20 minutes. Best when served hot.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and cut into bite size pieces (leaves and stems, too).
Chop onion.
Slice mushrooms thin.
Cut hard eggs into wedges.
Put all of this into a large salad bowl and sprinkle with garlic powder and seasoned salt.
In a small bowl, mix mustard and mayonnaise.
Pour over vegetables and eggs; toss gently with rubber spatula or wooden spoon until all pieces are coated. Scatter olives and nuts over top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, if possible, before serving.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: In a covered saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling water for 20 to 25 minutes or until just tender; drain well.
In a very large bowl, combine celery, green pepper, onion, mayonnaise or salad dressing, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes and eggs.
Toss lightly to mix.
Cover and chill for 6 to 24 hours. Makes 12 side dish servings.

title: hot mulled cranberry punch
directions: Bring first five ingredients to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Add juices and heat, but do not boil.
May add brandy.

title: carolina pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour and milk alternately, then flavoring. Pour in tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: picante sauce
directions: Chop all vegetables; add other ingredients.
Simmer for 2 1/2 hours.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Mix bread crumbs, salt, pepper, paprika and curry powder.
Dip chicken breast in yogurt, then roll in crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: cathedral cookies
directions: Melt margarine and chips in double boiler.
Cool for a while before adding remaining ingredients.
Put on wax paper; roll up and cool.

title: pumpkin date nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans or 1 large tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: steak rolls
directions: Slice steak into 4 x 2-inch strips and pound flat.
Saute chopped onion and parsley in butter.
Stir in bread crumbs and mushroom pieces (reserve liquid).
Add egg slowly while stirring rapidly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Place spoonful of stuffing mixture on each meat strip.
Roll up and fasten with toothpick.
Season with salt and pepper.
Brown gently in hot skillet in canola oil.
Reduce heat and pour in 2 cups bouillon.
Scatter sliced onion over top.
Cover and simmer over low heat 1 1/2 hours.

title: brownie banana split pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare brownie mix according to package.
Spread on pizza pan.
You may wish to grease pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool to room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Spread on brownie mix.
Top with fruits and pecans.
Drizzle melted chocolate.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour and butter together with pastry blender until it looks like coarse crumbs, then

thoroughly mix sugar in, then add buttermilk. Mix until forms a good ball. Roll out onto a floured surface until about 1/2-inch thick. Cut and dip in butter. Place on baking sheet and cook in 450° preheated oven for 12 to 15 minutes, until golden brown.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and salt.
Add to popped corn in pot; stir and toss constantly over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Wait until sugar is dissolved and popcorn is completely coated with mixture. Remove from heat.
Form into balls.
Don't use pressure to form balls.
Keep hands buttered.
Makes 6 to 8 balls.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour with baking soda.
Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and pudding mix.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: butternut squash and leek soup
directions: Cook leeks, garlic cloves, salt and thyme in the butter until tender.
Add white wine and cubed squash. Cover with vegetable stock.
Season with salt and pepper and sprinkle with Gruyere cheese and fresh thyme.

title: pecan cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour with nuts and fruit already in it.
Add juice, a little at a time.
Mix well.
Bake in tube pan that has been lined with brown paper or foil.
(I put a pan of water in oven.)
Bake for 4 hours at 250°.
Let cool before storing.

title: lazy oven stew
directions: Cut meat in 1 to 1 1/2-inch cubes.
Coat with mixture of flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
In a 3-quart casserole, toss meat and oil.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes.
Stir once.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 90 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: tuna and macaroni salad
directions: First, cook the macaroni and boil eggs.
Mix together the tuna, onion, pickles and tomatoes.
Then, in a small bowl, mix your salad dressing (mayonnaise, mustard and sugar).

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook, drain and rinse macaroni.
Melt the 4 tablespoons of butter and add flour; blend on low heat.
Slowly add milk; bring to the boiling point, stirring constantly.
Add cheese; cook until cheese is melted and sauce is thickened.

title: ma stouts stuffed peppers
directions: Mix all ingredients using only one stack of crackers.
Adding the other stack as needed.
Put peppers in water bath and boil them till light green.
Cool.
Remove seed.
Stuff peppers and place in a long pan.
Place in oven and cook for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.
Makes about 18 to 20 peppers.

title: lemon pepper catfish
directions: Note:
The mix without the bread crumbs can be too spicy and peppery.

title: stir-fried venison and mushrooms
directions: About 30 minutes before serving, prepare rice as directed; keep warm.
Cut venison into 1/2 inch cubes.
In medium size bowl mix venison, soy sauce, wine, cornstarch, ginger, salt and garlic powder; set aside.
Thinly slice mushrooms and onion.
Cook mushrooms and onion in 12-inch skillet over medium to high heat, stirring quickly and frequently until mushrooms are tender.
Remove mixture to a bowl.
In same skillet over high heat cook venison mixture in 3 more tablespoons butter.
Stir quickly until tender. Return mushroom mixture to skillet; add peas and heat through. Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: best sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, vanilla, almond extract and egg. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill at least two hours. Divide dough in half.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: almond joys
directions: Melt oleo.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Mix in confectioners sugar and coconut.
Put into 8 x 13-inch pan (buttered).
Place almonds. Chill and cut in squares, then freeze.
Dip in melted chocolate almond bark.

title: highland flummery
directions: Blend the whiskey, lemon juice and honey (to thin the honey). Add double (heavy) cream and whisk until thick and light.
Spoon into 6 individual serving glasses.
Chill for several hours. Lightly toast oatmeal for a few minutes under grill or in a dry frying pan.
Sprinkle a pinch over each glass.
May be accompanied by sponge finger cookies, if desired.

title: braunschweiger dip
directions: Mix ingredients until soft and creamy.
Refrigerate.

title: dream bars
directions: Mix into crumbly mass; pat into a large greased cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, pudding and oil together and beat for 3 minutes until light and fluffy.
Add 7-Up and beat for another minute.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: potato pancakes(yields 25 pancakes)
directions: Mix everything together and fry in 1/2 cup oil like regular pancakes.
Serve sauerbraten and potato pancakes with applesauce.

title: blt pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cook bacon accordingly and crumble. Spread mayonnaise on each pizza shell.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumbled bacon.
Lay tomato slices over bacon.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.	Sprinkle lettuce over each pizza.
Serves 4.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes two 8-inch pies.

title: walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks. Add dry ingredients (which have been sifted together) alternately with water. Beat well after each addition. Add flavoring and unbeaten egg whites separately. Fold in nuts.

title: barb's oven stew
directions: Put beef, soup, soup mix and red wine in deep baking casserole, uncovered. Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Pour over rice or noodles.

title: banana pineapple loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and mix
well.
Stir
in
bananas.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda
and
salt,
and
add
to butter mixture.
Fold in pineapple,
coconut
and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans
to
just over half full.
Small or large pans may be used.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix dressing and butter.
Layer 1/2 on bottom of casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top of bottom half. Add remaining 1/2 of dressing mix and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pink jello salad
directions: Empty Jell-O into bowl.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water.
In a separate bowl, cream the cream cheese with an electric beater or blender until smooth.
Add Jell-O very carefully.
Add marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator until firm.

title: sugar-free mile-high apple pie
directions: Roll 1/2 of pastry on floured surface into circle.
Place in pie pan.
Combine all other ingredients and place in pie pan.
Top with top crust, with cut-outs in center.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: After mixture of soup and margarine are dissolved, add hash browns and onions with sauce; pour into a 13 x 9-inch buttered casserole dish.
Bake with dried onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Cook mixture of sugar, milk, flour, vanilla and egg yolks until thick.
Layer alternately with vanilla wafers and bananas. Top with meringue.

title: crustless spinach quiche
directions: Thaw and squeeze all moisture from spinach.
Combine spinach with remaining ingredients.
Bake in buttered 9-inch pie pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
(Can substitute shredded Cheddar.)

title: low calorie shrimp dip
directions: Blend the cottage cheese, lemon peel and juice, dill, salt and Tabasco in a blender until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Serve sprinkled with additional cut up parsley.
Yields 2 cups.

title: a dozen "devil of an egg"
directions: Boil eggs approximately 20 minutes.
Drain.
Run cold water over eggs.
Sprinkle salt in water and let stand a few minutes. (Eggs peel much easier.)
Drain eggs again.
Crack and peel eggs. Slice eggs, putting whites on egg dish and yolks in a bowl. Flatten egg yolks with fork.
Mix all other ingredients with egg yolks except paprika.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Makes 1 dozen full stuffed eggs.
Discard extra egg whites.

title: asparagus supreme
directions: Wash asparagus well and snap off tough part of spear.
Steam asparagus in 1/2 inch of water until soft.
Lift out of water and set aside; keep it warm.
To 1 cup of cooking water, add the butter or oleo, the flour, the salt and pepper.
Stir or whisk well over medium heat until smooth and thickened.
Place asparagus in serving dish.
Put halves of toast around the edge and slices of hard-cooked eggs on top.
Pour cream sauce over and serve.

title: modified rice krispies treats(quick and easy)
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in pan over moderate heat until mixture boils.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Take from stove and add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Put in greased 9x13 pan.
Top with melted chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.

title: gabriel's heavenly chicken spaghetti
directions: Rinse chicken well.
Cook in water to cover in saucepan until tender.
Drain, reserving 2 cups broth.
Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces, discarding skin and bones.
Saute celery and onions in butter in saucepan.
Add reserved broth, Worcestershire sauce, salt and red pepper; mix well.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Stir in soup and cheese gradually.
Add spaghetti to soup mixture in saucepan.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Stir in chicken and olives. Spoon into shallow 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with pecans. Bake at 350° until heated through.
Serves 12.

title: request punch
directions: Combine grape juice and ginger ale in pitcher; mix well. Chill.
Pour into chilled punch bowl.
Add ice, if desired. Yield:
20 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and pour into 8 x 8 pan. Bake 1 hour or until golden brown on top.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Blend well.
Shape into balls 1 inch in diameter.
Place 2 to 3 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Press flat with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Divide bread crumbs into 3 equal parts.
Preheat oven to 350°. Mix 1/3 of the bread crumbs in skillet with butter.
Saute onion and both peppers.
Mix 1/3 more bread crumbs, squash, eggs, salt, milk, sugar and black pepper.
Place in buttered dish. Sprinkle rest of bread crumbs on top. Bake for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Heat oil in heavy pan to hot, not boiling.
Remove from heat and add garlic powder, dill weed and dressing mix.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in oyster crackers until all moistened.
Transfer to large bowl.
All moisture will disappear.
Store covered.

title: chocolate fried pies("cow patties")
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add liquids.
(Looks like pancake batter.)
Cook on griddle like you would pancakes.

title: dream bars
directions: Make layer of whole graham crackers in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt
butter over low heat. Add sugar, milk and egg.
Stir. Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add coconut, nuts and graham cracker crumbs.
Pour over crackers in pan and cover with another layer of crackers.
Top with thin layer of vanilla icing.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat ingredients until thickened.
Carefully blend 2 cups Cool Whip into first ingredients.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill about 1 hour until set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: easy nut roast
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Spray 9 x 9-inch baking dish and pour into it.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: homemade applesauce
directions: In a large saucepan place the apple pieces, water and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil and simmer until the apples are tender. Press the apples through a colander or put them in the blender. Return the strained pulp to the saucepan.
Add enough sugar or honey for your own taste and sprinkle with cinnamon.
You can serve hot or cold.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 cups.
Takes approximately 20 minutes.

title: brown gravy chicken jalop
directions: Place chicken in
boiler,
covered over with water.
Let boil until tender.
Debone.
Put
meat
back
into
broth
(cut chicken meat in bite-size pieces).
Add about 3 stems of celery cut in small
pieces.
Let
tender,
then
add about 3 potatoes (peeled and cubed) and 2 medium size onions (peeled and cubed). Add pepper and
salt.
Let
cook
up together.
Then take flour (about 4 tablespoons), brown slowly in oven. Add to ingredients to thicken gravy.
You may serve on sliced bread or toast.
The amounts of ingredients may vary according to number served.

title: after-brunch cheese-n-cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
(Use a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or 9-inch spring-form pan.) Bake at temperature on package for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool cake on wire rack for 15 minutes.

title: galaxy cheese ball
directions: Combine Cheddar cheese and softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill 3 hours or overnight.
Shape into ball.

title: teriyaki oven chicken wings
directions: Blend ingredients together and pour over chicken wings. Marinate overnight and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: macaroni-green chili pie
directions: Brown meat with onion and garlic in oil; drain off excess fat. Add tomatoes, paste and seasonings and simmer 30 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Grease 9 x 13 pan. Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and oil together. Spread evenly in pan. Then mix cream cheese, 2 eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla until smooth. Pour over cake mixture. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove tops and seed from peppers.
In large kettle, bring water to boil.
Cook peppers five minutes.
Remove and drain. Cook rice according to instructions on package.
Set aside.
In a skillet brown ground beef and onions.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, herbs, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes.
Stir in rice.
Stuff cleaned peppers with the rice mixture.
Place upright in a shallow pan.
Mix beef broth in 1/2 cup water.
Add to pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: ellen's cocoa brownies
directions: Soften shortening, add sugar and cocoa; mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and baking powder.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: Wash and drain rice.
Heat pan on stove on medium heat.
Add oil in pan.
Saute chopped onion and pepper, about 1 minute.
Add chopped tomatoes and mix together for another minute.
Also add salt to taste.
Add rice and mix well.

title: cheese pudding
directions: *Use 12 slices if the slices are thin.
Remove the crust and cut bread into cubes.

title: onion pie
directions: Crush crackers and line 13 x 9-inch cake pan/casserole.
Saute onions in 1/2 c. butter until transparent.
Spread onions over crumbs.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour in an 8-inch square greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in shortening. Combine all the ingredients and place in a casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: icebox muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Bran Buds and let stand.
Mix Crisco, sugar, eggs, buttermilk and soaked Bran Buds.
Mix well.
Then stir in bran flakes and raisins.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir well.
Store in refrigerator to be used as needed. Can be stored for 6 weeks.
Bake muffins for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry cheese layer dessert
directions: Mix together graham crackers, nuts, and melted margarine; press into pie pan or 12 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: dirty rice
directions: Boil giblets until tender; cool, then cut meat into small pieces.
Brown ground meat and sausage.
Drain off fat.
Mix giblets and broth together; simmer.
Then make a roux, using approximately 2 cups of oil and 10 tablespoons flour.
Cook until dark brown.
Add onions, celery, bell peppers and garlic; cook until tender, then add to meat and broth.
Add seasoning and simmer.
You may add more of Lou's Seasoning, if needed.
May use chicken broth if not enough for rice.
I use 16 cups of instant rice, having enough broth according to amount as directed to cook rice.
May use regular rice.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, pumpkin, water and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, mixing in nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 (9 x 5-inch) loaves.

title: sloppy joe pie
directions: Press together 1 package crescent roll dough in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Cook and drain ground beef.
Mix sauce into ground beef and spread mixture on top of roll crust.
Layer cheeses on top of meat.
Top with remaining roll dough and brush with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.

title: peaches 'n cream cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom and sides of 9-inch deep dish or 10-inch pie pan.

title: meatballs
directions: Blend crackers and spices.
Add beef, egg and V-8.
Make into 1 1/2-inch balls (16).
Place in glass pie plate; cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, 1/4 cup sugar and melted margarine. Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and whipped cream (or Cool Whip) and spread over cool crust.
Chill.
Dissolve gelatin in hot pineapple juice.
Add strawberries and juice.
Let partially gel in refrigerator and spread over top of cream cheese mixture.
Chill.

title: fresh peach dessert
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Brown meats together and crumble.
Cook spaghetti and drain. Beat eggs, milk and Parmesan cheese together; mix with drained spaghetti.
Lay spaghetti in greased jelly roll pan.
Pour sauce over spaghetti and top with crumbled meat.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting and serving.
(Serves a bunch.)

title: barbara's tabouli
directions: Cover bulghur with boiling water.
Add salt and let stand 30 minutes; drain any excess water.
Stir in lemon juice, garlic and oil.
Add parsley and pepper.
Toss in vegetables and olives. Serve at room temperature.
Serves 6.

title: au gratin potatoes with pork chops
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Boil 20 minutes.
Drain potatoes and put them in greased casserole dish.

title: dirty rice
directions: Combine rice, mushrooms, dry onion soup mix, beef bouillon and water in casserole.
Bake in 450° oven until done.
Put butter on top.

title: pudding pie squares
directions: Place 10 graham crackers in a plastic bag.
Close and crush with a rolling pin.
Place in an 8 inch square baking dish.
Repeat with remaining crackers.
Set aside 2 tablespoons of crumbs.
In a small saucepan, melt butter and margarine over low heat.
Pour in baking dish.
Using a fork, stir together crackers and butter.
Pat mixture evenly over bottom of dish.
Chill in freezer for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, place sour cream, pudding mix and milk in a bowl and beat with an electric mixer on low speed for 1 minute. Scrape sides of bowl often, with a spatula.
Beat 30 seconds more. Pour into baking dish, spreading evenly over crust.
Carefully spoon pie filling over pudding mix.
Sprinkle with remaining cracker crumbs.
Cover dish with plastic wrap or foil.
Chill for at least 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Cut into squares. Serves 9.

title: rice dish
directions: Mix water chestnuts and mushrooms; saute.
Then mix water chestnut juice, mushroom juice, French onion soup and rice.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green onion; add garlic and pepper for spice, then drain. Mix in a separate bowl both enchilada sauces, picante sauce and cumin. Grate cheese and mix them together. Soften tortillas in microwave. Spoon hamburger in shell; add some cheese in shell, then roll the shell. Place in square baking pan. Continue until all shells are filled; pour sauce mixture over top of enchiladas. Add rest of cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole supreme
directions: Scrub
potatoes.
Cook	in
salted
water until tender. Drain. Cool, peel and mash coarsely.
Add sour cream, onions, milk, salt,
pepper and cheese.
Pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine
melted
margarine and bread crumbs; spread over potatoes for topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: quick cream cheese danish
directions: In an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, press together one package of roll dough, sealing edges together.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add lemon juice, salt, vanilla and egg yolk.
Mix well.
Pour over rolls in pan.
Place remaining package of rolls on top of cream cheese mixture (press out on wax paper first).
Brush with slightly beaten egg white.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Let cool completely (overnight) before slicing.
Cheese filling is very soft when it comes out of oven.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Serve as appetizer spooned over block of cream cheese.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil potato until done.
Remove skin and mash with fork, adding sugar, until dough is formed.
Roll out on wax paper and spread with peanut butter.
Roll dough up like a jelly roll. Refrigerate and chill completely.
Cut in 1/2-inch slices.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Seed and slice peaches and put in plastic bowl.
Pour 1 cup sugar over peaches.
Stir well.
Cover tightly and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: sweet corn bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together by stirring around until soft and combined.
Break the eggs into the butter and sugar and beat together with a large spoon.
Beat well.
Add the cornmeal, then sift together the flour, baking powder and salt and stir in alternating with the milk.
Beat after each addition; beat a little flour and milk until all ingredients are combined.
Turn into a greased baking pan about 2 to 2 1/2 inches deep.
Bake at 375° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, vanilla and water until smooth.
Add flour and nuts.
Mix well.
Chill dough 3 hours in refrigerator. After chilling, roll dough into small balls (walnut size).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Fill a deep bowl with confectioners sugar.
Place warm cookies in sugar (4 to 5 at a time) and turn to cover cookie completely.
Let cookies cool on a tray for an hour or so.

title: crab cakes
directions: Soak crackers in milk.
Mix dry ingredients into crab meat; add margarine and mix well.
Mix cracker mixture into crab mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into crab mixture. Make into cakes and fry in oil.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Brown ground beef with onions in dutch oven.
Drain off any fat.
Then add tomatoes and water, salt/pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil and add noodles.
Cook till noodles are done and serve over mashed potatoes.

title: linda's strawberry pie
directions: Mix altogether in saucepan and cook and stir until thick.
Let cool, then fold in 2 cups sliced strawberries.
Pour in baked pie shell. Garnish with Cool Whip.

title: v's veggies 2 go
directions: Dump and mix ingredients.
Top with crumbled Ritz crackers. Pour 1/2 stick of melted margarine on top (optional).
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower in small pieces; chop onion and add bacon bits and mix in green pepper.
Make a dressing of 2 tablespoons vinegar and 1/4 cup sugar.
Mix this mixture and pour over salad when ready to serve.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix the nuts, flour and melted butter to make crust.
Crust will be flaky. Spread in a 9 x 12-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: mushroom swiss steak
directions: Place meat on foil and sprinkle both sides with beef-mushroom mix.
Wrap loosely, sealing airtight.
Place in shallow pan and bake for 1 hour or until tender at 375°.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop artichoke hearts.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Serve with crackers.

title: souper pork chops
directions: Season pork chops, layer in baking pan.
Cover with soup and onions.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil.
Continue baking 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Mix together first seven ingredients.
Blend together cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add the sour cream, cornstarch and eggs to the cream cheese and sugar mixture, mixing well.
Blend the pumpkin and spice mixture with the cream cheese and sour cream combination.
Mix well. Pour in spring-form pan that is lined with graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Place water in a shallow pan in the oven as cake is cooking; this prevents it from cracking.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: Put flour, salt and
pepper
into
plastic bag.
Put in shrimp a few at a time;
shake to cover.
Fry in oil at medium heat.
Add shrimp to cooked rice and mix.

title: yummy cake
directions: Bake cake on cookie sheet with sides for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool cake.
Spread pineapple on top of cake.
Beat pudding with milk and cream cheese.
Spread on top of pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Brown onion in the butter in a skillet. Add 1 cup of the cashews, chicken and soup (undiluted). Simmer for 10 minutes. Serve over hot rice. Top each serving with cashews.

title: sour cream blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together; add gradually to the egg mixture, alternating with sour cream and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in 1 cup blueberries.
Pour half the batter into well-greased and floured pan, 9 x 13 x 2-inches.
Cover with remaining blueberries.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: pina colada
directions: Blend ice cream and milk with flavoring. Pour in a glass, top with fresh pineapple chunks.

title: baked crispy chicken (honey mustard)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large roasting pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch) in oven melt butter.
Remove pan from oven.
Combine bread crumbs and pepper.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix mustard, honey, lemon juice, ginger and garlic.
Add chicken pieces and mix until coated, then coat with bread crumb mixture.
Arrange chicken, skin side down in melted butter in roasting pan.
Bake 35 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 10 minutes longer or until golden brown and fork-tender.
(Cooking times for chicken breasts: approximately 12 minutes on one side, then 10 minutes on the other.
It depends on the thickness of the breasts.)

title: paige's chili
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil.
Add chili, corn and cooked macaroni.
Heat thoroughly.
Add cheese and allow it to melt before removing from the heat.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on mix. While still hot, poke holes in cake, 1 inch apart. Mix caramel topping and Eagle brand milk, pour over top of cake. Let cool. Ice with carton of cool whip; sprinkle with 3 crumbles heath bars on top.

title: easy rice
directions: Put in casserole dish (don't stir together).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
After the first 1/2 hour, stir.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Put shortening, sugars, vanilla and eggs in mixing bowl.
Beat thoroughly.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to bowl.
Stir in nuts and oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes before removing to cooling racks.
Bake only until golden or will dry out. Makes 5 dozen plus.

title: crawfish machu
directions: Saute crawfish in small amount of margarine and set aside.
Cut corn cream style.
Using large pot, melt margarine or oil.
Add Ro-Tel, tomatoes, peppers, garlic, onion and salt.
Cook slowly about 10 minutes.
Add water and cook until pepper and onions are tender.
More water may be needed.
This mixture should be a little thick.
Add crawfish; cook 10 minutes.
Makes 2 quarts.
Shrimp may be substituted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients. Place in a deep casserole dish and top with cracker crumbs, then dot with butter.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a square pan, heat 2 cups milk and bouillon cubes.
Pour 1/2 cup milk into bowl and add flour.
Stir until smooth and add to pan.
Heat milk mixture until it boils and cook 2 more minutes.
Stir in drained vegetables, chicken and parsley.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cut biscuits into quarters and cover chicken mixture.
Or make Bisquick drop biscuits and spoon dough onto chicken.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: bulgarian salad
directions: Combine corn, peas and green beans that have been drained with remaining vegetables.
Heat sugar, vinegar, salad oil, salt and pepper until sugar is dissolved.
Cool and then pour over vegetables.
Keep in refrigerator. Stir 2 or 3 times to mix dressing and vegetables.

title: ten minute shrimp casserole
directions: *If you add more shrimp, add more soup!

title: cracklin' corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into hot, well-greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Or cook on top of stove in greased iron skillet.

title: cafe mudslides
directions: In blender, combine coffee and creamer until frothy. Add ice and blend until smooth. Add ice cream 1 scoop at a time and blend to desired consistency.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil; remove from heat. Cool slightly and add flour and sugar.
Beat well and add remaining ingredients.
Beat well; pour onto greased and floured jelly roll pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 360°.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in saucepan until tender.
Drain well. Place potatoes in baking dish.
Blend flour and margarine in saucepan.
Add milk and cheese.
Cook over medium heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Pour over potatoes.
Add pepper and salt.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: fried oysters
directions: Mix the flour and oats together; set aside.
Beat the egg together with the milk.
Drain the oysters.
Salt and pepper oysters; dip one by one into egg mixture, then into flour mixture. Drop into hot cooking oil; cook until lightly browned.

title: christmas wassail(serves 24)
directions: Mix and heat to boiling.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: mexican manicotti
directions: Combine ground beef, refried beans, oregano and cumin.
Mix well.
Fill uncooked manicotti shells with meat mixture.
Arrange in a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine water and picante sauce; pour over manicotti shells.
Cover with vented plastic wrap.
Micro-cook on High for 10 minutes, giving dish a half-turn once.
Using tongs, turn shells over and micro-cook, covered, on Medium for 17 to 19 minutes or until pasta is tender, giving dish a half-turn once.
Combine sour cream, green onions and olives. Spoon down center of casserole.
Top with cheese.
Micro-cook, uncovered, on High 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: marbled cream cheese brownies
directions: Position rack in center of oven and preheat to 350°.
Line a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with aluminum foil so foil extends 2 inches beyond sides.
Lightly butter bottom and sides.
Melt chocolates. Cool 10 to 15 minutes until tepid.
In a large bowl, using a hand held mixer set at medium beat together cream cheese and 1/3 cup of the sugar until smooth.
Beat in one of the eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla until combined.

title: wimpy's fruit salad
directions: Mix well and sweeten to taste.

title: christmas punch
directions: Dissolve jello in 4 cups of boiling water.
Add sugar until dissolves.
Add all ingredients and 8 quarts water.
Mix well. Chill!

title: plum good pork(serves four)
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 350°.
Cut pork tenderloin 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut plums into halves.
Add olive oil to pan. Saute pork and onion slices 3 to 6 minutes, or until done.
Remove tenderloin and onions; drain excess oil.
Deglaze pan with wine, stock and halved plums.
Stir sauce until reduced to gravy-like consistency.
Pour sauce over tenderloin and onions.
Garnish serving plate with fresh fruit.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into patties and fry in shortening.
Serve immediately.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham crackers, 1 stick of oleo and granulated sugar together.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Beat in separate bowl the powdered sugar, 1 stick oleo, eggs and vanilla.
Spread cover crumb mixture in pan.
Put a layer of sliced bananas over sugar mixture.
Drain pineapple and sprinkle over bananas.
Put a layer of Cool Whip over the pineapple.
Sprinkle nuts and cherries over Cool Whip.

title: rachel's chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch round cake pans.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in eggs.

title: fancy yeast dough or bread
directions: Put yeast in bowl.
Add milk and stir until yeast is dissolved. Add sugar, eggs, salt and butter and mix well.
Then add flour; mix well.
Turn out into a greased bowl and cover.
Let stand until double in bulk.
Knead down again and allow it to rise about 45 minutes.
Then you make your rolls.

title: frogmore stew
directions: In a very large soup pot, bring water to a boil.
Add unopened crab boil, potatoes and celery.
Cook 1 to 2 hours, until potatoes are tender, but not overdone.
Add kielbasi, corn and butter; cook for another 30 minutes.
Add shrimp with shells on and cook until shrimp are pink (only 3 to 5 minutes).
Break open package of crab boil and stir.
Drain water and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: o henry bars
directions: In a pan, combine sugar and Karo syrup and bring to a boil. Take off stove right away.
Stir in peanut butter and rice crispies.
Pour into 9 x 13 inch pan.
Smooth level.
Melt chocolate chips and pour on top.
Let cool in refrigerator.
Cut in squares when cool and serve.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grate cranberries and add sugar.
Let it set 4 1/2 hours or more.
Add rest of ingredients and chill.
This will keep a long time and can be made several days in advance.

title: cold cucumber soup
directions: Mix in blender and add 1 peeled and seeded cucumber; blend. Chill 4 hours.
Sprinkle dill weed on top.
I usually use 2 cucumbers.

title: pizza pie
directions: On top of
crust put ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 400° until crust is golden brown.
Makes a lot. Good cut up into squares and
frozen.
Take
out
and heat individually in oven or microwave.

title: busy woman's cobbler
directions: Place peaches in shallow baking dish.
Slice margarine on top and place in oven until magarine melts.

title: soul chicken (or hungarian paprikash)
directions: Brown onions in large skillet with minimum amount of "Green Mazola" or "Can't Believe-It's-Not-Butter."
Add chicken and lightly brown on each side.
*Add chicken broth to barely simmer (about 1/4 inch in bottom of skillet), and simmer 20 minutes.
Test for tenderness and add more broth if necessary, do not allow to dry out.
(Should be enough liquid in bottom of pan to make sauce.* Sprinkle paprika liberally over chicken when simmering, this gives the sauce its flavor and color.
Add the pint of sour cream at the last and blend to make the sauce.
Do not boil or turn off since sauce may curdle.
When reheating use low flame and do not boil. Serve over rice or with spaetzles.

title: chili verde
directions: In Dutch oven or frypan, brown pork steaks; add salt, pepper and onion.
Stir until all liquid is gone.
Add tomatoes (squished).
Add garlic salt, chilies and enough water to cover meat mixture.
Bring to a boil; simmer until tender.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dream delight salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together. Chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: mex style skillet
directions: Combine sausage, onion and green pepper in heavy skillet.
Cook until sausage is brown, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Stir in other ingredients except cheese and sour cream.
Cover and reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream, cook until thoroughly heated.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: healthy french toast
directions: Mix eggs, whey protein, cinnamon and skim milk to desired consistency for dredging the bread in.
Dredge bread slices in mixture and cook in a hot non-stick skillet.
Once on your plate, top with sugar free syrup or sliced bananas.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Wash vegetables; drain and chop.
Place in large container. Sprinkle with salt.
Cover with weighted plate.
Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Add vinegar, mustard, spices (which have been tied in cheesecloth bag), sugar and horseradish.
Simmer about 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Pack in hot sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, vanilla and cocoa; mix well.
Add flour mix. Refrigerate for one hour.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until tops of cookies crack.

title: broccoli ham strata
directions: With a donut cutter or 2 glasses, one large and one small, cut out 12 "donuts" and "holes" from the bread.
Use remaining bread scraps to line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bread with cheese, broccoli and ham.
Arrange the bread ring and "holes" over the top.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Chill overnight or at least 6 hours.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: shirley's zucchini soup
directions: Place all ingredients in 1-quart pot and select either pepper or curry powder to season, but be frugal.
Bring to a boil; then simmer 20 minutes.
Tastes great.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix together all ingredients and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes. Enjoy.

title: flavored vinaigrette
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Whisk or shake to emulsify.
Toss with salad and serve immediately or use as a dressing for pasta, allowing time for pasta to absorb the vinaigrette.

title: refreshing rhubarb punch
directions: Boil the first 3
ingredients for 5 minutes and strain.
When cool, add 1/2 cup orange juice and juice from 1 lemon.
Chill.
When ready to serve, add the ginger ale.

title: baked apple doughnuts
directions: Sift the flour, then measure.
Sift the flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and sugar into a mixing bowl.
Cut in the shortening with a pastry blender.
Combine the egg, milk and grated apple in a small bowl.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs by hand.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Mix well.
Line unbaked pie shell with pecans.
Pour mixture on top of pecans.
Bake in oven for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Pie is done when the middle of pie is jelled.

title: macaroni with meat and cheese
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft.
Add meat and seasonings and brown lightly.
Alternate layers of macaroni, meat and cheese in baking dish.
Mix soup and milk; pour over cheese.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Dice avocados, tomatoes, lettuce and onion into small pieces. Put into a large bowl.
Add lemon juice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese and mix all ingredients.
Form into ball and roll in pecan pieces.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with crackers at room temperature.

title: kay's best beans
directions: Gently mix together and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together on high heat. Bring to a boil and add peanuts. Boil about 10 minutes. When peanuts crack or turn light brown, add salt. Stir well and remove from heat. Add soda. Pour mixture into 5 greased pie shell tins. Beat tin on table well. Remove from pans and break apart when cool.

title: bella's zucchini frittata
directions: Mix well together in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until golden brown. Cool slightly and cut into squares. Can be eaten warm or cold. Freezes well.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream first five ingredients.
Add next three ingredients and mix.
Fold in oats and cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Yield: about 100 cookies.

title: beef stew
directions: Dice or chop onion, brown.
Brown beef cubes on very high flame.
Add Accent (pinch), salt and pepper after meat is brown all over.
Add water to cover meat.
Add carrots diced in large pieces; add string beans cut in half.
Add potatoes, diced; season to taste.
Add mushroom gravy 1/2 hour to 3/4 hour later.
Let cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until done.

title: fig jam
directions: Put figs, sugar and lemon juice in boiler with water to keep from sticking.
Cook slowly until thick.
Pour in hot jars and seal.

title: spinach salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix spinach, cottage cheese and walnuts. Cover and chill.
In a jar or shaker, combine remaining ingredients.

title: fat-free microwave lemon cheesecake bars
directions: In a food processor, combine the brown sugar, salt, cinnamon and flour. Pulse to blend.
Add the oats and corn syrup and pulse until just combined. Reserve 1 cup crumbs.
To the remainder, add 2 tablespoons egg substitute and pulse to combine.
Spray an 8 or 9-inch microwave-safe square pan with cooking spray and press crumb mixture into the bottom.

Microwave on 50% power for 2 minutes, rotating the pan 1/4 turn after 1 minute. Set aside to cool. Blend together the cream cheese, sugar (to taste), lemon rind, egg substitute (1/4 cup), lemon juice and sour cream until very smooth.

Spread over cooled crust and top with reserved crumbs. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes, rotating the pan 1/4 turn every 2 1/2 to 3 minutes. The center should look slightly moist. Cool, then cover and chill thoroughly.
Makes 16 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones.
Mix stuffing, melted butter and 1/2 cup chicken broth to make dressing.
In 2 1/2-quart casserole dish, alternate layers of chicken and dressing, ending with dressing.
Mix soup and 1 1/3 cans chicken broth.
Pour over chicken and stuffing.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix all other ingredients, except pecans, with the cheese.
Form into a ball.
Roll in the chopped pecans.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Mix together in a bowl.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes to marinate.

title: walnut cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until done.

title: ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Arrange 1/2 bread in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place cheese and then ham over bread.
Arrange rest of bread over ham.
Mix milk, eggs, salt and mustard.
Pour over pan and refrigerate overnight.
Then stir corn flakes into melted oleo and put over bread.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or 325° if glass dish.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Melt the margarine.
Add the sugar and milk. Boil 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Add the peanut butter, oats and vanilla. Mix well and drop by teaspoons on waxed paper.
Let set until cool.

title: hot peas
directions: Melt cheese and mushroom soup together.
Add peas and red pepper.

title: beet pickles
directions: Dissolve sugar and salt in vinegar.
Bring to boil. Add beets and celery seeds; simmer for 20 minutes.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix all other ingredients except fruit and pour over butter.
Pour fruit on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: georgia peach pie
directions: Combine brown sugar and 1/2 cup granulated sugar, salt and tapioca; pour over peaches and mix gently.
Sprinkle mixture with almond extract.
Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Pour in peach mixture.
Dot with butter.
Roll out remaining pastry and place over pie.
Seal edges by fluting; prick top with fork.
Brush top crust with cold water and sprinkle with small amount of sugar before putting pie in oven, if desired.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 375° and bake for 40 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serve with bowl of freshly whipped cream on the side.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: fiesta chicken
directions: Rinse chicken breasts, split in half and cut each piece again in half, making 8 pieces in all.
Dip chicken in flour; shake off excess.
Rinse peppers; remove seeds and membrane.
Slice.
Heat butter in skillet.
Brown chicken pieces all around.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
Remove from skillet and keep warm. Heat oil in pan; add peppers.
Cover with lid.
Cook peppers for about 5 minutes, shaking pan frequently.
Remove from pan.
Add bouillon cube dissolved in water to pan.
Stir to dissolve pan juices and drippings.
Add wine.
Add chicken and peppers to pan. Cover with lid.
Heat; cook for about 6 to 7 minutes or until chicken is done.
Sprinkle with some fresh herbs or add thinly sliced green onion.

title: katie and kelly's cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, margarine, egg, vanilla and almond extract.
Stir in flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Divide dough into halves.
Roll 3/16-inch thick on floured board.
Cut into shapes.
Place on lightly greased (or foil covered) cookie sheet. Prepare egg yolk paint.
Paint on cookies.
Bake until edges are light brown (about 7 to 8 minutes).

title: fruit punch
directions: Add all juices and water.
Add ginger ale and soda water prior to serving.
Add crushed ice.

title: candied yams
directions: Cook Karo, sugar and butter 5 minutes and pour over raw sweet potatoes. Bake, dipping juice over potatoes often. Bake until done in a 400° oven. Freezes well.

title: german potato salad
directions: Brown flour; remove flour from stove.
Mix water, vinegar and cooled flour together.
Fry cut up bacon until done.
Then fry onion in bacon drippings.
Mix bacon, onion, sugar, salt and pepper in with flour mixture, vinegar and water.
Pour over potatoes.
Serve hot.

title: golf balls
directions: Melt in double boiler.
Dip balls in chocolate, then place on waxed paper.
Can be dipped twice, but once is usually enough. For best results, have water very hot, but not boiling.

title: fresh steamed fish
directions: In a large frying pan, heat oil over medium heat for 1 minute. Add onions and saute until transparent.
Add garlic, tomatoes, salt and black pepper and mix well.
Place fish in the center of tomato mixture.
Cover and simmer for about 25 minutes or until fish is tender and flaky.

title: terrific bacon salad
directions: Place ingredients in layers, beginning with cut up lettuce. Add 1/2 of bacon pieces, then celery and pepper.
Add frozen peas. Slice the eggs and add.
Top the eggs with remaining bacon pieces, then cover with mayonnaise.
To finish, top with grated cheese.
Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: sherry beef
directions: Mix all together. Bake 3 hours at 350° or until beef is done. Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: coating for fried chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in a plastic bag.
Shake well.
Coat chicken twice.
Melt one stick of margarine in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place raw coated chicken in dish.
Bake at 400° for approximately 1 hour, turning once.

title: pineapple mint jam
directions: Mix well the pineapple and 3/4 cup water.
Add lemon juice. Add sugar to fruit in saucepan and mix well.
Place over high heat.
Bring to a full rolling boil and boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and, at once, stir in Certo.
Skim off foam with metal spoon.
Then stir and skim for five minutes to cool slightly and to prevent floating fruit.
Add flavoring and coloring.

title: party potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes.
Cool, peel and grate.
Mix all ingredients and bake in casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fort lauderdale dressing(lib brooks)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add egg, salt, juice of 1 lemon and onion.
Add salad oil slowly.

title: quick pizza sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Unwind rolls and separate along perforations, forming 4 rectangles.
Press together in the center of each rectangle to seal.
Put 2 rectangles of dough on an ungreased baking sheet.
Moisten edges of dough with water.
Place 2 slices of Mozzarella in the center of each rectangle, spread with 2 teaspoons tomato paste and sprinkle with 1/8 teaspoon oregano.
Cover each with remaining dough rectangle.
Press edges firmly with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: german meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and keep adding crackers until you can form a loaf.
Mix thoroughly. Transfer to baking dish and form into oval loaf. Bake at 350° for
1 1/4 hours.
If desired, spread 1/4 cup catsup over loaf the last 15 minutes of baking time. Let set at a slant for 5 minutes before slicing. (This allows the grease to drain off.)

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange potatoes in casserole.
Boil remaining ingredients, stirring for 3 minutes.
Remove and pour over potatoes.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 45 minutes.
You may need to baste after potatoes have cooked about 20 minutes.

title: melting moments cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, cornstarch and powdered sugar. Set aside.
In mixer on medium speed, beat margarine until smooth. Gradually add dry mixture until blended, then add vanilla.
Mix well. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls * and place them 1 1/2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer 1/2 of the sliced zucchini in 9 X 13-inch pan.

Put 1/2 of the browned hamburger on top. Repeat with remaining zucchini and hamburger. Sprinkle 1/4 cup Bisquick on top. Pour 2 cups spaghetti sauce on top. Mix together 1 beaten egg to 1 cup cottage cheese. Stir in 1 cup Bisquick. Pour mixture into pan and cover top. Bake 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's fudge
directions: Mix all together and stir.
Let boil 1 minute or until it forms soft ball in cold water.

title: beef mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread mix as directed on package.
Make up burrito mix as directed on package with cooked ground beef.
Pour enough cornbread mixture into bottom of lightly greased 10 x 10 x 2-inch casserole pan.
Put burrito mixture on top; top with cheese.
Pour remaining cornbread mixture on top.
Shake pan to let air bubbles escape.
Bake as directed on cornbread package until top is golden brown.
Let set 15 minutes before cutting.

title: milanesa
directions: Put eggs, garlic salt, pepper in a bowl and beat them, then dip sirloin steak in breading.
Fry until they are brown over low heat.
(Does not take long because the steak is thin.)

title: egg ribbons
directions: Use two dark and one white slice per stack.
Place dark slice on bottom and top.
Butter and spread filling between each slice. Cut off crusts.
Repeat.
Wrap and chill.

title: italian cod fillets
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, combine first 2 ingredients and 2 tablespoons oil.
In bowl, combine next 4 ingredients and remaining oil.
Press mixture onto fish.
Place on spinach.
Cover; bake 10 minutes.
Uncover; bake 5 minutes more or until fish flakes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spoon bread
directions: Place milk in top of double boiler and heat scalding.
Slowly add cornmeal.
Beat until smooth.
Add butter and cook for 20 minutes.
Separate eggs; beat yolk.
Add yolk and baking powder to first mixture.
Beat egg whites until they peak; fold into the mixture.
Add chopped turkey or chicken.
Pour into a well-greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Empty cake mix package into mixing bowl.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 9 to 13 minutes.

title: skillet supper
directions: Cut wieners into short thin strips.
Saute in melted oleo in large skillet; remove.
Stir flour and salt into remaining oleo. Gradually blend in milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until thick and smooth.
Add meat and remaining ingredients. Cover and cook over low heat about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: layered turkey casserole
directions: Cook lasagne noodles according to directions (drain and rinse in hot water); in a large bowl, combine soups, sour cream, Parmesan cheese, onion, olives, pimento and garlic salt.
Gently stir in meat.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; place 3 noodles in dish and cover with 1/3 of meat mixture.
Sprinkle with 1 cup grated cheese evenly over meat mixture; repeat layers twice more, ending with cheese on top.
