Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; if made ahead and refrigerated bake about 60 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix together sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over butter in dish.
Pour peaches over flour mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until crust is lightly browned.

title: fruit parfait
directions: Mix everything and freeze.
Let stand at room temperature a few minutes before serving.
May be served as breakfast dish, salad or in sherbet glasses with a tiny bit of ginger ale as dessert.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Squeeze lemon into small bowl (remove seeds); set aside.
Put cream cheese, condensed milk and lemon juice into mixing bowl. Beat until creamy.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serves approximately 6.

title: pennsylvania dutch apple cake
directions: Beat well the sugar, oil and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients except apples and nuts.
Mix and fold in chopped apples and nuts. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: taco pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese and sour cream with 1/2 of the taco seasoning mix. Spread on a large platter. Spread salsa or picante sauce on this. Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and cheese.
Add your choice of onion, black olives and jalapeno peppers to taste. Serve with tortilla chips. Great for large crowds.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour, mustard and salt.
Gradually stir in canned milk.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add tuna and pimento.
Line a baking dish with crescent roll dough.
Pour tuna mixture over dough.
Cover with grated cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Remove foil for last 5 minutes.

title: silver cake
directions: Cream butter until light, adding sugar; gradually add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla, beating well after each addition.
Gently fold in egg whites.
Bake in 2 layer pans at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
When cool, fill and frost as desired.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix ingredients together in large mixer bowl.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam before filling with batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and add remaining ingredients in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: pillsbury bonbons
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add condensed milk and mix until smooth.
Add vanilla, nuts and flour (mix until it works like "play dough").
Wrap batter around each kiss (or other candy).
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes (don't overbake).

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine the vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper and 1/2 can of French fried onions.
Put in a 2-quart casserole and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with the remaining cheese and onions; bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: chicken manicotti
directions: Cook manicotti shells according to package directions.
Drain and set aside.
Mix 1/2 can soup with 1/4 cup sour cream in large bowl.
Add chicken and stir well.
Stuff manicotti shells with chicken mixture.
Place in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter over medium-low heat in skillet.
Saute mushrooms and onions until tender.
Add remaining soup and sour cream in skillet until heated through.
Pour mushroom and soup mixture over manicotti. Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Sprinkle cheese over top and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Soak oatmeal in hot water for 20 minutes with salt.
Cream butter, sugar, eggs and baking soda.
Add flour and oatmeal mixture to creamed mixture.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed for 30 minutes at 350°
While still hot, frost with Oatmeal Bar Frosting.

title: tetra ziney
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter, saute onion.
Add meat, salt, pepper and tomato sauce; simmer.
Beat together cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream, some onion with tops, bell pepper and noodles.
Butter bottom of pan, put in noodles; mix.
Then pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top and some onion with green tops.
Cook 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve with salad and bread.

title: cheese and ham macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water according to package directions.
Drain well and place into mixing bowl.
Add grated cheeses, reserving 1/2 cup to sprinkle on top.
Stir in cheeses until melted.
Stir in margarine, eggs paprika, salt, pepper; no need to beat first, just stir well to distribute evenly.
Add milk. Mixture will be fairly liquid.
Pour into a 9 x 13 pan, sprinkle reserved cheese on top and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes, until set.	Serve.

title: old-timey scalloped tomatoes
directions: Heat tomatoes and butter in a saucepan over moderate heat just until butter melts.
Mix in crumbs, sugar, salt and pepper.

Spoon into buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, sprinkle ground allspice lightly over the top, then bake, uncovered, in a hot oven (400°) for 40 to 45 minutes, just until mixture seems "set" in the middle and is lightly browned.
Let stand at room temperature about 5 minutes before serving.

title: cherries in snow
directions: Mix the cream cheese, whipped cream and powdered sugar.
Put half of this mix into clear glass dish. Break off small pieces of cake and put on top of mixture. Top with half of the cherry filling.
Repeat and enjoy.
Can be chilled!

title: buttercup cookies
directions: Slice
cookie
roll
into
slices about 1/4-inch thick. Halve the slices.
Place each half into a miniature muffin cup which has been
lined
with
a
paper liner, or has been well greased or sprayed with Pam.
Top with a Reese's candy.
Place the other half
of the cookie slice over the candy.
Bake for 10 or 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: fruit kabobs with whiskey baste
directions: In mixing bowl, combine honey, whiskey and lemon juice; add pineapple chunks, banana pieces, orange sections and cherries. Gently toss to coat fruit well.
Cover and refrigerate up to 2 hours or until ready to grill.
Remove fruit with slotted spoon, reserving the whiskey baste to brush on fruit kabobs while grilling.
Alternately thread fruit onto skewers.
Grill fruit kabobs, on covered grill, over medium-low coals, 5 to 10 minutes or until fruit is warmed through.

title: potato casserole
directions: Recipe calls for bread crumbs to be spread on top of casserole and the margarine spread over crumbs, but you can just spread the melted margarine over the casserole.
Bake about 1 hour and 10 minutes on 350°.
This makes a big casserole so, if you wish, you can divide in half and freeze one.
If you divide, cooking time is shorter.

title: perfect key lime pie
directions: Whip the cream until stiff; fold in condensed milk and Key lime juice.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate 6 hours.
Decorate top with whipped cream premade.

title: applesauce oatmeal bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla. In a separate bowl, mix the flours, baking powder, soda and spices; add them to the wet ingredients in first bowl.
Mix in oat flakes, applesauce and walnuts.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 9 x 5-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, until a toothpick comes out clean.
Remove bread from oven; cool completely.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients. Pour into a clear glass bowl. Refrigerate.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: Drain cherries and reserve liquid.
In small saucepan, bring cherry liquid to simmer.
Add cornstarch and cook, stirring, until sauce comes to boil and thickens.
Cool to room temperature, then cover and set aside.
When ready to serve, put ice cream in chilled individual dessert plates.

title: bacon horseradish dip(makes 2 cups)
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and chill. Serve on crackers.

title: red cinnamon applesauce salad
directions: Heat water to boiling.
Add cinnamon candies and stir until dissolved.
Add the package of cherry Jell-O and stir.
Add the applesauce and mix well.
Pour mixture into a 13 x 9-inch dish and chill until set.
Cut into serving size squares, about 8 to 12 pieces.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix jelly and mustard.
Cook on low heat until blended and smooth.
Add wieners and simmer for 30 minutes.
For small portions or servings example:
make a portion of 2 to 1, 2 tablespoons of jelly, 1 tablespoon of prepared mustard and prepare the same.
If too sour to your taste, add a small amount of brown sugar.

title: mayhaw stromboli
directions: Mix together mayhaw jelly, mayonnaise and mustard until smooth.
Set aside.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Place dough on lightly greased baking sheet; pat into 15 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham and onion lengthwise down center.
Drizzle half of sauce over ham. Moisten all edges of dough with water. Bring each long edge of dough to center; press edges together securely to seal.
Seal ends.
Brush dough with 1 tablespoon butter.
Sprinkle with cornmeal and invert.
Brush top with remaining butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 28 minutes.
Serve remaining sauce on sides.
Yields 4 servings.

title: lye soap
directions: When transporting a decorated cake, keep the wrap or cake cover from touching the frosting by cushioning with marshmallows or raisins stuck on toothpicks.
Insert the toothpicks in the top and sides of cake.
Wrap and you are on your way.

title: company salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
When cold, add pineapple, bananas and marshmallows.
Pour in large, flat dish and cool until set.
In double boiler, mix sugar, egg, flour and pineapple juice; cook until thickened.
Chill whipping cream.
Fold into juice mixture and spread over jello.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over top.
Chill overnight.

title: cream pie with pecans
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk and cook over low heat until mixture is thick.
Beat egg yolks.
Mix 1/2 cup of this mixture with egg yolks, add to milk mixture.
Add mandarin juice, mandarin peel and butter.
Stir and cook over low heat until the custard is thick.
Add pecans.
Cool custard and pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and water at high speed for 3 minutes.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time. When whites hold soft peaks, add salt and vanilla.
Cover custard with meringue.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Saute onion and butter.
Stir in flour and brown.
Stir in milk and thicken.
Add salt & pepper.
Put over sliced potatoes. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncover and bake 1/2 hour more.

title: coconut cake with pineapple
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until mixture is smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Add flour and alternate with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Finely chop bread; set aside.
Finely chop mushrooms, carrots, onion, celery and red pepper.

In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook vegetables and 1/2 teaspoon salt until vegetables are tender and well browned, about 20 minutes. Remove skillet from heat, cool slightly.

title: brit and bill's bacon and franks
directions: Cut franks in half (crosswise).
Wrap bacon around franks and secure with toothpicks.
Put franks in crock-pot.
Put layer of brown sugar on top and layer until all are in the pot.
Cook on low for 3 hours.
Dip out grease occasionally.
Serve hot, alone or with sweet and sour mustard.

title: texas two-step chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place chicken in a 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Mix picante sauce, sugar and mustard.
Pour sauce mixture over chicken. Bake for 20 minutes or until chicken is done. Serve over rice.

title: quick 'n' easy lasagne
directions: Combine cheeses.
Brown ground beef, mushrooms and onion. Season with garlic salt, oregano, salt and pepper while cooking. Drain this mixture and stir in Italian dressing and Ragu sauce. Let cook 10 minutes.
Cook lasagne noodles until soft.
Cover bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan with several spoonfuls of sauce (to avoid sticking).
Put layer of noodles, Parmesan cheese, Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown.
Serves 6.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Optional:
Use pineapple tidbits instead of strawberries.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken, seasoning chicken with salt and pepper to taste. When done, remove skin and bone.
Place chicken in greased 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix can of cream of celery soup and the chicken broth (1 1/4 cups).
Heat soup-broth mixture and add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over chicken.
Melt margarine and mix with flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk and spoon evenly over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: spice and raisin rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium-low heat until thoroughly heated.
Makes 4 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix all the filling ingredients together.
Divide and spread evenly over tortillas.
Roll up and cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Unwrap and cut into 1/2 to 3/4 inch thick slices.
Serve with salsa.

title: val's good ole cornbread
directions: Put oil in frying pan. Get hot so bread won't stick. Mix ingredients. Pour into hot frying pan. Rub a little grease on top. Place in oven. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: recipe for life
directions: Mix together chutzpah, love, dreams, political action and fun. Transfer into saucepan and add military budget.
Reduce by half over high heat, stirring constantly.
Yields health, education and playgrounds for all
the world's kids.

title: chocolate eggnog frosting
directions: Melt the chocolate in a double boiler.
Remove from water; add the sugar and hot water.
Blend.
Add the egg and butter, one tablespoon at a time, beating thoroughly after each tablespoon. Add a little rum or vanilla.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook onion and mix with prepared chicken.
Mix soups and milk. Pour over chicken, peas, onions, carrots and mushrooms in a casserole dish.
Mix stuffing as directed on the package and place on top of the casserole.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Mix sugars and flour.
Beat in eggs, milk and butter.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: chipped beef appetizer
directions: Cream milk and cream cheese.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Good hot or cold.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in refrigerator.
For smaller salad, just use half of the ingredients.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown
onions
in Wesson oil.
Add hamburger and brown. Add tomato
sauce,
a little water (if needed), salt, pepper, Italian seasoning and oregano.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Cook lasagna noodles as directed on package.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch greased baking
dish as	follows:
noodles,
boiled
eggs, cheese and sauce.
Repeat until
all	ingredients
are used and top with sauce.
Bake
at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted good.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: fresh apple dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix dry cake mix, margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon until crumbly.
Reserve 2/3 cup crumbly mixture. Press remaining crumbly mixture in bottom of an ungreased pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Arrange apple slices on mixture in pan.
Beat sour cream and egg until well blended; spread over apples.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbly mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, or until topping is light golden brown.
Cool.
Makes 16 servings.

title: san dee bean soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pot.
Cover with water.
Cook several hours.
Cover the pot halfway through cooking process. Add water as needed.
Serve with cornbread and cole slaw.

title: cherry chocolate dessert
directions: Have cake layer ready.
Spread with thin coat of margarine. Simmer cherries, 3/4 cup juice and lemon juice (add water, if needed).
Add 1/2 cup sugar and stir for 5 minutes.
Mix remaining sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add to boiling fruit.
Stir until smooth and thickened.
Simmer 5 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon margarine.
Stir in almond extract.
Cool to room temperature, then cool in refrigerator.
When cool, spread on cake, just on top.
(Use deep dish pie plate, etc.)
Whip cream with sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top of cherries.
Decorate with chocolate shavings.

title: marinated cucumbers and onions
directions: Put 1/2 of the onion rings in a bowl.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the sugar, salt, pepper and oil.
Next, put cucumbers and repeat layers with remaining sugar.
Combine vinegar and water and pour over cucumbers and onions.
Shake.
Chill.
Will stay crisp, 2 to 3 days.

title: chocolate cherry drops
directions: Stir together flour, soda and salt; set aside. Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy. Blend in vanilla. Add flour mixture and stir to blend. Stir in chocolate chips, nuts and cherries. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: margie scott's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars and oil.
Add the two eggs and beat. Sift the flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add 2 cups oatmeal and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350°.
When cookies are about half done and are beginning to flatten, press almost completely flat with a fork and finish baking.
Watch so as not to burn.

title: banana split pie
directions: Make crust of crackers and add 1/2 stick margarine.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix margarine, eggs and powdered sugar with an electric mixer on high for at least 15 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Slice bananas over the mixture.
Spread pineapple and bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Garnish with nuts and cherries.
Chill overnight.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, salt and pepper and onion soup mix.
With heel of your hand spread out on wax paper to form a round shape.
Combine catsup and mustard and spread over meat.
Spread onion and then lay 3 to 4 slices of cheese.
Roll jelly roll style, sealing edges.
Over the top of loaf you may lay bacon pieces, if desired.
Put in loaf pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, pineapple and soy sauce in small saucepan.
Heat, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Dissolve cornstarch in cold water.
Stir into hot mixture and continue heating until bubbly and thickened.
Makes 1 cup.
Great with chicken tenders and meat balls.

title: greek salad
directions: Toss all together and chill overnight.

title: guacamole for a crowd
directions: Mash avocados or put in a food processor until smooth.
Put avocados in a bowl; mix in sour cream, cottage cheese, garlic, jalapenos, onion, tomato and lemon juice.

title: scrumptious chicken salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain well. Cool.
(Rinse with cold water to cool quickly.)
Combine cooled macaroni, chicken, celery, peas, pineapple, almonds and pimento in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise or salad dressing, lemon juice, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Blend well.
Gently stir dressing into chicken mixture until ingredients are evenly coated. Chill.
Makes six servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Use sweetened applesauce.
Add to creamed mixture, then add raisins with dry ingredients.
Bake in slow oven.
This cake will keep fresh for quite some time.

title: date-nut-orange cake(makes one 9-inch tube cake)
directions: Combine.
Stir well to dissolve sugar.
Slowly pour over hot cake, being sure to pour into the crack on top of cake and around the side of tube pan.
Allow the cake to stand overnight in refrigerator before removing from the pan.

title: lo-cal cheese soup
directions: Dissolve Butter Buds in 1 cup water.
Add 7 cups water and bouillon cubes.
Add onion, potatoes, carrots, cabbage and bay leaf.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours, then add cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Peel and core tomatoes.
Squeeze out all liquid.
Cut into quarters and then cut again.
Cook for 30 minutes.
Measure the cooked tomatoes and add equal part sugar as you have cooked tomatoes.
Add the lemon, sliced real thin.
Simmer until thick; stirring constantly.
Pour hot mixture into jars and seal.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Roll in finely chopped nuts (or sugar).
Makes 6 dozen.
This is even better if you spill the extract in the mixture.

title: skillet pork chops and rice
directions: In a large skillet cook pork chops over medium heat, turning once until brown on both sides.
Remove to a plate.
Add rice and seasonings from rice mix to skillet along with water, tomatoes and their liquid, scallions and raisins; mix well.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low and place pork chops on top of rice.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: midnight cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and beat. Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: southern chess pie(much like southern pecan pie)
directions: Heat oven to 375° (quick moderate).
Mix together sugars and flour.
Beat in thoroughly eggs, milk, vanilla and butter.
Fold in pecans.
Pour in pastry-lined pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes. Serve slightly warm, plain or with whipped cream.

title: german pancake
directions: Place eggs, milk, flour and salt in a blender; cover and process until smooth.
Pour the batter into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Add the butter.

title: chili stew
directions: In a large pot, combine beans, carrots, potatoes, onion and soup.
Add 2 cups water to mixture and cook over low heat for 5 hours.
Brown ground beef, along with chili powder, salt, pepper and garlic until meat is brown.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 1 more hour.
Serve with salad and rolls.
A good hot winter meal.

title: anitpasto
directions: Combine all ingredients but basil and oregano.
Sprinkle the basil and oregano over entire mixture and toss.
Cover and chill. Serve with bread sticks, crackers or pieces of crusty rolls.
(I eliminated some of the ingredients and it was still very good.)

title: pineapple-honey glaze
directions: Combine ingredients in a saucepan, stirring and simmering over low heat for 5 minutes.
During last 1/2 hour of roasting, spoon over chicken or pork.
Return to oven to finish cooking.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute sliced onion rings in oleo until limp.
Layer in casserole in this order:
onions, Parmesan cheese (heavy) and cracker crumbs.
Repeat layers until all ingredients are used. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix lemon jello with water and set cool.
Before completely set, add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Put in mold and chill.

title: sweet meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400. Beat eggs & yolk together, mix together with all ingredients except nuts & raisins. Once blended, fold in nuts & raisins. Pour mixture into shell and bake 40 minutes or until firm.

title: pia colada chiffon pie
directions: Drain juice from pineapple. In saucepan, combine 1/2 cup pineapple juice and marshmallows. Cook until melted. Remove and stir in crushed pineapple, rum extract and salt. Cool. Fold in 1 cup whipped cream. Use remaining whipped cream to garnish top of pie.

title: ham stroganoff
directions: Saute the ham and onion in 2 tablespoons butter until onions are cooked.
Add mushrooms and soup; stir until heated through. Stir in sour cream and heat carefully (if it boils it will separate).

title: pork ribs sauce
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together, except pork ribs. Brown pork ribs on both sides. Pour the sauce over top and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in pan and bring to boil.
After cool add garlic.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Makes 1 pint.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat in large skillet.
Drain. Add garlic, 1/2 teaspoon salt and water.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in spaghetti sauce and tomato paste.
Cook, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: While pie crust is warm, sprinkle with melted butter and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Place whole berries, tips up, in circles inside crust.
In saucepan, combine remaining ingredients and bring to gentle simmer.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, until thick and clear.
Pour glaze over berries in pie.
Chill pie.
Serve topped with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: stuffed pasta shells
directions: Cook shells while browning hamburger.
Mix meat, eggs, Mozzarella cheese, milk, bread, salt and pepper.
Drain shells. Add warm water.
Fill shells, one at a time.
Put 1/2 Ragu sauce in bottom of pan and some Mozzarella cheese.
Put filled shells in pan and cover with remaining Ragu sauce.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: baked tomatoes(serves 4)
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in 9 x 12-inch pan at about 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: brownie dessert pizza
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions. Spread in a 12-inch round greased/floured pizza pan. Bake for 22 minutes at 350°. Let cool. Frost with favorite flavor frosting. Decorate with toppings you like.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Slice thin.
Heat 3 tablespoons butter in saucepan over low heat until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat stirring constantly until smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat, stir in milk.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Layer potatoes, onions and sauce in 2-quart casserole.
Dot top with 1 tablespoon butter or oleo.
Cover.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Uncover, cook until tender 60 to 70 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Good with leftover ham cubes.
May also add cheese for au gratin sauce.

title: chicken-broccoli cordon bleu
directions: Place chicken between 2 pieces of plastic wrap.
With meat mallet or rolling pin, pound chicken to 1/4 inch thickness.
Place a ham slice and cheese slice on each breast half.
Roll up chicken from narrow end, jelly-roll fashion.
Tuck in ham and cheese if necessary; secure with wooden toothpick.
In 10 inch skillet over medium heat, in hot oil, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on all sides.
Spoon off fat.

title: lemonade fluff pie
directions: Add gelatin
and
egg yolks to water with salt and cook until slightly
thick.
Stir
in lemonade concentrate.
Chill until firm.
Beat
egg
whites and fold in.
Put in cooked pie crust and top with whipped cream.

title: donuts
directions: Mix well and drop with teaspoon in hot oil until golden brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar after draining on paper towel.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all filling ingredients until well blended and pour into a casserole baking dish.

title: gummy worms
directions: Mix in saucepan until mixture resembles play dough, then place pan over low heat and stir until melted. Once melted, pour into plastic candy molds quickly and place in freezer for at least 5 minutes (no more than 10). This will give you a consistency a little more "rubbery" than regular Jell-O (which is what you want).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli into small flowerets (some of the stem can be used if tender).
Add frozen peas (do not cook) and green onions. Toss with Ranch dressing and garnish with a jar of sliced pimento.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown
the
ground
beef
with	onions	and seasonings. After it is browned, stir in the enchilada sauce, tomato sauce and soup. Heat
until
it
comes
to
a boil.
In a casserole dish, put half
the chips, meat and cheese in layers.
Repeat chips, meat and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: apple fritters
directions: Peel apples. Combine apples, sugar and cinnamon together. Cook over medium heat until cooked down.
Remove from heat. Separate biscuit dough. Roll each biscuit flat.

Put 2-3 Tbsp. full of cooked apples in the middle of each biscuit. Fold biscuit over and seal by pressing the edges with the back of a fork. Place on a cookie sheet and brush with melted butter. Bake at 350° for about 20-25 minutes or until golden brown.
Be careful that the edges don't burn because they are thinner than the rest.

title: corn-in-the-husk(microwave cooking time: 11 to 12 minutes)
directions: Discard soiled outer portion of husk.
Soak corn 10 minutes in cold water.
Drain, but don't dry.
Arrange corn in spoke-like fashion on microwaveproof plate.
Cook on High for 6 minutes. Rearrange; cook 6 minutes more.
Let stand 3 minutes before serving.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except egg.
Add egg and mix thoroughly.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mac cheese - spag bake
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as box states.
Brown hamburger and add Prego
(may add any seasonings such as sugar, basil, oregano, parsley - whatever you put in spaghetti sauce).
Add Mac Cheese to spag sauce and corn.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 350° for 20-30 minutes.
Toward end of baking time, top with cheese and melt.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake as for regular cornbread at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes, until cornbread sides pull away from pan.

title: heavenly dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch dish, break cake into small pieces.
Spread the pudding (prepared per directions plus 1 teaspoon of vanilla) over cake.
Whip the Cool Whip slightly and spread over cake and pudding mixture.
Sprinkle crushed chocolate over top and refrigerate until served.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Place stock, vegetables, seasonings and ham in a medium stock pot.
Simmer 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in butter.
Mix flour and some of the hot broth in a small bowl, stirring until smooth.
Return to the pot, stirring into the soup. Add milk.
Serves 4.

title: hot spinach dip
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small saucepan over medium heat, bring half and half to a simmer.
In another saucepan, melt butter and add flour to make a paste; cook 1 minute.
Add flour mixture to half and half.
Whisk constantly until thickened, 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove and add Tabasco, Parmesan, salt and pepper.
Cool to room temperature.
(At this point, the sauce can be refrigerated for 2 days.) Stir in spinach.
Can add more Tabasco, salt and pepper.
Spread in 9-inch pie pan or individual casserole dishes.
Top with cheeses.
Bake about 15 minutes.
Serve with chips with sour cream and salsa on the side.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well. Mix spinach, sour cream and onion soup mix.
Place in baking dish. Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gretchen's caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter in medium size saucepan.
Add brown sugar, salt and cream of tartar.
Stir until all is dissolved.
Keep the stove on medium heat and don't let it boil.
Pour the mixture on the popcorn while hot.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 200°, stirring occasionally.
Don't forget to share uncaramelized popcorn with your pot belly.

title: chocolate bottom stuff cake
directions: Swirl oil in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump in the cake mix, pudding mix, eggs and water.
Stir all with a fork.
Top with chocolate chips and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey loaf(makes 10 servings)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Divide into 2 (3-quart) casseroles or loaf pans (sprayed).
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Test for doneness by pricking center of loaf.
When juices run clear rather than pink, turkey is done.

title: creole barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Brush on any kind of beef, pork or poultry as it is barbecued.

title: super bowl chicken
directions: Mix Ricotta, Mozzarella and spinach together.
Either make pocket between skin and chicken and stuff or put mixture on bottom of pan and skinless chicken on top.
Brush chicken with olive oil. Sprinkle with garlic salt, basil and Romano cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 20 minutes longer.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: swiss mocha coffee
directions: Mix well.
Add 2 rounded teaspoonfuls to a cup of hot water.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla. Add cinnamon; mix well. Add flour; mix well. The mix will be thick. Add apples and walnuts; mix. Pour into pan and bake for 45 minutes. Cool. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight in a covered dish.

title: jiffy rhubarb dessert
directions: Grease oblong pan (about 7 x 10-inch or 12 x 9-inch).
Place raw rhubarb in pan.
Sprinkle with sugar, then strawberry Jell-O, then 2 cups cake mix.
Gently pour water over top and dribble melted margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; let boil until ready for beating.
While it boils, add some vanilla and a handful of nuts.
Beat until right consistency to set.
You can let it cool a bit before beating.
You can substitute brown sugar for the cocoa.

title: miracle pie
directions: Mix and pour in pan in which 1 stick butter had been melted. Pour fruit on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pork in oven
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix salt, black pepper and garlic.
Put seasonings over pork and them in 1 quart of water in an ovenproof receptacle.
Cover it with foil, leave it for 2 hours.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Add to milk.
Combine dry ingredients in a medium-sized bowl and cut in shortening.
Make a well in center of dry ingredients.
Add liquid mixture to dry mixture and work into a dough.
Knead for 10 minutes or until smooth.
Cover and set aside.
Heat oil in electric skillet to 420°.
Roll dough to 1/8-inch thickness, cut into 4-inch squares. Brown on both sides, turning once.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot with honey.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; reserve broth.
Boil spaghetti in broth.
Saute onions and peppers in oleo.
Drain off excess broth after spaghetti is done.
Add onions and peppers; add diced Velveeta cheese.
Mix well, then add Ro-Tel tomatoes and mix again.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Stir together sugar and cinnamon. Dip biscuits in butter and roll in sugar mixture.
Place on sheet and bake 7 minutes in 425° oven.
(Note:
Little ones love to do the dipping and rolling.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, Accent and onion.
Roll into 1 or 2 balls.
Roll in chipped, dried beef.
Chill.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Make your graham cracker crust with the top three ingredients and put on the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook until melted the milk and marshmallows.
Cool, then add strawberries and whipped topping.
Fold in and pour into the graham cracker crust.

title: spicy turkey roast(microwave)
directions: Lay turkey out as flat as possible on cutting board, skin side down.
Combine spices in a food processor and turn on.
Add oil, processing until coarsely chopped.
Spread half of garlic mixture on inside of turkey and re-roll.
Spread rest on outside of turkey and wrap firmly with micro-safe plastic film.
Poke holes in film with a fork in 3 places.
Microwave on High 10 minutes; turn roast over.
Microwave on Medium for 40 minutes, turning 2 or 3 times. Let stand 15 minutes before slicing.

title: bohemian pound cake
directions: Blend the first 3 ingredients until fluffy; add eggs one at a time on medium mixer speed.
Mix dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool.
Remove from pan.

title: mankato hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger and onion until browned.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 2 to 3-quart casserole.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: zucchini custard pie
directions: Cook zucchini. Blend or mash it. Blend all ingredients and pour in unbaked pie crust. Bake for 15 minutes at 400°, then at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Makes a 10-inch pie.

title: mullins oreo cookies
directions: Cookie Top/Bottom:
Mix together cake mix, shortening, eggs and 1 teaspoon of vanilla.
Roll mixture into 1-inch diameter balls and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 8 minutes at 325°. Do not overbake.

title: tuscan shrimp
directions: You will need bamboo skewers soaked in hot water for a few minutes.

title: donna's rhubarb cream cake
directions: Pour cake mix in a greased pan.
Then add the rest of the ingredients in order given.
It will all sink to the bottom, very good.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil water, bouillon cubes, potatoes, celery and onions for 20 minutes.
Add vegetables.
Boil 10 minutes.
Add soup and cheese. Cook on low heat until cheese melts.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs with sugar. Add sweet potatoes and mix well.
Mix in butter, shortening, salt and baking powder.
Add flour, 1/2 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Dough will be sticky.
Turn out on lightly floured board or waxed paper.
Flour hands and knead gently 3 or 4 times.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes or until brown.
Yields 20 to 24 biscuits.

title: chess pie
directions: Melt butter and set aside.
Add sugar, then milk to melted butter.
Add eggs, meal, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell. Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Check for firmness.

title: cherry flip
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot cherry juice.
Cool and add lemon juice. Pour 3 tablespoons of this mixture over ice cubes which have been placed in tall glass.
Fill with pale dry ginger ale.
Garnish with thin curl of lemon and fresh mint.

title: crunchy vegetable burrito banditos(makes 4 servings)
directions: Preparation Time: 15 minutes.

title: jim's kidney bean salad
directions: Chop pickles, eggs and onions in small pieces, add to Miracle Whip, then add beans, stir lightly.
Chill well and serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas and mix with egg, butter and sugar.
Add flour and walnuts.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: indian rice pudding
directions: Wash rice; add all the ingredients, except the eggs.
Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Add yolks and fold into the rice mixture.
Spoon into casserole dish.
Bake in slow 250° to 300° oven for 2 hours, stirring several times.

title: budget fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients for a red punch.
Use tropical punch and lemon Kool-Aid for a yellow punch.
You can add sherbet to either. Serves 35 to 40.

title: banana slush
directions: Boil sugar and water together and cool.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together and stir while freezing.
Add about 1 quart fresh peaches, if desired.
Mix sugar, water and juice together and stir about once every hour.

title: mac and cheese special
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Fry ground meat; when finished, drain off all grease.
Add ground meat and macaroni and cheese dinner together, then add red pepper; amount added is optional to how hot you want it.

title: impossible custard pie (diet)
directions: Blend all of the ingredients in blender.
Pour into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until done, basting frequently.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: mock zucchini crab cakes
directions: Combine
all
ingredients and mix well.
Fry in hot fat until brown on both sides.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake according to instructions on box.
(Better to use round cake pans.)
When cakes are thoroughly cooled, cut one of the cakes into 3 thin layers.
Prepare pudding according to instructions on box and let cool.
Prepare the whipping cream by placing the cream in a large bowl and with hand mixer, whip until you can form peaks.
While whipping the cream, add powdered sugar a teaspoon at a time to your taste.
In a large bowl (punch bowl works the best) start layering the ingredients in this order: cake, strawberries, pudding, whipping cream, cake, strawberries, etc. until all used.
Garnish with sliced almonds.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Cook chicken in 5 to 6 cups of water until tender; drain. Remove meat from bones and cube, discarding skin and bones. Crush tortilla chips and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add chicken.
Saute onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter. Blend in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour over chicken. Top with cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: that cake(cinnamon streusel coffee cake)
directions: Combine the sugar, cinnamon and chopped walnuts and set aside.
Mix together the eggs, oil, water, Dream Whip, pudding mix, cake mix, vanilla and butter extract and beat for 7 minutes. Place half of this mixture in a well greased and floured angel cake pan.
Top with half of the streusel mixture.
Add remaining batter and top with remaining streusel mixture.
Marble slightly with a knife.
Bake in a 350° oven for 50-60 minutes or until done.
Cool in the pan for about 15 minutes.
Run knife around sides to loosen and slide cake gently from pan onto plate. Immediately turn upside down onto another plate to sit it in an upright position.
Mix together the confectioners sugar, vanilla, milk and butter flavoring and drizzle over the cake.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate with 1 cup pecans sprinkled over top.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into two 9-inch slightly greased pie pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken surprise(meat dish)
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Layer Swiss cheese over chicken.
Mix soup and milk and pour over chicken and cheese. Sprinkle stuffing over other ingredients.
Cover dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Beat the cream cheese and powdered sugar together.
Add whipped whipping cream.
Pour into graham cracker or baked pie crusts.
Cover with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake at 350° in preheated oven until done. Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Add sugar, salt and milk; bring to a boil.
Let boil for 9 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat. Add marshmallow cream; stir until melted.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla; stir until melted.
Stir in nuts.
Line a large cookie sheet with foil.
Let cool completely.
Cut into desired size squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: monte cristo sandwiches
directions: Heat oil to 375°.
Assemble sandwiches:
1 slice bread, ham, cheese, bread, turkey and bread.
Secure with toothpicks.

title: tropical punch
directions: Combine punch, lemonade, orange juice, grape and water.
Pour over ice in large punch bowl.
Add ginger ale gradually and stir; float small scoops of sherbet on top.
Makes 30 (5 ounce) servings.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Place crushed Oreos in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the chocolate and vanilla puddings with milk.
Mix in the softened ice cream.
Pour on top of cookie crumbs; freeze.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mash bananas, then fold in along with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes one loaf of wonderful banana bread.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Scald cabbage leaves until limp.
Cool.
Combine first three ingredients.
Dice green pepper and onion, then saute in butter. Cool.
Add to ground beef mixture.

title: glorious morning muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Stir in carrots, raisins, coconut and apples.
Beat eggs with oil and vanilla.
Stir mixture into flour mixture until batter is just combined.
Spoon batter into 1/3 cup muffin tins, filling to top.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool for 5 minutes, then place on rack and let cool completely.
Yields 30.

title: fish dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, salad dressing, sour cream and mustard.
Add flaked fish and chill overnight.
Serve with crackers, chips or raw vegetables.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Heat milk and butter on medium heat until melted.
Add sugar and boil on medium heat for 7 minutes or until soft ball forms. Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream and mix well.
Add peanut butter.
Beat with mixer.
Pour in 13 x 9-inch pan and let cool.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Blend the sugar, milk and syrup and boil to soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add the cocoa, dissolved in the boiling water.
Add the butter and cocoa.
Cook.
Add the 1/8 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Beat until mixture is a creamy consistency.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: gazpacho
directions: Dice half the tomatoes (if not already diced), not losing any of the juice, cucumber, half the onion and half the green pepper. Set aside in a large bowl or pitcher with half the green chiles. Put the remaining tomatoes, cucumber, green pepper, chiles and onion into a blender, along with the garlic, olive oil, vinegar, tomato juice and salt.
Blend for a few seconds.
Pour into the container with the chopped veggies.
Mix well.
Cover and chill thoroughly.

title: lolani rainy day clam chowder
directions: Pour a glass of wine.
Wash and cube potatoes.	Dice onion. Drain clams and reserve juice.
Rinse clams.
Watch the rain spatter on the portholes - pour some more wine.
In a 6 qt. pot, brown bacon - Remove and crumble.
Drain grease and brown onion in pot.
Separately heat fish stock or water and bouillon and reserved clam juice, then add to pot.
Add potatoes, pepper and thyme. Simmer 1 hour, or until potatoes are cooked.
Have another glass of wine.
Check if the rain has stopped.
Add clams and condensed milk.
Simmer 10 - 15 more minutes or until clams are cooked. Serve with bread and wine - if there is any left!

title: fresh pico de gallo
directions: Dice everything and mix. Serve with tortilla chips or use to garnish Mexican dishes.

title: seafood cracker dip
directions: In a blender, combine low-fat cottage cheese, cream cheese spread, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Remove from blender and mix in seafood; cover and chill.
Serve with non-fat saltine crackers. Yields 2 1/2 cups (ten 1/4-cup servings).

title: rivel soup
directions: Put sliced potatoes into the broth and bring to a boil.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Combine the flour, salt and beaten egg and mix together with the fingers until mixture is crumbly.
Pour this mixture into the boiling broth and cook about 10 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 1 hour.

title: 5 minute fudge (peppermint)
directions: Heat to boiling the Carnation milk, sugar and margarine.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add marshmallows, chocolate chips and peppermint oil.
Stir until marshmallows and chips are melted and pour into pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: miss sontag's tuna dip
directions: Mix gelatin in water and let stand for 5 minutes.
Warm it a little before mixing with other ingredients and it mixes easier. Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole type dish. Cover!
Refrigerate.
Tastes better if mixed the day before. Makes good sandwiches!
Also tastes good on saltines, snack crackers or chips.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in medium saucepan.
Bring to boil; stir constantly.
Add carrots.
Return to boil; reduce heat to low.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream all ingredients but flour.
Blend with flour a little at a time.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press crisscross with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 dozen.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and beat until fluffy.
Stir in milk and flour.
Drop on cookie sheet. Bake 6 to 8 minutes on 375°.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: super caruso nachos
directions: Combine refried beans, taco seasoning and Monterey Jack cheese.
Spread in a 9 1/2 x 11-inch baking pan.
Brown beef.
Add onion, cumin and salt.
Layer on top of refried beans.
Sprinkle with chilies.
Add shredded Cheddar cheese.
Top with salsa.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Top with sour cream and serve with nacho chips and enjoy.

title: 22-minute cake
directions: Bring the water, shortenings and coca to a boil in a small saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Combine the sugar and flour in a large bowl.
Pour the melted shortening mixture over the flour and sugar, combining well.
Combine the buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla and add to other mixtures.
Blend.
Pour into a 12x18 inch greased loaf pan and bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes or until done.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Add to chopped ingredients.

title: spaghetti
directions: Buy pork chops at the store.
Chop it into little pieces. Cook tuna fish together with the pork chops.
Put it in the oven. Cook it for 20 minutes at 60°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil until thickens the first 4 ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients.

title: goose
directions: Take a 9 x 11-inch pan, spray or grease; layer the 3 goose breasts that have been cut thin horizontally, sliced spuds, sliced onions and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with bacon; put sliced orange over top.
Pour barbecue sauce over the whole thing.
Seal pan tightly with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: six dollar chocolate peanuts
directions: Melt the chocolate bark in a double boiler.
Add peanuts.
Mix well and dip by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter in heavy 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Stir in sugar, salt, cocoa and milk.
Bring to boil and boil exactly 2 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and then oats.
Mix thoroughly and drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.
Cool and then chill.
Store airtight.

title: cherry nut squares
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add vanilla.
Mix in eggs, one at a time.
Stir
in
flour, then nuts.	Mix well.
Spread 3/4 of the batter
in	the
bottom
of
an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with filling.
Drop remaining batter by teaspoonfuls and spread with a spatula.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar before serving.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Combine syrup and sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to full boil. Remove immediately from heat.
Mix in peanut butter and cereal. Press into a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in top of double boiler.
Spread over cereal mixture as icing.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: apricot jello salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to a boil.
Stir in apricot jello. Add cream cheese, water and nuts.
Chill for 1 1/2 hours.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
Roll into a ball and place on a plate. Sprinkle with some chopped pecans and place cherry on top.
Cool in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together. Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pour margarine into cup, leaving some in pan.
In large bowl, mix peaches, vanilla, sugar and melted butter. Pour first mixture into oblong pan. Pour peach mixture on top of this and bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: green chili
directions: Dice onion, jalapeno peppers, stewed tomatoes and Anaheim pepper.
Put in crock-pot with all juices.
Dice roast; cut most of fat off.
Brown roast in skillet.
When browned, add some flour to absorb grease.
Put in crock-pot.

Add water to almost fill crock. After cooking 6 to 8 hours, if it's not thick, then make a thin flour paste with flour and water and add slowly while stirring. Wait about an hour; if still not thick enough, add more flour and water mixture.
The more you heat this up the hotter it gets.

title: roast chicken oriental style
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces; arrange on a platter. Layer chicken over lettuce.
Slice green onions lengthwise into 2-inch strips.
Arrange around edge of lettuce.

Place spring roll wrappers in a vegetable steamer rack over boiling water; steam 3 to 5 minutes or until hot or wrap spring roll wrappers in a damp dish towel and steam 1 to 2 minutes in the microwave.
Remove to a napkin lined basket.

title: pumpkin muffins(egg free)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Prepare pans for 24 cupcakes.
Mix first 5 ingredients in a small bowl.
In a large bowl, mix sugar and pumpkin; add oil and mix again.
Add flour mixture to large bowl, beating as needed.
(Add in 3 pans.)
Pour batter into pans. Bake for 25 to 35 minutes or until done.
Test with a toothpick.

title: ham delights
directions: Use blender to chop ham, then add chopped onion and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Cut rolls in half and spread with mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake 10 minutes at 400 degrees to warm rolls and melt the cheese.

title: refrigerated rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar, salt and Crisco.
Stir until Crisco is dissolved and cool mixture to lukewarm.
Add yeast which has been dissolved in lukewarm water.
Add egg; mix well.
Stir in flour to make a soft dough.
Place in refrigerator.
Use as needed.
Form into rolls and let rise.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna patties
directions: Combine all ingredients; drop by large tablespoon out onto a thin layer of meal in plate.
Sprinkle top; take fork and mash out thin and flat.
Fry in hot oil just enough to cover bottom of skillet.
When that side is brown, turn over and brown other side, 2 1/2 minutes at most on each side.
Delicious with beans.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter. Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter. Sprinkle with coconut, chocolate chips and walnuts. Pour milk over top. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until top browns lightly. Let cool completely and cut in squares.

title: walking salad(method:  fireless)
directions: Cut the tops of the apples and core them, being careful not to break through the bottom (like preparing a pumpkin).
Fill the cavity with the mixture of raisins, carrots and celery.
Put the tops back on.
Wrap in aluminum foil.

title: deep, dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Put cut up rhubarb into the bottom of a greased 10 x 6-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle the 1 cup sugar over and dot with butter. In a mixing bowl, beat together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and eggs.
Pour over the sugared rhubarb.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Combine
cake mix, whipped topping, egg, and lemon rind. Mix well.
Drop
by
teaspoonfuls
on
sugar.
Place 1 1/2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from sheet immediately.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and let rise for 15 minutes. Make into rolls; let rise 15 minutes.
Bake for about 15 minutes.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; cool slightly.
Add mayo and crumbled corned beef.
Add vegetables and mix well.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch square and refrigerate several hours.
Serves 12 (or more).

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients together in medium mixing bowl, except walnuts.
Chill for several hours.
Form mixture into ball and then roll in the walnuts until completely covered.
Serve with crackers.

title: frozen mint dessert
directions: With just three ingredients, you can whip up a frozen mint dessert to brighten summer menus.
First place contents of a 10-ounce jar (about 1 cup) mint jelly in a small bowl and beat until smooth.

title: turkey meat loaf(heart healthy)
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, until done.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion and oleo.
Add cheese and soup.
Bring to a boil. Add rice and broccoli.
Put into casserole dish and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli and ham quiche
directions: *I use ham that comes in 5 ounce tuna size cans.

title: sunset soda
directions: Dissolve soft drink mix and sugar in water. Stir in soda. Place a small scoop of ice cream in each of 6 tall glasses. Stir in soda mixture; top with a second scoop of ice cream.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.
Cut in bars. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: squash and onions
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender; drain well.
Mash with fork or potato masher.
Add salt, pepper, butter and light cream or milk.
Let simmer on low heat for 15 minutes.

title: granola
directions: Melt margarine with pure maple syrup or honey.
Cook in flat pan at 350° for 25 minutes, turning every 5 minutes until golden brown.
Add dried fruit after and put back in oven until it dries out.
Store in airtight containers.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix milk and eggs together.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 cup batter in funnel.
Swirl around in deep fat fryer.
Brown.
Top with powdered sugar.
Yields 8 to 10 funnel cakes.

title: pecan pie
directions: In mixing bowl slightly beat eggs.
Stir in corn syrup, brown sugar, butter or margarine and salt.
Add pecan halves and vanilla to mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° until center is set when gently shaken, about 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.

title: buckeyes
directions: Soften butter and peanut butter.
Mix together.
Add powdered sugar.
Shape into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Freeze for 1 hour.

title: anthony's strawberry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix or beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk. Stir in lemon juice, strawberry extract and Jell-O.
Pour into a prepared crust.
Chill for 3 hours.
Top with chopped fresh or frozen strawberries.
Refrigerate.

title: shirley's stromboli
directions: Thaw
bread
dough;
spread
on a cookie sheet.
Spread pizza sauce,
ham, pepperoni, salami and Mozzarella cheese on top. Freeze
for
15 minutes, then roll up tightly and secure with toothpicks.
Beat
egg
and spread on top; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soups, broth and vegetables together in a large bowl.
Pour over chicken.

title: cardamom bread(one and one-half pound loaf for bread machine)
directions: Set machine to "dough-mix" setting.
Place ingredients in machine.
When finished, let dough rest for 10 minutes on a floured surface.
Divide the dough into 3 parts.
Braid the 3 sections.
Pinch the ends together and place on a greased sheet pan.
Smooth over the top with fingertips dipped in milk. Sprinkle with poppy seed and sugar.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; add a little of the milk to egg yolks, then mix the dry ingredients in.
Add to scalded milk; stir until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla. Stir.

title: easy bake coconut pie
directions: Mix all together; pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: fresh vegetable salad
directions: Marinate vegetables at least 4 hours in liquid and spice combination. Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh peach butter
directions: Puree peaches in food processor or blender. In a 6 to 8-quart saucepan, heat lemon juice for 1 minute over medium-high heat. Add pureed peaches and sugar. Bring to boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling, stirring constantly, until mixture is the consistency of thick applesauce, about 15 minutes. Immediately fill hot, sterilized half-pint jars leaving 1/4 inch headspace. Place hot lids on jars and screw bands on firmly. Process in boiling water canner for 5 minutes. Yields about 6 half pints.

title: hash brown baked potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except corn flakes and melted butter, and pour into a casserole dish.
Top with corn flakes, mixed with the melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chop supper
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish with potatoes and carrots.
Cover with the mushroom soup.
Layer onion over mixture. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Brown pork chops; place on top of mixture.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Place foil over top of dish.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Make Minute rice according to directions on box, also to how many servings you would like to make.
Take the chicken breasts and cut off bone into chunks.
Place in egg and milk batter. Roll in flour and deep fry.
Set aside.

title: hamburger wellington
directions: Brown beef with onion; cool and add bread pieces and ketchup. Roll dinner rolls into squares (use two rolls for each).
Use 3/4 cup of beef mixture for each square.
Top with Mozzarella; spread egg over rolls.
Bake according to roll directions.

title: mamaw campbell's shortcake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Will be sticky.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 350° until brown on large cookie sheet for 20 minutes.

title: popcorn salad
directions: If made ahead, combine all except the cheese and popcorn.
Add just before serving.

title: italian style cheese chowder
directions: Saute onions in butter in 4-quart saucepan until softened. Add zucchini, garbanzo beans, tomatoes, wine, salt and pepper, garlic, basil and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer gently 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cheese and cream.
Simmer on low until cheese melts and chowder is heated through, stirring occasionally.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except grated cheese.
Pour half of batter into greased and heated 10-inch skillet.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Add remaining batter.
Sprinkle with rest of grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add onion flakes, green pepper and celery.
Cook until celery is tender.
Blend cornstarch and tomato juice in separate bowl.
Mix sugar and seasoning with tomatoes and add to celery mixture.
Add cornstarch mixture and cook and stir five minutes or until clear and slightly thickened. Add shrimp to hot creole sauce and simmer gently about 10 minutes or until shrimp is pink and tender.
Serve with hot fluffy rice. Makes 6 servings.

title: hacienda casserole
directions: In glass casserole, brown onion, ground beef and sausage 4 to 6 minutes.
Remove excess drippings.
Add corn, soup, tomato paste, chili, salt and pepper.
Stir to blend.
In 10-inch skillet, layer half the meat mixture, half the noodles and 1 cup cheese; repeat with remaining ingredients.
Cook 10 to 12 minutes, rotating.

title: roasted corn salsa
directions: Remove corn from cob.
Place skillet over high heat until hot. Add corn, stirring frequently, until crisp tender.
Cool.
Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with chips.

title: hamburger-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Prepare rice according to box directions. Brown meat gently, season to taste.
Mix all ingredients in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: rice and green chilies casserole
directions: Cook rice until just tender.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Mix chilies with sour cream.
Cut cheese into strips.
Butter casserole and alternate layers of well-seasoned rice, sour cream with chilies and cheese.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Top layer should be sour cream.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir in carrots, raisins, nuts, coconut and apple.
In separate bowl, blend oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix with flour mixture just until combined.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 15 muffins.
Unbaked batter may be stored in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix and pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chess bars
directions: Melt butter.
Mix all together.
Put in bottom of baking dish and press down.

title: baked haddock fillets
directions: Thinly slice onion, green pepper and carrot.
Place fish in a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and a dash of paprika.
Place vegetables on top of fish.
Add undiluted cream of onion soup and bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Make a roux, medium brown, of the first two ingredients.
Keep stirring until brown, 20 minutes.

title: party wheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; spread on tortillas, then sprinkle the remaining ingredients on top.
Roll up and wrap tightly with clear plastic wrap; chill for about 2 to 3 hours.
Cut off roll ends and slice rolls into 1-inch pieces.

title: spanish stew
directions: Cut all vegetables into large pieces.
Put beef to boil with onion and garlic for about 2 hours.
When beef is tender, add vegetables until cooked, not too soft.
Should be a little hard. Add salt to taste and serve.

title: easy donuts
directions: Using donut cutter, cut hole out of biscuit.
Fry in deep fat fryer until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Mix powdered sugar and water to desired consistency.
Dip donuts in icing.
Makes 10 donuts and 10 holes.

title: boiled chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Immediately drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
Let cool and harden.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients with spoon.
Drain all liquids from fruit and add.
Add cherries, small marshmallows, raisins and pecans.
Fold all together.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: In mixing bowl, cream shortening and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Combine 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk.
Spread into a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Toss blueberries with lemon juice; sprinkle over batter.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine salt, flour, baking powder and soda.
In another bowl, combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat until frothy.
Add bananas and blend thoroughly.
Fold into flour mixture until blended.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour until browned. Let cool 10 minutes.
Can be doubled and made in soup cans, coffee cans and mini loaf pans.

title: shrimp sauce #2
directions: Mix all ingredients well ahead of time.
Place in refrigerator to chill before serving.

title: guacamole del norte
directions: Whirl all in blender.
Put in dish with avocado pit in center. This keeps guacamole from turning dark.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well in bowl.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 12-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: sour cream apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, sugar and oleo.
Stir in nuts.
Mix until crumbly.
Press 2 3/4 cups of this crumbly mixture into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
To remaining mixture, add cinnamon, soda, salt, sour cream, vanilla and egg.
Blend well. Stir in apples; spoon evenly over base.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.
Cut into squares.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl and let stand.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, in serving bowl.
Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Add pineapple, bananas, peaches and cold water to jello.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Add soup, milk, wine, butter or margarine, tarragon and pepper.
Heat through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, butter and salt.
Bring to a boil over low heat.
Pour hot syrup slowly over beaten eggs.
Cool; add vanilla and pecans and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 375° and bake 35 to 40 minutes longer.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Butter casserole. Line bottom with crackers, then layer of cabbage, chunks of butter and salt and pepper. Sprinkle a little flour on top. Repeat in layers until casserole is filled. The last layer should be crackers and chunks of butter. Pour milk to just below this layer. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. The casserole should be thick.

title: copper pennies
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
This will keep, refrigerated, for 4 weeks.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together well.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: bloody duck
directions: Come in from duck hunt.
Insert a stick of butter inside a freshly cleaned Mallard duck.
Throw in hot coals of a fire for 7 minutes, covering duck entirely.
Remove duck from coals and use very sharp knife to cut paper-thin slices.
Serve on crackers.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook pie crust and then cool.
Mash strawberries to measure 1 cup.
Stir sugar and cornstarch together, then gradually stir in water and berries.
Cook mixture over a medium heat.
Stir constantly until it thickens and boils.
Let boil for 1 minute. Add a few drops of coloring.
Then beat cream cheese until smooth.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef and oyster sauce
directions: Cut beef into 2-inch wide strips along grain, then slice across the grain into thin strips.
Mix in 1 tablespoon wine, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, 1 tablespoon cornstarch and 1 tablespoon water.
Add 1 tablespoon oil to meat mixture before frying.
(This separates the beef during the stir-fry process.)
Heat 1 1/2 tablespoons oil and stir-fry beef until medium well; remove. Using remaining oil in pan to stir-fry green onions, ginger root and asparagus until fragrant.
Mix remaining soy sauce, oyster sauce, wine, sugar and cornstarch.
Add to pan.
Add beef back to pan and mix well.
Cover and cook until steamy, then stir-fry to mix.
Remove; sprinkle with sesame seed.
Serves 2.

title: stover fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk; bring to a boil and cook 6 minutes then mix with chocolate chips.
Add marshmallow cream, pecans and Hershey bars.
Pour on greased sheet and cool.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. When cake is done, punch holes in it.
Pour sauce over it while warm.
Let it set overnight and let sauce soak in.
Add Cool Whip to top of cake and sprinkle generously with coconut.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and melted margarine.
Add eggs and mix well. Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn oven down to 350° and bake
about 30 minutes longer or until done.

title: auntie claire's banana bread
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs together.
Combine dry ingredients.
Blend both mixtures, beating until well mixed.
Add bananas, sour cream, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured medium loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco; add sugar and egg yolks.
Add flour and soda to creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Add nuts, coconut, vanilla and egg whites.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Steam onions until transparent.
Brown hamburger in garlic. Add onions.
Use potato masher and mash until broken and very fine.
Add chili, paprika and salt; work all of the lumps out with a potato masher.
Add liquid and simmer for 2 hours.
You can freeze.

title: butterhorns
directions: Soften the yeast in warm water.
Combine hot milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup flour.
Add yeast mixture and eggs, beating well.
Stir in remaining flour or enough to make soft dough.
Turn out on floured surface and knead lightly, 5 to 8 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise until double.

title: pound cake
directions: Measure and sift 3 cups cake flour.
Add 1 cup at a time. When well mixed, add 5 eggs at a time until well mixed.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 300° to 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix together in bowl the baking powder, sugar, flour, milk and salt.
Pour this batter over butter. Add drained peaches.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: no sugar orange cookies
directions: Beat together first 4 ingredients.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes (until lightly brown).
Store in tightly closed container. Makes about 2 dozen.
Enjoy.

title: cranberry-apple crunch
directions: Combine cranberries, apples and sugar in a lightly greased shallow 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine brown sugar and flour.
Cut in butter with pastry blender.
Stir in oats and pecans.
Sprinkle mixture over cranberries and apples.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, until golden brown.

title: never fail banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening.
Slowly add the sugar; beat well.
Add the eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add bananas and nuts.
Alternately add dry ingredients with milk.
Bake in two greased loaf pans at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Heat oil in 3-quart heatproof casserole on top of stove.
Add green pepper and onion; cook until tender.
Salt and pepper beef; brown in casserole, breaking up with fork.
Add tomatoes, beans and chili powder; let simmer.

title: famous nameless cookies
directions: Stir together dry cake mix, dry pudding powder and flour. Using your hands work in the mayonnaise until dough is smooth and a little stiff.
Work in pecans and chocolate chips.
Shape dough by rounded tsp. into marshmallow shapes.
Arrange them 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake on center rack at 350° for 16 minutes or until delicately browned.
Do not overbake!
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Heat milk, shortening and sugar to boiling point, but do not boil.
Cool, then add salt, soda and baking powder.
Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons warm water and add to first mixture.
Add 7 cups sifted flour, a cup or 2 at a time.
Drop by spoonfuls into bowl or crock and set in refrigerator.
Make out rolls (as much as needed) 1 or 1 1/2 hours before time to bake.
Bake about 12 to 15 minutes at 400° to 425°.

title: creamed crab soup - chesapeake bay
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour and add milk, salt, black and red pepper.
When heated, add crabmeat and cream.
Heat and mix thoroughly.
Add chopped eggs and sherry to taste.
Garnish with sprigs of parsley.
Serve in cups.

title: kiss cookies
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter and sugars. Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix thoroughly, then shape into balls. Roll balls in sugar. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Place the Kisses on the cookies and press down.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream together butter, margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and water, mixing well.
Add coconut, raisins and nuts.
Stir until blended.
Mix in vanilla wafer crumbs.
Pour into a tube cake pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate fudge nut cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Melt butter; add water and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Pour mixture into bowl with sugar and flour mixture. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Makes a thin batter.
Pour into greased 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix and serve with fresh vegetables.

title: canned green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes as thin as you would to fry.
Pack in jar.
Pour cold water over them and add 1 teaspoon salt to each quart.
Seal and cook about 3 to 5 minutes after they start to boil.
They stay just like you put them in the jar.
Real good to fry with okra or by themselves.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple well.
Add nuts and Cool Whip. Chill until ready to serve.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together crushed pretzels, melted butter and sugar. Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool.

title: chops in sour cream
directions: Rub chops with mixture of sage, salt and pepper.
Brown in shortening.
Drain excess fat.
Add onion.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water; pour over chops.
Cover skillet; simmer for 25 to 30 minutes, until meat is done.
Remove meat to a hot platter. Combine sour cream and flour in a bowl.
Slowly stir drippings into mixture until well mixed.
Return gravy to skillet and boil. Add water to thin gravy to desired consistency.
Pour over chops. Sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: far east chicken salad(first place winner 1989)
directions: Core, rinse and thoroughly drain lettuce.
Shred lettuce in large bowl.
Add celery, carrot, green onion, green pepper, bean sprouts, chicken; toss well.
Sprinkle on top with mein noodles and sesame seeds.
Add ginger-soy dressing and serve.

title: peach cobbler(no added sugar)
directions: Combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons apple juice, mixing well; set aside.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until tender; cut in small pieces.

title: potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes into bite sized pieces and boil in a saucepan until tender.
Add cut up carrots and ham.
Simmer for 15 minutes. Add cheese, butter and milk.
Simmer for 15 more minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with crackers or cornbread.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Combine sugar and sour cream, stirring until smooth.
Add cranberry sauce and pineapple; stir until smooth.
Pour into muffin tins lined with paper baking cups.
Freeze.
