When frozen, remove from tins and store in plastic bag.
To serve, peel off paper.

title: calcutta chicken salad
directions: Stir together all ingredients, except apple and banana, gently smoothing out top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, add apple and banana and mix gently.
Serve on lettuce lined plate.
Garnish with any or all of the following:
sliced cantaloupe, candied ginger, fresh grapes, toasted coconut slices.

title: chicken curry(native american style)
directions: Fry onions in butter.
Add spices, salt and tomato sauce.
Add chicken (with skin removed) and cook for 40 minutes, turning every 10 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups water and cook 10 to 12 minutes longer.
Add pepper and cool for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice or slices of bread.

title: miracle pie
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice; stir until blended.
Fold in whipped topping and fruit cocktail.
Spoon into 2 graham cracker crusts and refrigerate several hours.
Garnish with mandarin orange sections.
Yield: two 9-inch pies.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water and pineapple juice. Stir in pie filling.
Chill until set in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Combine pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over jello mixture. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Place noodles in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with water and sprinkle with salt.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Remove and let noodles stand in water while preparing sauce.
Crumble ground beef in 3-quart glass casserole.
Add onion.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, uncovered; stir well. Microwave 3 minutes longer.
Drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce. Alternate layers of noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish, ending with noodles and sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover loosely with waxed paper. Microwave on High for 8 minutes; turn dish and microwave for 7 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: jello gelatin dessert
directions: Go by directions on gelatin box.
Add cottage cheese and fruit cocktail.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan or ring mold.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins. Cool, peel and shred coarsely.
In saucepan, over low heat, combine cheese and margarine.
Stir occasionally until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream and scallions.
Fold mixture into shredded potatoes. Add salt and pepper.
Turn into a greased 2-quart casserole. Dot with butter pats and sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
(Can be frozen before baked.)

title: eagle bars
directions: Melt margarine in oblong pan.
Pour on graham crackers, chocolate chips, caramel chips, crushed nuts and shredded coconut. Over all pour Eagle Brand milk.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
Cut into bars.

title: tuna turnover
directions: Open tuna and drane.
Mix tuna, onyon, sweet relish and mirichal wip in a bowl.
Brown bred in skilit and then malt cheese on bred slihgres (slices).
Tuna on bred.
Fold or make sadwqige (sandwich).

title: pistachio cake
directions: Beat 3 minutes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in Bundt pan, greased and floured. Refrigerate 1 hour before frosting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place first four ingredients in casserole in the order given. Mix remaining items well and pour over other ingredients.
Bake until bubbly and slightly brown at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Preparation time:
20 to 30 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: taco salad
directions: Mix beans and taco mix together and spread over bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix avocado dips and sour cream mix together and spread over beans.
Mix onions, green chilies and olives.
Spread over avocado layer.
Cover that layer with tomatoes.
Spread lettuce over tomatoes.
Cover lettuce with grated cheese.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Bring to a full rolling boil and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add while hot the oatmeal, cocoa and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add coconut, nuts or whatever you have. Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: pizza bundles
directions: Let dough thaw and rise.
Brown beef and onion; add remaining ingredients, except cornmeal.
Tear off small pieces of bread dough; roll out on board sprinkled with cornmeal.
Place filling in center of each dough circle.
Bring edges of dough together over center of filling.
Twist dough as if closing a sack, to seal.
Place twist side down on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 375° until bundles are golden brown.

title: corn souffle
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mixture.
Bake in greased casserole 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: virginia cornbread(shared by mary crump)
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and shortening.
Add egg and beat.
Spoon into greased iron skillet or iron muffin rings, that is preheated.
Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: aztec pie
directions: Saute onion in oil in 9 or 10-inch cast-iron skillet 5 minutes. Add garlic, cook 1 minute more, transfer to small bowl.
Cook ground beef in skillet until browned, about 8 minutes.
Return onion and garlic to skillet.
Stir in chili powder, sugar, cumin, oregano, salt, pepper and cinnamon.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes more, stirring to blend flavors.
Stir in undrained tomatoes and chilies, break up tomatoes, simmer for 10 minutes.
Transfer mixture to bowl and reserve.

title: graham squares
directions: Mix crumbs and milk; add remaining ingredients.
Spread into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cool and drain carrots.
Mix heated ingredients and pour over carrots, onion and pepper.
Let stand at least 12 hours before serving.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix eggs, shortening and sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: southern style red beans and rice
directions: Combine ingredients together in a large pot or slow cooker for about 2 hours or until ready. Serve to your taste.
Serve with rice.

title: afternoon delite
directions: Mix and pour this over crust.
Mix 2 small packages instant vanilla pie filling; prepare as directed.
Let set up and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip, coconut and 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.
(You may use chocolate or lemon pudding.)

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put everything in a pot.
Sammy said sometimes when his mom makes chicken and dumplings, she puts in a little bit of carrots and a few tomatoes.
Cook for 10 hours or 11 minutes.

title: chicken cacciataco
directions: Sprinkle season-all over chicken. Brown on all sides in hot oil. Drain. Combine seasoning mix, water and tomatoes, breaking up tomatoes. Pour over chicken. Cover and simmer 40 minutes. Serve over cooked pasta. Serves 4.

title: janet's rum balls
directions: Crush vanilla wafers, grind pecans and melt margarine.
Combine all ingredients using only 3/4 box of confectioners sugar.
Mix well.
Form small balls and coat in remaining confectioners sugar.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: In a 2-quart casserole, microwave 1 pound crumbled ground beef 5 to 6 minutes at High until no longer pink.
Drain off excess fat.

title: mama's chocolate pie
directions: Cream 1 cup
sugar,
egg
yolks,
flour
and salt.
Add cocoa, then add milk.
Stir until smooth and cook until thick. Cool and pour into
cooked pie shell.
Beat egg whites;
add 3 tablespoons sugar, one at
a
time,
being
sure
all are well dissolved. Spread over pie and brown.

title: boiled white frosting
directions: Frost a 13 x 9-inch cake.
Mix in saucepan first 3 ingredients and boil (cover first few minutes so crystals form).
Boil until 6 to 8-inch thread or 242°.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff.
Pour syrup into egg whites and beat.
Add vanilla.
Spread.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Put shortening or butter in sifted dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until when lightly touched bounces back.
Cool 1 hour on rack.

title: flan - caramel custard
directions: In small frying pan over moderate heat melt the 1/3 cup sugar, shaking pan instead of stirring.
Sugar will caramelize quickly. Immediately
pour
into individual metal cups.
Just enough to cover
the bottoms.
Beat eggs with 6 tablespoons of sugar; add milk and
vanilla.	Set
metal
cups
in pan of hot water.	Pour in	egg
mixture.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes. Small crevice may appear when done.
Remove from hot water and chill at once. To serve, invert on small plates.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs and beat well. Add soda and salt, mixing well. Add mashed bananas alternately with flour, mixing well until it is well blended. Bake at 340° to 375° for 1 hour.
Small pans will have a shorter baking time.

title: blueberry or peach pudding
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add skim milk and mix until batter is smooth.
Melt margarine in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Pour blueberries into casserole.	Gently pour batter over
blueberries.
Bake
at
for
40	to 45 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with Doritos.
Sprinkle with 4 tablespoons chicken broth.
Combine soups, green pepper, onion, tomatoes, green chilies and chicken.
Stir well.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix thoroughly Eagle Brand, Cool Whip and pink lemonade.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate for 3 to 5 hours.
Enjoy!

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and place in salad bowl.

title: beef and shell bake
directions: Prepare shells according to package directions.
Drain.
Cook ground beef, celery and onions until beef is browned.
Drain excess fat.
Add tomatoes (with juice; break up with spoon), tomato paste and spices.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine with shells and pour into a 3-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Place oleo, cocoa and water in pan and dissolve.
Cool mixture.
Mix in mixing bowl sugar, flour, soda, eggs and milk. Add melted mixture and vanilla.
Grease and flour cookie sheet pan.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: cherry date nut cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into 1 large or two small balls. Roll in finely chopped pecans.
Make at least 1 to 2 days ahead of serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Put strawberries into jello.
Pull apart with fork.
Do not mash berries.
Put bananas and drained pineapple into jello mixture.
Put half of this into a long casserole dish.
Chill until firm.
Put sour cream over this, then spoon remaining jello mixture over sour cream.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares and serve over lettuce leaves.

title: anne's chicken casserole
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Add salt and cook until tender. Remove and cube.
Add broccoli to chicken broth; cook, covered about 10 minutes.
Drain broccoli well and add to mayonnaise, cheese, eggs, celery soup, and minced onion; mix well.
Add chicken cubes, stir.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Cover with buttered, finely crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Combine apples, sugar, flour and 2 tablespoons water; bring to a boil.
Place boiling mixture in the bottom of an 8-inch baking dish.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with thawed pie shell and bake at 425° for about 1/2 hour or until crust is golden brown.

title: golden egg bake
directions: Remove egg yolks.
Mash and combine with mayonnaise, onion, mustard, vinegar and salt.
Refill egg whites.
Arrange stuffed eggs in greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Combine soup, milk and curry powder; beat thoroughly.
Cover eggs with the sauce.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve on toast. Serves 4.

title: taco ring
directions: Lay out rolls (ends out) around a circle pizza pan.
Mix meat with taco seasoning, water, and cheese.
Drop by spoonful onto the center of each roll, fold the roll over.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20-25 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix chopped apples, raisins, nuts and cinnamon together.
(If apples are very tart, add a little extra sugar.)
Mix other ingredients and add apple mixture.
Grease and flour 8 x 12 1/2 inch pan.
Cook at 325° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: grape-nut bread
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and let stand 1 hour.
Beat and add the nuts, egg and salt.
Add sugar to mixture.
Add flour with baking powder.
Mix well.
Put in 2 greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Arrange cucumbers and onions which have been sliced medium thick, in layers.
Sprinkle salt between each layer.
Allow to stand 3 or 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Drain; combine remaining ingredients.
Bring slowly to boiling.
Add drained onions and cucumbers and cook for 5 minutes.
Pack in hot pint jars.
Yields 10 pints.

title: almond chicken with vegetables
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add chicken.
Mix. Refrigerate 15 minutes.
Pour 1/4 cup of oil into preheated wok for 1 minute.
Add chicken.
Stir-fry 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: connecticut cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add brown sugar, sugar and butter to mixture; stir until butter melts. Add eggs, mixing well.
Sift together the flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa and add to mixture.
Add 1/2 package chocolate chips. Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle walnuts and 1/2 package chocolate chips over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: boursin cheese
directions: Pack into a container.
Better if made the night before. Serve with crackers.

title: asparagus milanese
directions: Cook asparagus in small amount of salted water, about 15 minutes.
Arrange asparagus in a buttered baking dish.
Cover with eggs and seasoning.
Sprinkle with cheese and place under broiler until eggs are done and cheese a golden brown.

title: parmesan potato wedges
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Do not peel potatoes.
Scrub well and cut potatoes; quarter lengthwise.
Melt butter and moisten wedges. Mix all dry ingredients in small bag.
Coat potatoes by shaking few in bag.
Place potatoes in buttered baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Turn potatoes once during baking.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, add oil.
Add vanilla and eggs. Alternate milk, soda and all dry ingredients.
Can add 3/4 cup of chopped nuts.
Bake in either tube pan for 40 minutes at 350°, 8 x 12-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350° or three layer pans for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: green chili stew
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer for approximately 20 minutes.
Serve with flour tortillas.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash until tender; drain well.
Saute onions. Layer in casserole squash and onions.
Add a few tablespoons of any cream soup (undiluted) and buttered bread crumbs.
End with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: God is like a Coke, He's the real thing.

title: chex mix sweet manglers
directions: In large microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate at HIGH for 1 minute. Stir and heat an additional
30 seconds at HIGH or until melted. Stir in peanut butter and peanuts. Gently stir cereal into chocolate-peanut butter mixture, until well coated.
Place powdered sugar in 2-gallon storage bag. Add coated cereal to sugar and close bag. Gently toss cereal mixture until well coated. Store in airtight container in refrigerator. Makes about 8 cups.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, syrup, butter and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: strawberry glaze pie
directions: In a saucepan stir sugar and cornstarch. Gradually add water stirring to dissolve; add crushed strawberries. Cook over med. heat until thickens, let come to boil. Boil for 1 minute; remove from heat. Beat cream cheese until smooth; then spread in bottom of pie shell. Fill with whole strawberries. Pour cooked strawberries on top; spread evenly. Chill for 3 hrs.

title: easy chicken divan(low-fat)
directions: Arrange broccoli in an 8-inch square baking dish sprayed with nonstick oil. Top broccoli with chicken. Combine remaining ingredients (except bread crumbs) and pour over chicken. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: multi-grain pancakes
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
In another bowl, mix liquid ingredients (minus oil) and the egg whites.
Stir together.
Mix well and add oil.
Heat skillet and pour out cakes.

title: corn pudding
directions: To the corn, add sugar, flour, salt, pepper and eggs.
Mix well.
Melt butter in baking dish (1 quart size).
Pour mixture into the hot buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then 50 minutes at 325°.

title: stir-fried chicken and zucchini
directions: Cut chicken in thin strips.
Heat oil in frypan.
Add chicken and garlic.
Cook, stirring constantly, until chicken turns white, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove garlic.
Add soy sauce and stir. Add celery, mushrooms and zucchini.
Cover and cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water.
Add slowly to chicken mixture. Cook until ingredients are coated with thin glaze, about 1 minute.
Makes 6 (3/4-cup) servings.
About 155 calories per serving.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Cook onion and butter until tender.
Stir in flour, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add milk and stir until thick.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 of the potatoes and ham.
Layer this mixture in a large glass greased casserole dish with the remaining potatoes and ham.
Bake at 400°, stirring once or twice during cooking.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes and then, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients and apply on open-face English muffins. Bake at 400° for 5 minutes; broil for 2 minutes.
Cut in half or quarters.
Serve warm.
Makes 12.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Mash berries in strainer with bowl underneath.
Pour juice in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch to water; mix well and then stir into boiling berry juice.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and mashed berries.
Thicken and set aside to cool.
Cream together cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pan lined with Graham Cracker Crust.
Add cooled berry sauce to top. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Mix all thawed concentrates in a punch bowl.
Add the lemon-lime soda.
Fresh strawberries, oranges and cranberries may be floated in the punch.
Makes 30 (1-cup) servings.

title: mushroom steak
directions: Cut round steak in slices; put in crock-pot.
Mix soup, milk, water, mushrooms and onions; pour over steak.
Stir together. Cook 6 hours on high.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Saute onion in butter until soft.
Place prepared bacon, cheese and onion in pastry shell.
Beat eggs and cream together. Season with salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Pour liquid mixture over bacon mixture.
Bake quiche in preheated 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool approximately 10 minutes.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and oleo and blend at low speed.
Add milk and blend.
Add pineapple chunks and bread cubes.
Bake at 325° in an ungreased casserole dish for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix and form into balls; cook in one can tomato soup and 1/2 cup water for 1 hour on low heat in electric skillet.

title: sauce for apple cake
directions: In saucepan, blend brown sugar, white sugar and flour.
Stir in boiling water slowly, then add butter and vanilla.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour hot sauce over cake as soon as it comes out of oven.

title: slumber dogs
directions: Use 1 dough bread and cut up into 10 portions.
Fix franks in dough like a sleeping bag, but first spread mustard and catsup on. Moisten edges with water to seal.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 17 minutes until brown.
Decorate using cheese to make hair and horns for hat, green pepper for eyes and pimientos for mouth.
Great for slumber party.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In casserole dish, put sweet potatoes, pineapple and pie filling; mix well.
In large bowl, mix sugar, pecans and butter. Pour over top of fruit and potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lime jello dessert with pineapple(great for christmas)
directions: *For Thanksgiving, you can substitute a package of strawberry Jell-O and a can of cranberry sauce instead of pineapple.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Put butter, cocoa and water in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add sugar, flour and salt; mix well.
Add eggs, sour cream and soda.
Beat well.
Pour into 11 1/2 x 18-inch cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Mix up icing while cake is baking.
Remove cake from oven.
Pour icing over warm cake.

title: catatini
directions: Boil your noodles until tender; drain.
Brown meat until done; drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish; bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Add cheese.
Put back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: baked manicotti
directions: In large skillet, brown beef, stirring.
With slotted spoon transfer beef into large bowl and add egg, salt, herbs, pepper and 1 1/4 cups jar sauce.
Stir in 8 ounces Mozzarella.
With small spoon, fill raw manicotti with meat mixture.
Preheat oven to 375°. Spoon 3 1/2 cups sauce in bottom of 17 x 12 x 2-inch baking pan. Arrange 3 rows of manicotti lengthwise.
Cover with remaining sauce; sprinkle with Parmesan
and top with rest of cheese.
Bake covered with foil 60 minutes; bake uncovered 10 minutes.

title: rhubarb jelly
directions: Cut rhubarb into chunks. Cook until soft. Pour into 1/2 pint jars. Put lids on. Cool and freeze.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix the above together, except peanut butter and oats and bring to a boil.
Boil 3 minutes, then remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and oats.
Mix quickly and drop by tablespoonfuls onto wax paper.
After approximately 10 minutes, cookies should be hard.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Mix hamburger, chili and Ro-Tel tomatoes together and cook for 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add Velveeta cheese (chopped or cubed) and whipping cream.
Stir until cheese melts.
Serve over Doritos. Top with chopped tomatoes, onions, lettuce (shredded), shredded cheese and picante sauce.

title: white fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and Karo syrup until soft ball forms when dropped into cold water.
(It will change color, sort of a light brownish color.)
Add butter, peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Beat until mixed well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan that has been lined with foil.
The fudge will come off the foil easily if you grease it lightly with butter.
Let it cool. Cut into squares.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chicken.
Pour over wings in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 1 hour.
Place drained wings on a baking sheet.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn and bake 15 minutes more.

title: becker's best strawberry pie
directions: When you want something light and really easy, spoon creme de menthe over fresh grapefruit sections, no sugar or anything, for a pleasant and satisfying dessert.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add all ingredients and cook, covered, about 15 minutes.

title: hot sauce
directions: Chop first 3 ingredients; mix last 4 ingredients and boil. Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: granny's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in an uncooked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes. Turn oven to 300° to 325°. Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and bake in buttered pan in a moderate 375° oven 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
May be served with carrots, peas and white sauce.

title: roasted tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Core the tomatoes and cut in half horizontally.
Squeeze gently to remove the seeds.
Place them cut side up on a rack in a broiler pan.
In a small bowl, combine the oil, basil, thyme, salt and pepper. Brush over the cut sides of the tomatoes.
Place cut side down on the rack and bake for 30 minutes.
Remove the skin, if desired.
Use in pasta salad or as a vegetable side dish.

title: elegant chicken a la king
directions: Cook green pepper and mushrooms in 2 Tbsp butter until tender, but not brown; push vegetables to one side, and blend flour and salt into the butter.
Stir in cream; cook and stir until sauce thickens and bubbles.
Add chicken and heat; stirring occasionally.

title: extra moist chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Bring to a boil oleo, shortening and water.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix in buttermilk with soda and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 35 minutes or less at 350°.

title: baked ziti with ricotta
directions: Cook macaroni
until
almost
done.
Strain and place in large bowl with
enough
sauce
to
keep from sticking.
In the pan, alternate a
layer
of macaroni and sauce and spoonfuls of Ricotta, Mozzarella and
grated
cheese until you have 3 layers and top with
sauce
and
sliced
thin Mozzarella.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°, covered in aluminum foil.

title: easy fudge
directions: Combine pudding mix, margarine and milk in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat, quickly stirring in sugar completely.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan; chill.
Cut into pieces.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Let stand 10 minutes at room temperature before serving.

title: humus
directions: After crushing garlic, put in blender and add all other ingredients.
Then mix in blender.
Serve with wedges of pita bread that are toasted.
Cut like a pizza pie, but smaller.

title: maui slush
directions: Combine all into a large freezable container.
Freeze at least 1 day.
When serving, add 7-Up to each glass of slush.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese and milk.
Add dressing and catsup.
Add onion and blend well; refrigerate.

title: green creme de menthe cake
directions: Mix cake mix, liqueur, orange juice, oil and eggs in mixer; beat for 4 minutes.
Reserve one cup of batter.
Pour the rest of the batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Pour liquid chocolate into the one cup of reserved batter and mix well.
Pour over the middle of the batter in the Bundt pan.
(This will sink to the bottom of the cake and look like a frosting when cooked.) Bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan and dust with powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar and spices in mixing bowl.
Pour into an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over the top.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake until cake is set in center, about 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool to room temperature, then refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: mary ann's caramel corn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a large shallow aluminum pan, spread the popcorn and nuts.
In saucepan, stir together the sugar, butter and corn syrup until all is melted.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until the mixture comes to a boil.
Continue cooking for 5 more minutes, without stirring.
Remove from the heat.
Add the vanilla extract and the baking soda.
Pour this mixture over the popcorn and peanuts in the pan, stirring it around to coat and distribute the coating.
Bake in the preheated oven, stirring occasionally, for 1/2 hour.
After the mix is done, pour it out on waxed paper and cool.
Serve warm or cold.
You'll love it.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix together and pour into a baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper in olive oil; add ground beef and brown.
Drain fat.
Add hominy, tomato sauce and chili powder; mix well.

title: sugar-free christmas tortoni
directions: Mix cookie crumbs, cut up gumdrops and the almonds.
Fold into the softened ice cream.
Divide ice cream mixture among 8 paper lined medium foil muffin cups (2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inch).
Decorate tops.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: potato dumplings
directions: Heat butter and saute onion until lightly brown.
Set aside.

title: favorite chicken dish
directions: Combine soup, milk, mushrooms and 1/2 onion soup mix.
Pour over chicken (13 x 9-inch baking dish).
Add rice.
Sprinkle balance of soup mix over top.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°. Uncover and bake for 15 minutes longer.
Add additional liquid, if necessary.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Fix regular or instant mashed potatoes.
Add the above ingredients and place in large Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and/or paprika.
Bake at 350° until hot, about 20 minutes. Simple, but it gives pizzazz to a favorite dish.

title: stained glass windows
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over low heat; cool.
Add marshmallows and 1 cup chopped nuts to chocolate mixture.
Shape into 2 rolls 1 1/2 inches to 2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill 15 minutes.
Roll in additional walnuts and chill until firm.
When rolls are thoroughly chilled, slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with 1/2 cup melted butter and press into a 10-inch pie plate.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter and pour into the crust.
Scald milk and add slowly into the eggs.
Add grated cheese and stir.
Pour over onions and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge
directions: Boil the sugar and evaporated milk for 8 to 10 minutes.
Add butter; boil again for about 5 minutes.
Add the chocolate chips, marshmallows, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until dissolved; pour fast into buttered jelly roll pan.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine in a small bowl: cream cheese, egg, chocolate chips and set aside. Mix together: flour, 1 c. of sugar, cocoa, soda, salt, oil, water and vanilla. Fill muffin cups 1/3 full with batter. Top each with 1 heaping tsp. of cream cheese filling. Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix together mustard, paprika, celery seed and sugar.
Add vinegar.
Mix well.
Add vegetable oil slowly as you mix.
Mix until thick.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: queso con picante
directions: Using an electric mixer, beat cheese and picante sauce until creamy.
Spread mixture on a plate.
Serve as is or with shredded lettuce and Cheddar cheese on top.
Place a basket of tortilla or nacho cheese chips next to the dip and watch it disapper.

title: lemon phluph
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; chill until partly set.
Whip jello until lightly foamy.
Add lemon juice and mix very well (to jello).
In a separate bowl, whip cooled milk until thick.
Whip in sugar gradually (into milk).
Blend both mixtures together. Line 9 x 13-inch glass dish with 1/2 crushed Nilla wafers.
Pour mix into 9 x 13-inch glass dish over layer of crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Chill until set.
Serve.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve in a small bowl the yeast and 1/2 cup warm water. In a large bowl, mix 3 1/2 cups hot water, sugar, salt and oil. Add yeast mixture to large bowl.
Stir.
Add in 4 cups flour (use high gluten bread flour, such as "Better for Bread").
Mix by spoon until smooth.
Add in by stirring and then by kneading: 7 cups flour or more.
As you knead you may add more flour until you have a ball of dough that is smooth and not sticky.
Kneading makes the difference with pizza dough!

title: cabin cookies
directions: Mix up gud 'n drap on greasy cookie sheet...Bake...take outta oven 'n stand back!

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour oats over hot water and let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream butter and sugar; add oatmeal-water mixture, then sift in dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured pan that measures about 9 x 13-inch.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tim's chili colorado
directions: Cut roast into 1/4-inch chunks.
In a large pan, add oil, liquid smoke and meat.
Brown until almost done.
Drain meat and place in crock-pot or Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low for approximately 2 hours.
Serve over cooked rice or with tortillas and make burritos.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Chop cranberries in blender using water.
Drain and mix with other ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Beat together the first 8 ingredients; stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: turkey crunch casserole
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Stir soup into mayonnaise and toss with turkey mixture.
Turn into a 2 quart casserole and sprinkle with noodles or chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbling.
Serve 6.

title: the great pumpkin pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth or place in a large bowl and beat with an eggbeater.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg, sugar and salt in bowl.
Beat well and add chocolate chips.
Set this aside.
Beat the rest of the ingredients until mixed well; fill cupcake liners full with this mixture.
Top each with a heaping teaspoonful of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 18 cupcakes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: In bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in blueberries.
Add milk, eggs and butter; mix.
Batter will be lumpy.
Spoon batter into 12 greased muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until tops spring back when lightly touched.

title: cherry twist
directions: Spread "Thank You" cherry pie filling on the bottom of Pyrex dish.
Spread one box of yellow cake mix over this.
Cut up one stick of margarine over all.
Cover with nuts.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° to 375°.
You can use any "Thank You" filling.

title: deer marinade for steak or roast
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour over meat and marinate in refrigerator 2 to 4 days.
Drain meat and pat dry.
Cook as directed.

title: coconut macaroons(makes about 4 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine coconut, Eagle Brand and extracts; mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto generously greased baking sheets.
Garnish with fruit or nuts, if desired.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Immediately remove from baking sheets (macaroons will stick if allowed to cool on baking sheets).
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: finger jello
directions: In a large bowl, mix unflavored gelatine with fruit flavored gelatin powder.
Add boiling water and stir until completely dissolved.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or a jelly roll pan and chill until firm.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.

title: honey garlic ribs
directions: Cook ribs in boiling water until tender.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Coat ribs with sauce.
May be baked, broiled, barbecued or simmered on stove.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: In a large pan combine cream cheese, milk, salt and pepper. Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add potatoes and chives; mix lightly.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: muskrat stew
directions: Soak muskrats in salt water overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, drain, wipe dry and cut each into 6 pieces:
2 hind legs, 2 front legs and 2 saddles.
Dredge with flour, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Brown on all sides in hot fat (traditionally lard) in a heavy frying pan.
Then put into a roasting pan, cover with water and add a finely chopped onion.
Cover pan and cook about 1 hour in a 350° oven, or until the meat is tender and juices are cooked down and thickened.
Stir in sherry.

title: ruth head's strawberry pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add water and boil 1 minute.
Add red food coloring, if desired.
Cool.
Bake pie shell according to package directions; cool.
Mix and fold liquid mixture with strawberries.
Place mixture in pie shell.
Top with Cool Whip. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: german sweet chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and 2 tablespoons milk in bowl in microwave. Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Beat in cream cheese, sugar and remaining milk until well blended. fold in whipped topping, blending until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger and drain off fat.
Rinse and drain sauerkraut. Add all ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: marie's microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix and pour on top of meat loaf.
Microwave 25 to 35 minutes on Medium-high (roast).
Pour off liquids and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: homemade pot pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together with a fork.
Make wet with milk.
Do
not
make too wet, just enough so you can roll into a ball.

title: french bread a la zonie
directions: Split the loaf of bread lengthwise, then slice the halves crosswise just to the crust, but not through it.
Mix the cheese, parsley, garlic, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Beat in enough melted butter and olive oil to make a creamy, spreadable mixture. Spread this paste on the cut surfaces of the bread and let stand for an hour or two.
Just before serving, place on a baking sheet and heat thoroughly in a 375° oven for 10 minutes, then brown lightly under the broiler.

title: raisin brown bread
directions: Combine raisins and 1 1/2 cups water. Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in the egg, brown sugar, oil and orange peel. Stir together the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Add to the raisin mixture, stirring just until blended.
Pour into a greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan. Bake at 325° until done, about 1 hour.
Remove from pan and cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: german potato pancakes(theresa shea)
directions: Peel and grate potatoes.
Do not include any excess moisture which accumulates.
Add egg and onion; stir well.
Add dry ingredients and mix until blended.
Drop batter by the heaping tablespoonfuls onto hot skillet, containing 1/4-inch shortening or bacon fat.
Spread with the spoon to form flat, even cakes.
Fry until crisp and golden brown.
Serve hot with applesauce.
Makes about 16.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Drain. Drain tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients and simmer, covered, for two hours.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly coat a cookie sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
Prick the sweet potato with a fork and bake in the oven for 1 hour or cook in microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Combine the cinnamon, allspice, flour, baking powder and salt in a food processor.
Add the margarine and Pulse 6 or 7 times until slightly crumbly.

Or combine these dry ingredients in a bowl and cut in the chilled margarine with a pastry cutter or two forks. Add 3/4 cup of the baked sweet potato meat and mix until crumbly. Add the milk, a tablespoon at a time until a soft, kneadable dough is formed.
You may not need all the milk.
Place the dough on a lightly floured board and knead it for 30 seconds.
Roll it out to 1/2-inch thickness and cut 12 rounds, using a 1 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
You will have to reshape and reroll the dough several times to utilize all the dough for the biscuits.
Lay the rounds of dough on the prepared pan and bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until the tops are lightly browned.
Yields 12 biscuits.

title: cheese ball
directions: Shred sharp Cheddar cheese.
Knead in softened cream cheese and Blue cheese.
Add onion powder and cayenne pepper to taste. Form into ball or log.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: snicker snack
directions: Place graham crackers side by side in an ungreased 15 x 10-inch pan.
In heavy 2-quart saucepan, combine butter and sugar. Cook over medium heat until boiling (3 to 5 minutes).
Boil for 5 minutes; stir constantly.
Immediately pour over graham crackers and spread to coat.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Let stand 1 minute, then spread.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Lightly press peanuts into chocolate.
Cool.
Break or cut into bars.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: roast to boast on
directions: Take your roast and with a sharp knife, make a hole through the center of your roast from one end to the other.
Stuff as much of the onion and green pepper as possible in the middle of the roast along with half of the garlic.
Take the remaining ingredients and put them on the outside of the roast except for the oil and bouillon cubes.
Let marinate for 24 hours.

title: chicken-rice-green bean casserole
directions: Layer green beans, water chestnuts and chicken in order listed. Mix remaining ingredients together and spread evenly over first layer.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: In large mixing bowl, add all ingredients in order. Mix well until thoroughly blended. Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2 baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: carolina skillet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Grease and flour skillet or cake pan. Cream shortening, gradually adding sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each. Add flour and milk alternately. Mix in vanilla. Fold in nuts. Pour into pan and top with crumble topping. Make indentions in batter so the topping will bake into cake.

title: brewed ice tea with sugar and lemon
directions: Brew tea bags in boiling water and allow to sit about 1 hour as tea cools.
Then, add the tea to lemonade and sugar in a 1-gallon jug.
Add water to fill jug.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Drain well.
Add chili powder, garlic and tomato sauce.
Rinse cans with water.
Add vinegar, sugar, red pepper and oregano.
Cook for 45 minutes.
Add the beans and simmer for 15 minutes.
Mix the 3 tablespoons of flour with the cup of water.
Mix well.
Add this mixture to the chili.
Stir well and cook on low heat for 1 hour.

title: mashed potato donuts
directions: Combine.
Dough will be soft.
Chill thoroughly.
Pat out to 1/4-inches.
Cut and fry at 375°.
Turn when donuts come to top.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix nuts and coconut and spread in bottom of 11 x 15-inch greased pan.
Mix German chocolate cake according to directions and spoon over nuts and coconut.
Combine powdered sugar, cream cheese, water and margarine.
Spoon over top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: lean american omelette
directions: Combine egg yolks, milk and salt; beat until thick and lemon colored.
Add onions.
Fold into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Melt margarine in a 10-inch skillet over low heat.
Pour egg mixture into skillet; cook over low heat for 10 to 12 minutes, or until underside is golden brown.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until top is firm.
Remove from oven.
Make a deep crease across center of top.
Place process cheese slices and meat on half of omelette.
Slip spatula underneath; tip skillet to loosen and gently fold omelette in half.
Top with additional process cheese slices.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: carp casserole
directions: Rub the cleaned carp with salt and dredge in flour.
Roast in a covered pan in the oven.
Fry potatoes in oil with bacon. Remove carp from pan and add potato, pickles and parsley. Sprinkle this with chopped garlic.
Arrange carp on top of potato, add wine and bake until potatoes are tender.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in square cake pan.
Mix the cake mix, pineapple and pie filling.
Melt 1 stick of butter; pour on top. Sprinkle walnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve hot with ice cream, if desired.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and salt together, getting all lumps out of cocoa.
Add milk, vanilla and margarine; mix.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Add chopped nuts and coconut. Pour into 3 regular or 2 deep dish pie crusts and bake 1 hour at 350°.
After pies are taken from oven, they will set.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix all together in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover pan with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; let set for several hours before serving.

title: ginger chicken
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
In large skillet, brown chicken and remove from pan.
Using same pan, add julienned carrots, mushrooms, broccoli and green onions.
Brown and add ginger and ginger ale (Vernors, regular or diet).
Boil.
Turn off.
Move vegetables to the side of pan and put rice in center of pan.
Cover for 5 minutes.
Mix and serve.
Serves 4.

title: california sugar cookies
directions: Beat together the first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Blend remaining dry ingredients together in separate bowl.
Add to sugar mixture and beat again until well mixed.
Drop small balls of dough onto cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet and sour spareribs(chinese)
directions: Cut ribs into 2-inch squares (or have butcher cut package of ribs in thirds).
Dip each piece in batter.

title: pork au onion(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Put boneless pork into a baking dish. Cover roast with the vinegar and soy sauce.
Add enough water to cover roast.
Bake with cover for 1 hour at 350°.
Saute onions in butter until well cooked while roast is baking.
After 1 hour, remove baking dish from the oven.
Drain the pork and remove any excess fat from the roast.
Slice pork roast and return to baking dish.
Cover with onions, red wine and mustard.
Bake, uncovered, about 1/2 hour or until sauce is thick.
Garnish with red and green peppers or other colorful vegetables.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook hamburger with onion until brown. Arrange layer of cabbage and a layer of hamburger in a casserole dish. Pour the tomato soup and water over the other ingredients. Cover dish and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: crab meat au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 1-quart casserole dish. Drain crab meat.
Slowly heat butter on low heat.
When melted, gradually stir in flour; add milk, then salt and pepper.
Continue to stir until very thick.
Remove from heat.
Stir in crab meat and mushrooms.
Pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until hot.

title: sundae dessert
directions: Save 1 cup
crumbs
for
top
and
put rest of crumbs on bottom. Layer fruit
(diced).
Slice
ice cream and nuts.
Layer ingredients in order given and
freeze.
Melt
chips and butter and add powdered sugar and evaporated
milk;
cook until thick and smooth.
Add vanilla; cool. Pour over
the
layered ingredients and freeze.
Top with whipped cream and crumbs.
Makes a 9 x 13-inch pan real full.

title: tamale pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook meat, onion and green pepper in a large skillet until meat is slightly brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, corn, olives, garlic, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, chili powder and pepper.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until thick.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Turn into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Make cornmeal topper.

title: zerilli meat balls
directions: Combine sausage, bread crumbs and eggs.
Mix well with moist hands.
Roll meatballs very tiny (bite size).
Brown meatballs. Combine ketchup, soy sauce, vinegar and sugar.
This is the sauce. Add meatballs and sauce in a crock-pot and heat.

title: filet mignon with mushrooms(serves 6)
directions: Slice mushrooms; saute in 3 tablespoons butter.
Add flour and salt and pepper to taste; blend well.
Stir in warm cream; keep well heated in a separate skillet while you saute Filets in hot butter for 2 1/2 minutes per side (for rare).
Saute bread slices in 6 tablespoons butter, turning often to prevent butter from being absorbed.
Arrange bread slices in a ring on well heated platter.
Top with the Filets; arrange the mushroom sauce in the center.
Stir the Scotch into pan juices.
Boil for 1 to 2 minutes and spoon sauce over meat.

title: penne with lamb ragu
directions: In a large skillet, heat the olive oil.
Add the lamb and saute over high heat until browned, 1 to 2 minutes.
Add the garlic, rosemary, parsley, hot pepper and salt; saute for 30 seconds.
Pour in the wine and boil, scraping up the browned bits, 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the tomatoes; cover and simmer over low heat until the lamb is very tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Cook the pasta. Remove the hot pepper from the sauce and toss with the pasta.

title: pecan pie
directions: Lay pecans in pie shell.
Beat all ingredients together.
Pour into shell. Bake in 325° oven for 35 minutes or until middle of pie doesn't wiggle.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Nice in hollowed out head of red cabbage.

title: sausage bean salad
directions: Mix the Italian dressing with the mustard.
Marinate the beans, potatoes, onion and peppers in 1/4 cup of the dressing mixture. Before serving, add the sausage and tomatoes and toss with the remaining dressing.
Serve on top of escarole or romaine lettuce.

title: shrimp etouffee(serves 4)
directions: Chop all vegetables as fine as possible.
Heat butter until bubbly and add chopped vegetables. Fry until golden brown. Add tomatoes and half juice.
Let cook 10 minutes.
Add shrimp (peeled), seasoning and wine.
Lower fire and cover, letting steam 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over fluffy rice.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix salad dressing and sugar.
Toss with salad and top with cheese.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Place half of crushed cookies in 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bowl ,mix sugar, cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Add milk and pudding mix.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over cookie crumbs in pan.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze 24 hours before serving.

title: no peek casserole
directions: Mix all together in 2-quart casserole. Cover tightly. Bake at 300° for 3 hours.
Do not peek. Serve over rice or noodles. Serves 6.

title: delicious hamburgers
directions: Mix all together and form burgers.
Makes 25.

title: meat loaf
directions: Pour over meat loaf and continue cooking about 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Crumble crackers on top with melted margarine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place in buttered dish.
Grate cheese on top.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage beef stew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook sausage and beef in 2 tablespoons melted shortening.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
In large pan, cook onion in oil until transparent.
Add peppers and cook 1 minute longer.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly, then pour over meat.
Cover and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook package of vegetables until tender (not soft).
Drain. Melt oleo; pour over crushed crackers; mix.
Layer vegetables, cheese and crumbs.
End with crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Add condensed milk and rum.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Re-chill mixture if it becomes soft.
Flavor improves after 24 hours.
May be refrigerated for several weeks.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain oranges well.
Heat 1 bottle of ginger ale to boil.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add second bottle of ginger ale and lemon juice.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Chill until syrupy. Fold in whipped cream, bananas and oranges.
Place in a 7 x 11-inch pan or mold and chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: anise sticks
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar; add eggs and flavorings.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients.
Oil 4 cookie sheets as this makes 4 loaves longways.
Divide dough into 4 parts and make loaves about 1 inch high.

Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350° until lightly browned. While still warm, slice 1/2 inch thick and place slices on cookie sheet and return to oven to crisp and brown slightly on both sides, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Heat in coffeepot.
(This smells good, too!)

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Stir flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside. In a large bowl, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth. Beat in sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; beat well. Dough may be chilled for a few hours (optional).
Shape into 1-inch balls; place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork which has been dipped with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese.
Put half mixture in preheated oiled iron skillet; add about 1/3 of cheese.
Pour rest of mixture and top with rest of cheese.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: In large bowl, mix Ricotta or cottage cheese, 1 cup shredded Mozzarella, the egg, spinach, salt, pepper and oregano.
Grease a lasagna tin or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce, 1/3 of the noodles, and 1/2 of the cheese mixture. Repeat.
Top with remaining noodles, then remaining sauce. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup (or more if you like) of Mozzarella cheese.
Pour water around edges.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 20 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving (8 portions).

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix oleo, flour and nuts. Press in bottom of 13 X 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes. Cool. Blend together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip. Spread on cooled crust and refrigerate. Mix pudding and milk and put over the cream cheese mixture. Refrigerate. Cover with cool whip and nuts, if desired.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Blend
together
sugar,
salt
and flour.
Add eggs and blend well;
add remaining ingredients, mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into 2 greased 9-inch pie pans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30
or 40 minutes or until coconut is brown.
(Mixture will be loose and thin when poured, but will be firm when cooked.)

title: cheese zucchini pie
directions: Brown meat in large skillet, stirring to break into bits. Drain.
Add onions and green pepper.
Saute several minutes to soften vegetables.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, garlic salt, oregano and pepper.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush 20 ounce package of Oreo cookies.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, mix 1/2 stick margarine, 8 ounces cream cheese and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Set aside.

title: holiday jello fruit salad
directions: Mix the Jell-O powders, then add 3 cups of boiling cranberry juice and stir to dissolve.
Chip the orange and the cranberries in a blender.
Use the remaining 2 cups of cranberry juice to moisten the fruit as it is chopped.
Add the fruit mixture, chopped apple and nuts to the Jell-O.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into serving dish and chill.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Beat butter, sugar and egg with electric mixer.
Blend in flour, salt, baking powder and milk.
Pour cherries into greased, shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with butter, tapioca and lemon juice.
Spoon batter on top of cherries.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Serve warm with milk or cream or ice cream.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and soak in water for 1/2 hour. Drain and arrange in deep baking dish in layers. Sprinkle each layer with flour, salt and pepper. Dot with butter. Pour milk over all and sprinkle with grated cheese if desired. Bake in 450° oven for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni.
Cook eggs; chop.
Chop onion, carrot and celery.
Mix remaining ingredients together and add to macaroni.

title: grandma's gelatin fruit salad
directions: Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened. Let cool, arrange bananas over gelatin.
Combine dressing with whipped topping, (can use Cool Whip); spread over bananas.
Yield: 12 - 15 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell. Bake in 400 degree oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake an additional 30-35 minutes.

title: ufaikiki meatballs
directions: Mix all together and form into meatballs.
Brown and drain. The meatballs cook up very easily and quickly in a microwave oven.

title: bacon swiss meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine egg, milk, 1 cup cheese, 3/4 cup bacon, bread crumbs and garlic and onion powders. Crumble beef over mixture and mix well. Shape into a loaf in a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour or until meat is no longer pink and a meat thermometer reads 160°. Drain and sprinkle with remaining cheese and bacon. Bake 3 to 5 minutes longer until cheese is melted. Let stand for 10 minutes before slicing. Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy lime dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together until smooth and refrigerate. Serve with favorite mixture of fruits.

title: busy day grilled cheese
directions: You will need foil and an iron.

title: zesty cheese ease
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Chill.
Stuff vegetables or serve on crackers.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over low heat, heat cheese and margarine, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted.
Into another bowl, sift together sugar and cocoa.
Gradually add sugar/cocoa mixture to melted cheese and butter, stirring until smooth.
Add pecans and vanilla; mix well.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover, chill and cut into squares.

title: squash casserole
directions: Rinse squash and cut ends off.
Slice or dice squash and cook in water with butter and salt until tender.
Let cool and add onion, soup, sour cream and half of dressing.
Mix well.
Pour into greased baking pan.
Sprinkle remainder of dressing on top of casserole until covered.
Bake at 375° until top is golden brown and bubbly.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cranberry cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Mix next four ingredients and add to dry ingredients.
Mix buttermilk, oil and eggs.
Add to mixture and stir until well mixed.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. While warm, pour glaze over cake.
Wrap in tinfoil.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: pecan pie
directions: For filling, in a mixing bowl, beat eggs lightly with beater or a fork.
Stir in corn syrup, sugar, margarine or butter and vanilla.
Stir well.
Stir in pecan halves.

title: banana bread
directions: Add in order and beat well together.
Place in buttered loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Allow to cool.

title: blueberry cupcakes
directions: Measure flour before sifting. Stir margarine just to soften. Mix in flour, sugar, egg yolks and half of milk. Beat for 2 minutes. Add remaining milk and vanilla and beat. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lumpia
directions: Brown pork and drain. Mix all ingredients, except wrappers. Take a heaping tablespoon and roll in won ton wrapper according to package directions. Deep-fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: peanut butter oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Beat in water, egg and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and chill about 2 hours.
Shape into 1-inch ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten with fork dipped in sugar to form crisscross pattern.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Melt butter; saute onions until clear.
Add flour and salt to taste.
Stir well and cook for 1 minute on medium.
Stir in milk, slowly.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens. Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Continue stirring until cheese melts.
Add cheese mixture to broccoli.
Stir in beaten eggs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: rainbow fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine fruit.
Add Pineapple Lime Dressing; stir gently to coat.
Makes 8 servings.

title: allie's cinnamon rolls
directions: Cream together 1/2 cup oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, salt and yeast, then add warm milk.
Add flour, 2 cups at a time.
Do not knead.
Grease top and cover.
Let rise double, 5 to 6 hours.
If in a hurry, use 2 packages of yeast.
Roll out and spread with oleo, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll like jelly roll and cut 1 inch thick.
Place on greased pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until brown.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: Put the vegetables in layers in a dish. Combine the mayonnaise and sugar and spread on top. Slice the eggs on top. Sprinkle grated cheese over all. Refrigerate overnight.

title: seashell rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Bring milk to almost boiling; add butter, sugar and salt.
Cool.
Add beaten eggs and yeast mixture.
Add 3 cups flour.
Add 3 more cups flour.
Refrigerate overnight or for at least several hours.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll out into large circle (dough approximately 1/8-inch thick).
Cut into 12 triangular parts.
Roll up and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Butter.
Makes 36 rolls.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken, debone and tear into small pieces.
Pack back into pot.
Add soup, broth, Ro-Tel, onion, cheese, chili powder and garlic salt.
Cook on top of stove until cheese melts.
Place a layer of chips in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour mixture over chips; sprinkle cheese on top.
Place in oven and bake at 350° until browns.
Serve hot over fresh chips.

title: very good easy sweet pickles
directions: Fill a quart jar with whole, medium size cucumbers.
Add pickling spice (being sure not to add more than two of the red peppers from spice), salt, horseradish, alum and vinegar.
Fill jar with cold water.
Seal and shake.
Set aside for at least 6 weeks.
When ready to use, wash cucumbers.
Discard all juice and spice.
Cut in chunks and add 1 cup sugar.
Stir occasionally until sugar is dissolved; then put in refrigerator.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: blackberry vodka tonic
directions: Place the blackberries in a 6 cup jar with a tight fitting lid. Add the vodka. Cover tightly and let stand at room temperature for 4 days, turning the jar over every day.
Transfer the jar to the freezer and freeze for at least 2 days or up to 1 year.

title: venison chili
directions: Place first 9 ingredients in large skillet and cook until meat is brown and tender.
Remove from skillet and place in 2-gallon pot.
Add next 10 ingredients and cook for 45 minutes at low heat, stirring every 10 minutes.
Add kidney beans and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Serves 6.
Preparation Time: 2 hours and 30 minutes.

title: lemon cream mold
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients in bowl; add water.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in lemonade.
Chill until jelly like consistency. Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into 4 cup ring.

title: mediterranean fish stew
directions: Cook onions and garlic in oil until tender.
Add tomatoes; cook over moderately high heat for 4 to 5 minutes.
Add water, clam juice and seasonings; simmer for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes; cook until done.
Add fish fillets; simmer until fish flakes easily, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fudge nut bars
directions: Cream butter or oleo and brown sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchilada
directions: Saute onion in	butter.
Combine soups, broth and green chili. Add chicken pieces
and
beat well.
In a large baking dish, place a layer of tortillas, a layer of chicken sauce and a layer of grated cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: souperburgers
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion in shortening.
Stir to separate meat particles.
Add soup and seasonings; simmer about 5 to 10 minutes, stirring now and then.
Serve on buns.

title: pop rouge ice cream(strawberry)
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
May freeze in electric or hand freezer or put in refrigerator freezer until hard.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for flour and zucchini. Add flour, one cup at a time.
Stir in zucchini.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 325° for 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: two kinds of squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until done, then drain.
Mix together cooked squash, onion, eggs, milk and Good Seasons Italian dressing mix. Add salt and pepper to taste.
In bottom of casserole dish, line with Velveeta cheese and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Spread squash mixture on top of cheeses.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and broil until brown.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients; blend well.
Keep covered in refrigerator until serving time.
Shake well before using.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into about 1-inch cubes.
Brown steak in oil over medium heat until done.
Add beef broth, garlic salt, ground ginger and green pepper.
Reduce heat and simmer until crisp-tender.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and soy sauce, stirring well; add to beef mixture.
Bring to a boil.
This will thicken fast; stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Serve over rice.

title: white lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to directions; drain.
In a large saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour, onion, garlic powder and pepper.
Add broth and milk.
Cook and stir until bubbly and thickened.
Stir in 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Spread 1/2 cup sauce in the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir mushrooms into the remaining sauce.
Lay 3 noodles in the pan.
Top with asparagus, chicken, Mozzarella and about 1 cup sauce.
Top with 3 more noodles, cooked ham and half of remaining sauce.
Cover with remaining noodles and sauce.
Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: frothy orange drink
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender; cover and process until drink is thick and slushy.
Yields 4 cups.

title: berry-banana smoothie
directions: Combine blueberries, banana slices, orange juice and dry milk in blender container.
Process until smooth.
Yield: 2 servings.

title: mini-chocolate mint cheese cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Process first 6 ingredients with electric blender until smooth.
Add melted chocolate chips. Process until smooth.
Spoon batter evenly into 24 cups of mini-muffin pans lined with paper liners.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until set.
Let cool in pans.
Cover and chill.

title: crunchy lentil salad
directions: Combine lentils, bay leaf and water in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook, uncovered, 15 minutes or until lentils are tender, but still crunchy.
Stir occasionally.
Pour into colander and discard bay leaf.
Drain well and let sit 5 to 10 minutes.
Place lentils in a serving bowl and gently stir in celery, carrot, onion and parsley.

title: raisin-oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Add eggs, beating until blended.
Gradually add flour and cinnamon, beating at low speed until blended.
Stir in oats, raisins, and pecans.
Cover and chill dough 8 hours.

title: coffee fudge swirl milkshake
directions: Give the automatic icemaker a rest, make a batch of flavored ice cubes.
Place a strawberry, raspberries, mint leaves or citrus peel in each compartment of an ice tray.
Fill with lemonade, Hi-C flavored drink, Kool Aid, cool tea, or fruit juice.
Freeze.
Then add to your favorite drink.
Great fun for parties.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender container.
Cover.
Blend until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Makes 3 servings.

title: cheesy chicken crescent supper
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine chicken and 2 tablespoons cheese in small bowl.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles. Place about 2 tablespoons of chicken mix on wide end of each triangle.
Roll up, starting at shortest point.
Combine soup, milk and 1/2 cup cheese in saucepan.
Heat until cheese melts. Pour half of soup mix into 8 or 9-inch square baking dish.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix the cake mix according to directions.
Divide batter into two parts.
To
one part of the batter, add the melted butter and milk.
Mix together and put into greased and floured 9 x 12 x 3-inch pan. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apricot cobbler
directions: Cook apricots with 3/4 cup sugar and heaping tablespoonful cornstarch.
Mix Bisquick, 3 tablespoons sugar, margarine and milk*.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: deluxe lima beans
directions: Fry bacon crisp; remove from pan.
Add onion and brown.
Add tomatoes,
lima beans and crumbled bacon.
Simmer about 10 minutes.

title: macaroni hamburger casserole
directions: Cook and drain elbow macaroni.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic salt and pepper to hamburger while browning meat.
Drain well.
Add hamburger mixture to macaroni and stir.
Add tomato sauce or spaghetti sauce.
Stir together.
Add frozen corn or peas to hamburger mixture.

title: corn chowder
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Brown onion in bacon fat.
Add water and potatoes, cover and cook until tender. Add milk, seasonings and crumbled bacon.
Stir and reheat.
If mixture is too thick thin with milk.

title: peanut chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine chicken broth, peanut butter and soy sauce; set aside.
Stir-fry chicken and garlic in vegetable oil until chicken is almost done.
Add frozen vegetables and sauce mixture. Stir-fry 5 to 7 minutes longer until thickened.
Serve over prepared rice.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Preheat cooking oil 2 or 3 inches deep in a small pan.
Drain all but 1/3 liquid from the salmon or tuna and set aside.
Put salmon or tuna in mixing bowl and break apart until you have it in no big flakes.
Add flour and egg.
Use a dash of pepper but no salt.
Add baking powder to the liquid and beat well with fork or whisk until frothy (this is an important step, do not skip).
Pour into salmon and stir until well blended.
Scoop about a teaspoon of the mixture at a time into the hot oil.
Brown on both sides.

title: mocha cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) layer pans.
Sift flour with salt.
Add sugar to shortening in large mixing bowl; cream at high mixer speed until fluffy.
Blend in eggs.
Add coffee to cocoa; add to creamed mixture.
Gradually add sifted dry ingredients; blend thoroughly.
Dissolve soda in water.
Add to batter.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with desired frosting.

title: pasta fagioli
directions: Combine beans, onion and 2 1/2 quarts of water in Dutch oven. Heat to boil.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour.
Add vegetable bouillon.
Simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, until beans are tender.
Saute garlic in oil.
Stir into beans.
Stir in tomatoes with liquid, salt and cayenne.
Heat to boil.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine
all
ingredients
except
bread.
Stir
until mixed. Make a cavity in the center of the round loaf, arranging pieces around the edge to be used in dipping.
Fill cavity with dip and enjoy!!

title: non-cook jello salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle nuts on top to decorate, if desired.
(Also, if wrapping with plastic wrap, nuts keep wrap from sticking.)
Enjoy!

title: ellen's yeast bread
directions: Mix together hot water and shortening and set aside.
In large bowl, stir together sugar, salt, dry yeast and 5 cups flour. Add water mixture and beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Add eggs, powdered milk and 7 cups flour.
Beat well with mixer.
Add 5 cups flour and mix well using bread hook on mixer.
Turn on floured surface and knead well.
Put in bowl and cover with towel.
Let rise in warm place until double. Punch down and let raise again. Punch down and form into 6 loaves; raise until double.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan; brush tops with butter, cover with towel and let cool.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain the broccoli.
Place in buttered 11 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Mix bread crumbs with melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine sour cream, cream cheese, mayonnaise and seasonings. Mix in crabmeat.
Place in casserole dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Serve warm with crackers, Triscuits or rye bread.

title: fruit surprise
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Mix next 4 ingredients together with fruit cocktail.
Sprinkle coconut on top as garnish.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: squash supreme
directions: Mash squash.
Add remaining ingredients, except crumbs; mix thoroughly.
Place crumbs in bottom of casserole dish (reserve some crumbs for top).
Spoon squash mixture on top of crumbs. Cover top with crumbs; dot generously with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: good for arthritis
directions: Mix well.
Keep in refrigerator.
Take a wine glass of this night and morning.
This formula came from the Mayo Brothers Texas Clinic.
Very good.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Boil 1 minute.
Cool and pour on cabbage and freeze.

title: corn rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well and place in a lightly buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
About 10 minutes before it is done, add 8 ounces grated Cheddar cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rehydrate hash brown potatoes per package directions and drain.
Brown sausage and drain off grease. Press crescent rolls into 10 x 13-inch ungreased pan, making an edge all the way around.
Sprinkle sausage and hash brown potatoes evenly over dough.
Beat eggs and pour over all.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until cheese is bubbly and bottom of crust is lightly browned.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Sift flour; combine with eggs, vanilla, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Heat milk and butter in pan.
Cool before adding to first mixture.
Mix well all ingredients.
Batter will be thin!
Do not add flour.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven in an 8 x 8-inch square pan.

title: zippy chicken stir-fry
directions: Stir together salad dressing, soy sauce, ginger and red pepper; set aside.
Heat oil in wok or heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken.
Stir-fry 4 minutes.
Add veggies and garlic.
Fry 4 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Stir in salad dressing mixture.
Simmer 30 seconds.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Beat egg whites until thick and fluffy.
Beat remaining ingredients together.
Fold in egg whites.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Mix well - bake in greased muffin pans, 2/3 full at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: beef rice pilaf
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add rice, cinnamon and bouillon cube. Add water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 20 minutes.
If desired, use chicken bouillon instead of beef and do not use cinnamon.

title: flannel cakes
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Beat egg yolks, then add milk and shortening.
Beat in flour mixture with rotary beater.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake on hot griddle, turning to brown both sides.
Makes 24.

title: meat loaf with vegetables
directions: If chopped, the meat should be minced very fine, together with the pork fat or trimmed and blanched salt pork or bacon.
Grate the potatoes, onions and carrots.
Crush the dry biscuits or bread fine.
Reserve 2/3 cup of bread crumbs.
If you are using tomato paste, mix it with 3/4 cup water.
Combine all ingredients and seasonings, except the butter and reserved bread crumbs; mix well.

title: wild game barbecue
directions: Cut up meat and combine onion, garlic, salt and pepper in large pan; bring to a boil, reduce heat to simmer and cook for about 1 hour.
Let cool and debone meat.
Put into casserole dish and cover with barbecue sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You can substitute chicken.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter. Add egg yolks, 1 at a time. Add sour cream. Mix together flour and baking soda; add slowly. Add vanilla and lemon flavoring. Fold in egg whites. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: summer veggie slaw
directions: Whisk vinegar with soy sauce, pepper and red pepper sauce in large bowl; gradually whisk in oil.
(Can be made ahead.
Cover and refrigerate dressing and vegetables separately up to 8 hours.)
Add remaining ingredients and toss well.

title: spiced ice tea
directions: In medium saucepan, heat water to boiling.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients.
Cover and let steep about 5 to 7 minutes.
Strain and pour tea into tall glasses filled with ice cubes.
Makes 4 servings, about 2/3 cup each.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, flour, butter, pineapple and coconut and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° until done. Makes 2 pies.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Combine flour, Parmesan and pepper.
Cut veal into 2-inch wide strips.
Dust with flour mixture.
Heat olive oil and garlic; brown meat lightly on both sides.
Remove garlic.
Add wine, stock and lemon juice.
Cover; simmer slowly for about 30 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Beat lemon juice, milk, pineapple, coconut and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in pie shell.
Chill; can be made the day before.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Beat sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add combined flour and crumbs; mix well.
Press onto bottom of greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients (marshmallows, chips and nuts).
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into 16 servings.

title: creole wieners
directions: In large skillet, fry bacon and onion until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.
Drain all but 2 tablespoons bacon drippings from skillet.
Stir in tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add wieners; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: puffed sweet omelet
directions: Brown the almonds by toasting lightly in the oven or saute in a little butter.
Beat the egg whites in a bowl until they form stiff peaks.
Beat the egg yolks in another bowl with the honey, liqueur and nutmeg.
Scoop a spoonful of the egg whites into the yolks and stir until combined.
Now pour the yolk mixture into the egg whites and fold together gently.
Preheat your broiler.
Heat a 10 or 12-inch frying pan over medium heat and add the butter. When the foam subsides and the butter just begins to color, add the omelet mixture.
Do not stir.
Cook for exactly 1 minute until the bottom is browned.
Place the pan containing the omelet under the broiler for 20 to 30 seconds.
