Slide the omelet onto a serving platter, folding as you do.
Garnish with the almonds and serve.

title: bennett's barbecue
directions: Cook meat until tender; cool and shred.
Add to large pot the meat and all the above ingredients.
Cook at least 2 hours.
Serve on toasted buns with cole slaw and pickle.

title: chicken casserole or hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients (except cheese, potato chips and almonds).
Place mixture in a large rectangular dish. Top with cheese, crushed potato chips and almonds.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(I mix potato chips and almonds before spreading.)
This recipe freezes well.

title: night before french toast casserole
directions: Arrange 1-inch thick slices of bread in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients except butter.
Pour over bread. Cover with foil. Refrigerate 24 to 36 hours or overnight. Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Sprinkle with cinnamon (if desired). Serve with maple syrup. Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken, remove bones and chop up. Set aside.
Save broth. Saute in skillet in oleo the onion, green pepper, celery and parsley.
Add the chicken, tomatoes and 2 cups chicken broth. Simmer about 20
minutes. Add seasoned salt to taste.
(If while simmering mixture gets too dry, add more chicken broth.)
Remove from heat and immediately stir in half the cheese so it will melt. Add mushrooms.
Cook the spaghetti and mix all together.
Place in a 9 x 14-inch baking dish and cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add remaining cheese and bake, uncovered, another 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 10 or more.
Can be frozen in foil covered baking dish.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Make pastry shell with a high, fluted rim.
Cream butter or margarine, gradually adding sugar, and blend well.
Separate egg yolks from whites.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add lemon rind, juice, flour and salt.
Mix well. Stir in milk.
Beat whites until stiff, but not dry, and fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate hazelnut java
directions: Pour the cocoa mix into large heatproof pitcher. Add the coffee and stir until dissolved. Pour into 4 large cups or mugs. For a coffee house touch, stir with cinnamon stick.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Blend all ingredients except cream cheese together.
Mix the cream cheese with enough mayonnaise to give it a good consistency, then blend with mixed vegetables.
Use thinly sliced sandwich bread.
Makes 10 generous full size or 20 triangle sandwiches.

title: nana's caramel bars
directions: Melt margarine (could be done in pan in which they are going to be baked).
Pour over sugar; stir.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to first mixture, then add nuts. Mix well.
Spread into 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch or 5 x 11-inch pan, depending on thickness of bar you want.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly and cut into 16 squares or size you want.
Do not overbake.
They should be chewy.
They keep well in an airtight container.

title: meat loaf
directions: Soak oats in the milk.
Mix all ingredients together and shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 45 minutes.
Drain off excess grease as soon as taken from the oven.

title: barbecued meat loaves
directions: Break bread crumbs into water, then mix all ingredients together; shape into small loaves.

title: cheesy tuna and noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Add seasoning packets, drain.
In large skillet over medium heat, in hot butter or margarine, cook broccoli and garlic until tender.
Stir in soup and milk.
Add cheese, pepper and nutmeg.
Cook until cheese melts.
Stir in noodles and tuna.
Heat through.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, flour and salt in double boiler.
Add milk. Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking for 10 minutes, stirring.
Add egg yolks gradually, stirring vigorously. Cook for 2 minutes longer.
Add butter and vanilla; cool.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Add meringue and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cold spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Better if made a day ahead.
Serve with Doritos.

title: candy kisses
directions: Save out enough pecan halves for the tops.

title: old fashioned vinegar pie(depression pie)
directions: Mix all together and pour into 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Top with grated nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until crust is done and filling is firm.

title: fruit swirl coffee cake
directions: Blend sugar, butter, shortening, baking powder, vanilla, almond and eggs in large bowl on a low speed.
Beat for 3 minutes on high speed.
Stir in flour.
Spread 2/3 of the batter in pan. Spread the pie filling over the batter.
Drop the rest of the batter in spoonfuls on top of the pie filling.
Drizzle with a glaze over it while it is still warm.
Bake in a greased pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan tarts(portuguese)
directions: Pastry Cup:
Mix cream cheese and butter until smooth. Add flour and baking powder. Continue adding flour until a nice ball forms.
Form small balls and shape into small muffin pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until just about done.
Place in buttered casserole.
Mix soup, lemon juice, cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread on broccoli.
Sprinkle with crackers.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: streusel cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box and pour 1/2 batter into pan.
Place filling on top and save 1/4 filling after pouring other 1/2 batter.
Sprinkle rest of filling on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine carrots, apple and raisins. Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add mayo or salad dressing.
Stir gently to coat well.
Cover and chill for 2 to 24 hours.

title: party gelatin mold
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; cool until mixture begins to thicken.
Then fold in sour cream, salt, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In saucepan, melt peanut butter and margarine.
In large bowl, combine powdered sugar and cereal; pour peanut butter mixture over cereal and sugar.
Blend together with hands and form into 1/2 inch balls.
Chill until firm.

title: sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish; set aside.
Cook sausage until brown, stirring to crumble; drain.
Spoon over bread; sprinkle with grated cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Mix and pour over cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
(May be assembled the day before, covered and refrigerated.
Remove from refrigerator 15 minutes before baking.) Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water.
Add oil, sugar, eggs, 4 cups flour and salt.
Stir and beat well, then add remaining flour.
Turn out onto floured surface and knead until you can handle.
Put in large covered container and let rise.
Then punch down.
Can be stored in refrigerator and used as needed.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix gelatine, sugar and salt thoroughly.
Add 1/2 cup of the water.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatine is dissolved.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining 1 cup water and vinegar.
Chill mixture to unbeaten egg white consistency.
Fold in apples, chopped celery and chopped nuts.
Chill until firm; garnish with apples.

title: sand tarts
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add flour and pecans.
Cook on 350° for 10 minutes.
Dip in sugar while still warm.

title: texas beans
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
May cook in slow cooker 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: peach and raisin pudding
directions: Drain peaches.
Cut bread into cubes and fry in butter or margarine until lightly browned.
Add milk; let stand 30 minutes.

title: school rolls
directions: Put warm milk in large bowl.
Add sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add melted shortening and stir.
Add flour. Knead until dough is smooth and soft.
Put dough in well-greased bowl. Set in a warm place and let rise double in size.
Punch dough down.
Shape into loaves or rolls.
Put into a greased pan. Let rise again.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.
Brush with butter and serve.

title: deep dish pizza dough
directions: Mix and let stand approximately 45 minutes.
Knead dough and place in ungreased pan.
Let stand another 45 minutes or more. Add desired topping and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes in 9 x 15-inch dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Crushed potato chips or cracker crumbs can be placed on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Mash bananas and mix with lemon juice.
Cream together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add mashed bananas and whip until light.
Sift together flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture along with milk and nuts.
Mix thoroughly. Divide batter between greased and floured loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove and cool on rack.
Wrap in plastic wrap. Attach festive ribbon.
Tuck in recipe and deliver to a friend.

title: aunt june's green beans and mushrooms
directions: Do not cook beans.
Put beans in casserole dish.
Heat cheese in mushroom soup until melted.
Pour over beans.
Add soya sauce, salt, pepper and water chestnuts.
Mix well; sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly, uncovered.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Boil slow for 6 to 8 minutes the milk, butter and sugar. Remove from stove and add the chocolate morsels and vanilla.
Beat until the morsels are melted, then beat in Marshmallow Creme until smooth.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch buttered pan.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Pour into one round and one square 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake and cool.
Place round layer in bottom of punch bowl.
Then layer remaining ingredients in order in bowl using 1/2 of each.
Cube the square layer cake and place in bowl and then layer remaining ingredients in order again in bowl.
Garnish with nuts and maraschino cherries.

title: hot crabmeat spread
directions: Saute onion and green pepper until tender using Teflon pan. Add remaining ingredients and heat until cheese is melted.
Spread on crackers.

title: creamed corn
directions: Cut corn off cob; put into saucepan.
Add salt, sugar, 1/4 stick margarine, Crisco oil and water to just cover corn.
Bring to boil and cook gently for about 20 minutes.

title: cold pasta fruit salad
directions: Combine spaghetti, apples and pineapple.
Combine eggs, lemon juice
and	powdered sugar and cook until thick and let cool.
Add to
spaghetti mixture.
Mix well, chill overnight. Before serving, mix in 8 ounces Cool Whip.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Meanwhile, in saucepan, cook bacon.
Stir in flour, then cream, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in cooked, drained broccoli.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: Break pretzels in small pieces; measure, place in bottom of oblong pan and pour melted oleo over.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°; cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Spread on top of pretzels; add layer of Cool Whip.
Mix Jell-O according to package, using only 2 cups water (1 cup cold and 1 cup hot).
Stir in strawberries. (Will gel very quickly.)
When partially set, pour remaining Cool Whip on as topping.
Chill; serve cut into squares.

title: cocoa cream frosting
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix and beat until smooth and fluffy.

title: welsh cakes(picauarymaen)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, spice and salt together.
Rub into the butter until it looks like bread crumbs.
Add sugar and fruit. Add beaten egg and milk and mix to a soft dough.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick on floured board and use cookie cutter to form 2-inch rounds.
Cook over a gentle heat on griddle or electric frying pan for 3 minutes each side.
When golden brown, remove and sprinkle with sugar.
Serve alone or with butter.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Combine cocoa and water.
Bring to boiling.
Add milk.
Heat until hot, but not boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add sweetener, vanilla and salt.

title: maggie's potatoes
directions: Use baking dish with lid.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Add water to pineapple juice to equal 4 cups liquid.
Bring liquid to a boil.
Stir in jello until dissolved.
Add 1 cup cold water and pie filling.
Pour into mold.
Chill until firm.
Blend cream cheese and sour cream.
Stir in sugar and nuts.
Spread over salad.

title: can't fail divinity
directions: Boil sugar, salt and water to hard ball stage (248°).
Do not stir while cooking.
Put Marshmallow Creme in a mixing bowl and pour in hot syrup.
Stir until slightly stiff.
Fold in nuts and vanilla.
Drop from spoon on waxed paper or pour into buttered dish.
Very good and easy.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each one.
Sift dry ingredients together 3 times.
Alternately add milk and dry ingredients to sugar mixture. Add vanilla.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: southern cole slaw
directions: Mix sugar, salt and lemon juice with mayonnaise.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chill before serving.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; pull apart.
Mix together remaining ingredients and microwave until cheese melts.
Pour over spaghetti and chicken.

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Mix all together except one package of beef.
Either put beef around ball or roll in strips.

title: blue ribbon jello salad
directions: Mix and dissolve lemon jello, hot water and cold water. Refrigerate until semi-thick.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Chill in 9 x 12-inch pan until firm.

title: blushing apple or rhubarb dessert
directions: Mix with beater the 1 1/4 cups flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, baking powder, salt and butter; combine slightly beaten egg and milk; add to butter mixture and blend well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Press sliced apples in dough overlapping (or cut up rhubarb).
Mix with Jell-O, 1 tablespoon sugar and sprinkle over fruit.
Cover with a topping of 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar and 1/2 cup butter, mixed until crumbly.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until edges are brown.

title: best peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt morsels and peanut butter in microwave or over medium heat on stove, stirring often.
(In microwave, melt on roast about 5 minutes.)
When melted, stir in milk.
Mix well.
Spray 13 x 9-inch pan with Pam; pour in mixture.
Refrigerate until firm. Makes about 100 (1-inch) squares.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Make salad dressing (Good Seasons) according to directions. Mix together and chill.

title: cornmeal mush
directions: Heat to boiling 3 cups water in saucepan.
(I use a small iron kettle.)
Mix cornmeal, salt and 1 cup cold water.
Pour into boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened, stirring frequently; cover.
Continue cooking over low heat 10 minutes or longer.
To make fried mush, pour cooked cornmeal into loaf pan and cool. When cold, cut into 1/2 inch slices.
Pan fry slowly on lightly greased griddle or skillet until golden brown. Serve hot with syrup or honey.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix all and put in a greased pan.
Crush 2 cups of corn flakes and sprinkle on top along with 1/2 cup of melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Combine butter, sugar, orange juice and cinnamon in frypan. Bring to a boil, mixing well.
Add halved sweet potatoes and simmer 10 to 15 minutes, spooning syrup over potatoes frequently and turning.

title: limeade pie
directions: Chill evaporated milk in freezer until ice crystals begin to form around the edges.
Soften gelatin in water.
Add limeade to gelatin in saucepan; heat until gelatin dissolves.
Add sugar, stirring until dissolved, but not thickened.
Put evaporated milk into a chilled bowl and beat at high speed until stiff.
Fold into cooled gelatin mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill 3 to 4 hours. Serve.

title: fellowship salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water; add cold water, pineapple and juice and bananas.
Sprinkle top with marshmallows and chill until firm.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Put in strawberries and let them dissolve.
Fold in remaining ingredients (except sour cream). Pour 1/2 mixture in a 9 x 12-inch dish and let set in refrigerator until firm.
Spread sour cream on top and add remaining mixture. Put in refrigerator until firm.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute 1 medium onion, chopped.
Add and saute water chestnuts.
Add spinach, cheese, sour cream and artichoke hearts.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle with more Parmesan cheese the last 5 minutes of baking.

title: sausage balls
directions: Knead all ingredients and roll into small balls.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: casserole bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixer bowl.
Add milk, 2/3 cup margarine, eggs, salt and 1 cup flour.
Beat on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour until smooth.
Scrape batter from sides of bowl.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place until double (about 30 minutes).
Batter is ready if indentation remains when touched.
Stir batter down by beating about 25 strokes.

title: budget casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onion in a skillet slightly.
Add tomato sauce and simmer a few minutes.
Cook noodles as per package instruction. Mix cheese, milk and soup.
Place noodles in a baking dish.
Top this with meat mixture.
Top this with cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain corn.
Pour in whipped cream and mix.
Melt butter and mix flour and butter.
Pour into corn and whipped cream and stir. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crisp chips
directions: Cut each shell into half, then fourth, then eighths.
Deep fry shells until they begin to curl.
Take out and drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cinnamon.

title: glazed meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Form in loaf pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: pig picking cake with icing
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, eggs and orange sections well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Combine cake mix, nectar, oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Bake in a greased Bundt or tube pan in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Cool right side up for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; top with glaze.

title: white layer cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into bowl; add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat 300 strokes with a spoon or 2 minutes with electric mixer at medium speed, until well blended.
Add egg whites and beat 2 minutes more.
Pour into 2 greased and lined 8-inch round layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place chicken, salt and pepper.
Then add rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken. Mix cream soups and water together, then add soups, pouring evenly over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover and top with cheese.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli beef
directions: Combine all ingredients except broccoli, water and oil.
Soak for 5 to 10 minutes.
Wash and clean broccoli.
Cut, parboil, drain and set aside.
Heat oil and fry steak mixture.
Add broccoli and water.
Simmer until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: fruit cake - dark nova scotian
directions: In a
large saucepan cook raisins, sugar, water, shortening, spices and	salt; boil for 5 minutes.
Cool the raisin-spice mixture.
Dust the dry fruit and nuts with flour and add to the raisin-spice
mixture,
then add the beaten eggs.
Bake in a greased large tube pan or 2 loaf pans at 275° for 2 hours and 30 minutes.
(If
you	plan
to give away cakes for gifts, you may want
to
use
the	small
individual
foil
loaf pans purchased at the
supermarket
and
fill
only
half full with mixture for baking.)
After
cooked
and
cooled, you may pour over brandy or rum,
or
wrap
the whole cake in brandy or rum soaked cheesecloth.
You
may
also serve with a brandied hard sauce, if you prefer.

title: butter biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Knead 5 times lightly on floured surface.
Pat 1/2-inch thick.
Cut out biscuits and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix yeast in 2 cups of water until dissolved.
Mix flour and shortening or Promise.
Add other ingredients, add water and mix well.
Pour into muffin pan.
Makes about 20 rolls.

title: barbecued chicken with lemon
directions: Have chicken split and remove the wings, backbone and tail. Clean well.
Place in shallow pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour into jar.
Cover. Shake well to blend.
Pour over chicken.
Cover tightly and marinate overnight in refrigerator, turning chicken occasionally.
Barbecue chicken or bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: old time fudge
directions: Cook cocoa, milk and salt on slow rolling boil until soft ball stage when tested in cold water.
Pour in mixing bowl and beat in butter and vanilla.
Beat until mixture starts to thicken and loses shine.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Cut into small pieces.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl, stirring to blend.
Beat at medium speed 5 minutes (700 strokes by hand), scraping sides of bowl frequently.
Pour into greased 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan on rack about 15 minutes before turning out on cake plate.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix brown sugar, regular sugar, butter and cream together over medium heat in large skillet.
Bring to boil, stirring often. Once mixture reaches soft ball stage (test by dropping small amount of hot mixture into cold water and being able to shape into soft ball), remove from heat to test.
Quickly add vanilla, peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Blend until smooth and mixed well.
Pour mixture into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: spinach spoon bread(side dish)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
After spinach is cooked and drained, melt two tablespoons margarine in a small saucepan.
Add flour, stirring constantly.
Add spices.
Slowly pour in milk, stirring until sauce thickens to a medium white sauce.
Mix white sauce, spinach, onions, sour cream, eggs and melted margarine in a large bowl.
Stir in muffin mix.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart glass casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, for about an hour, until a toothpick inserted in the center of dish comes out clean.
Serve immediately.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Put zucchini, butter and seasoning in skillet.
Cover, cook slowly 5 minutes.
Uncover, cook slowly, turning slices until almost tender.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Toss.
Can also add some Velveeta after turning slices, cooking about 5 minutes.
Then toss with Parmesan.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Put jello, sugar, cornstarch and boiling water into saucepan. Boil until clear.
Cool until the consistency of egg whites.
Pour into baked pie shell already half full of sliced fresh strawberries.
Cool in refrigerator.
Serve plain or with whipped topping.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix and freeze, then add 1 (2 liter) bottle of lemon-lime. Thaw 2 hours before serving.

title: p. j.'s apple dumpling
directions: Core and slice the apples into sections, leaving the peel on (approximately 12 slices per apple).
Put these sections into a bowl of water until ready to use to avoid discoloration.
Next, remove 1 biscuit at a time from the package and separate the biscuit to form 3 equal layers.

Do not cut; pull apart. Place one section of apple on each layer of dough. Fold the dough over the apple and crinkle the edges together to form a crescent dumpling. Layer these dumplings into a 9 x 12-inch ungreased baking pan. Continue until all dumplings have been made.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips and pour into a greased baking pan.
Top with chips.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and 1 1/2 cups water, then add the instant pudding and Cool Whip.
Let set 5 minutes in refrigerator. Put vanilla wafers and strawberries (sliced, not quite a quart) in a bowl in layers.
Pour filling over wafer-strawberries. Garnish with whole strawberries.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Fill bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with chicken pieces.
Mix milk and soup together.
Pour over chicken.
Pour broth into stuffing and mix until lightly moistened.
Spoon stuffing over chicken. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Toss in large salad bowl.

title: riverboat pie
directions: Melt butter and sugar together.
Stir in evaporated milk.
Let cool.
Add pineapple and chopped pecans when mixture is room temperature.
Add Cool Whip.
Last, put in lemon juice.
Divide among 3 pie crusts.

title: toasted coconut pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, butter, lemon juice and vanilla.
Stir in coconut.
Pour filling into unbaked shell.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add layer of mushrooms and layer of chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream; spread over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over soup mixture.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° until cheese bubbles up, about 20 minutes.

title: pork roast with rosemary
directions: Sprinkle pork roast with salt and pepper; rub with rosemary and garlic.
Place pork, fat side up, on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer so tip is in center of thickest part of pork and does not rest in fat.
Roast, uncovered, in 325° oven until thermometer registers 170°, about 2 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, orange juice and sour cream.
Mix until blended.
Stir in flour mixture just until moistened.
Fold in cranberries and pecans.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice ahead of time.
Scramble eggs (hard scrambled and cut into cubes).
Boil frozen carrots and peas for 2 to 3 minutes and drain.

title: never fail pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in pan and cook on top of stove until thick like pudding.
Pour in precooked crust.
Cook in oven at 350° until crust browns.

title: healthy fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in buttermilk, then roll in Bisquick.
Let set 5 to 7 minutes.
Lay in sprayed pan and bake in a 425° oven 20 minutes per side.

title: zero dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a tightly covered container.
Shake to blend. Store in refrigerator.

title: german chocolate icing
directions: Generously covers a 9 x 13-inch cake or 3 round layers.

title: my favorite snack:  bread and cheese
directions: Take the bread.
Take the cheese.
Put the cheese on the bread.
Put the bread in the microwave for 30 seconds or one minute.
Do not forget to cover it with a paper towel.
Then you take it out of the microwave and eat.
Enjoy!

title: casserole potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes in salted water until tender.
Drain and return pan to low heat, shaking to dry potatoes.
Cream together cream cheese and sour cream with electric mixer.
Add hot potatoes 1 at a time to cream mixture and continue beating.
Add green onions, diced bacon, salt and pepper to taste.
Put in well-buttered ovenproof casserole.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons melted butter or margarine over top.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot through.
Remove and sprinkle with finely minced parsley before serving.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening; add
sugar,
salt and eggs.
Dissolve soda in molasses.
Sift	flour
and
spices.
Add
to
mixture alternately with milk.
Add fruit and nuts last.
(Rum makes a nice flavoring.) If batter is
not	good
and
stiff, add more flour.
Bake slowly at 300° for
2	hours.	Cake
is better if made several weeks in advance and wrapped in foil to season.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together until smooth. Cook in microwave for 2 minutes, stirring every 1/2 minute. (Can be done on stove top, low heat, stirring until thickened.) Serve at room temperature.

title: pot roast
directions: Flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt the roast.
Place a small amount of Crisco in the electric frying pan, and brown the roast. Put in cream of mushroom soup, onions, potatoes and carrots.
Also put in about 2 1/2 cups of water.
Cover and cook at 225° for about 2 to 3 hours.

title: pannukakko(oven pancake)
directions: Using electric mixer, beat eggs well.
Add about 3/4 cup milk. Beat until blended.
Add the flour and salt; beat until smooth. Gradually add remaining milk and beat at low speed until blended. Melt the stick of oleo in jelly roll or large drip pan.
Pour batter over melted oleo.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 35 minutes until browned.
Sprinkle sugar on top when removed from oven.
Also good with berry sauces.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
Mix the pudding and milk together.
When it thickens, stir in Cool Whip. Pour pudding mixture over graham crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers on top.
Melt butter and chocolate in milk.
Pour this over powdered sugar and beat with mixer until shiny.
Spread over graham crackers.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: wassail
directions: Mix all ingredients together and boil for 5 minutes, then simmer.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir only enough to just mix.
Bake in greased baking pan at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: peppered pork roast with rosemary potatoes
directions: Coat roast with pepper.
Place, uncovered, in a roasting pan with drip rack.
Roast for 1 hour at 350°.
Add potatoes which have been tossed with oil and sprinkled with rosemary and salt. Bake 1 more hour.
Remove from oven and let rest for 10 minutes. Slice roast.
Serves 8.

title: cupcake brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and oleo.
Stir in sugar, flour and vanilla. Add eggs (beat after each addition).
Stir in pecans.
Fill cupcake papers 1/2 full.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Chop or shred the first 4 ingredients.
Add salt and let stand overnight.
Drain and wash well.
Combine the last 7 ingredients with vegetables.
Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Seal in hot jars.

title: cheese scrambled eggs
directions: Beat together eggs, milk, dash of salt and dash of pepper. In a small skillet, melt butter; add egg mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, until eggs begin to set. Sprinkle with cheese.
Continue cooking just until eggs are firm and cheese is melted.
Sprinkle with green onion.
Makes 1 serving.

title: green chile burritos
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain grease.
Simmer gravy, green chiles (undrained) and 3/4 of sour cream over low heat.
Do not allow to boil.
Soften tortillas by placing in wet dish towel and microwaving for 1 minute.
Place spoonfuls of meat mixture, gravy, cheese and salsa on tortillas.
Place seam side down in gravy-lined baking pan.
Pour remaining gravy and cheese over burritos.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until hot.
Serve with remaining sour cream and salsa.

title: potluck casserole
directions: Mix altogether and pour into a greased flat Pyrex pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse sauerkraut well and drain.
Chop and drain celery, green pepper, onion, pimentos. Mix sauerkraut and vegetables. Mix vinegar, sugar, water, oil and salt and pour over vegetable mixture.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: minnesota beans
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Put all ingredients in 9 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil.

title: french bread garlic loaf
directions: Cut bread in halves lengthwise.
Place halves on aluminum foil-covered baking sheet.
Tear out inner portion of bread in large chunks, leaving crusts intact.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight.
You add vegetables and water.
Then cook for 5 hours. Serve over rice.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, orange peel and vanilla.
Add egg; beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in milk.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in creamed mixture.
Divide dough in half.
Chill for 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll out (I leave mine somewhat thicker).
Cut in shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Add icing and colored sugar.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter or margarine in medium saucepan.
Add onion; saute until soft.
Stir in flour; cook over low heat one minute. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat until slightly thickened and beginning to boil.
Add 1 cup cheese, salt and mustard.
Remove from heat; stir until cheese is melted. Arrange 1/2 of potatoes in 13 x 9-inch greased dish.
Pour 1/2 sauce over potatoes in dish.
Arrange remaining potato slices in dish and pour on remaining sauce.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 hour or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Uncover; sprinkle remaining 1 1/2 cups cheese and paprika.
Continue baking until cheese is melted.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding enough whole milk to fill ice cream freezer to fill line.
Freeze as you would any homemade ice cream.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat.
Remove excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients and 2 cups water.
Simmer uncovered 3 hours or until sauce is thick; stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve over hot spaghetti.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumber (peel first, if desired).
Add remaining ingredients and marinate 30 minutes or more.

title: chinese dish
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Add pepper and onions to sausage and cook until transparent.
Add chopped celery; cook until tender. Cook soup mix in the broth from chicken, making 9 cups of liquid. Add this mixture and chicken to rice.
Put into baking dishes and bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
This makes 2 casseroles.
Freezes well.

title: chicken vermicelli
directions: Cook vermicelli.
Saute chopped onions and peppers in margarine.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes with 1/2 the juice, discard the rest.
Cut Velveeta in cubes and add to the sauteed mix.
Add cooked chicken which has been cut into bite-sized pieces and mushrooms to the melted cheese mixture and enough chicken broth to make mixture thin.
It will thicken as it cools.
Place vermicelli in two large glass baking dishes and pour the cheese mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 2 large casseroles and freezes well.

title: hot ham and cheese finger rolls
directions: Slice
through	each
package of rolls without breaking rolls. Layer
with
ham
and cheese.
Put back in pans.
Stir all
other ingredients into melted margarine.	Pour over rolls in pan	and stir
so seeds won't settle.
Cover with foil and let sit at least 30 minutes; can sit overnight or even freeze. Bake at
for 15	minutes.
Cut into individual rolls in their pans.
Serve at once.

title: crunch cake
directions: Mix and beat as any plain cake. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: chunk chocolate peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugar and peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to mixture; mix well.
Stir in chocolate.
Drop by tablespoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and pour into greased casserole.
Top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes and pour 1/2 cup melted oleo over top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: russian tea
directions: Blend above at high speed in a food processor.
Use 4 tsp. per mug.
Add boiling water.

title: chicken melt
directions: Top 1 slice of bread with cheese, salsa, chicken or roast beef and bread slice.
Spread sandwich with margarine.
Cook in skillet on medium heat until lightly browned on both sides.
Makes 1 sandwich.

title: summer bean salad
directions: For the dressing:
Whisk together oil, vinegar, salt, sugar and pepper.
Set aside.

title: scalloped potatoes with peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine potatoes, milk, cream and garlic in pan.
Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove.
Stir in all peppers and seasonings.
Bake in 2 dishes and cover with cheeses.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes more.
Makes 16 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening. Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water. Sift dry ingredients together. Add flour mixture to pumpkin mixture. Stir in coarsely chopped nuts and add raisins. Pour into 9 x 5 x 3 inch well greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean when inserted in center.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Saute onion (brown meat) and drain.
Add to this noodles, soup, tomato sauce and salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning, oregano and basil.
Put Mozzarella cheese on top with pepperoni on it.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Cool at least 5 to 7 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook and stir meat and onion in butter until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic, pepper and mushrooms; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in soup; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over noodles.

title: 3 bean-no bake(1 full crock-pot)
directions: In large pan, brown hamburger meat, bacon and onion; drain. Add beans and rest of ingredients.
Cook on stove or pour in crock-pot.

title: garden slaw
directions: Mix the shredded cabbage, carrots, green pepper and onion. Sprinkle with the 1/2 cup cold water and chill.
Soften the gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water and set aside.
Mix the sugar, vinegar, celery seed, salt and pepper in a saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Stir in softened gelatin.
Cool until slightly thickened. Beat well.
Gradually beat in the 2/3 cup of salad oil.
Pour dressing over top of cabbage mixture and stir lightly until all is coated.
Can serve immediately or store in refrigerator.
Will keep forever.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Melt sugar and Jell-O in pineapple syrup.
Remove from heat. Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts; mix well.
Pour into mold or bowl. Chill until set.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: strawberry pudding
directions: Heat
strawberries,
sugar
and
jello	just
enough to dissolve
jello,
stirring	constantly. Cool.
Mix pudding and milk by directions on box. Add sour cream. Fold in 3/4 of Cool Whip.
In
a large 13 x 9-inch dish, layer wafers, pudding mix and strawberries. Repeat until all are used.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Garnish with sliced strawberries. Refrigerate. (If desired, bananas can be used instead of strawberries.)

title: pig eater cake
directions: Mix cake mix with ingredients as instructed on back of box. Add in the oranges (drained).
Mix and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl.
Let stand five minutes.
Add sugar, shortening, egg, salt and half of the flour; beat at low speed until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to make a soft dough.
(I find it is best to reserve part of the flour to knead the bread with.) Knead 8 or 10 times.
Place in well-greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until doubled.
Punch dough down on lightly floured surface and knead 4 or 5 times.
Grease hands well and shape in rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 400° until golden.

title: united states senate soup
directions: Put soaked beans, ham bone and water in kettle. Simmer 2 hours.
Add mashed potatoes when beans are half cooked.
Stir and mix thoroughly.
Add onion, celery, garlic and parsley.
Simmer 1 hour longer.
Remove ham bone and chop ham in pieces.
Return ham pieces to kettle before serving.

title: hamburger squares
directions: Fry hamburger; drain and put in Special sauce and chili powder. Simmer for 5 minutes. Set aside.
Spread 1 tube of biscuits in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread hamburger mixture over biscuits.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over hamburger.
Spread the other tube of biscuits over the cheese.
Follow baking directions on tube of biscuits or until golden brown.

title: bacon cheese logs
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Combine with remaining ingredients except chili powder.
Shape into 3-inch logs.
Coat with chili powder and chill several hours.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices and serve with crackers.

title: chicken and rice(original recipe)
directions: Brown chicken in oil over high heat; remove from pan.
Brown onions in pan.
Add broth, garlic, chives, parsley, pepper and onion soup mix.
Cook 5 minutes.

title: david's favorite shrimp salad
directions: Boil and drain macaroni.
Rinse with cold water.
Thaw frozen salad shrimp according to package.
Mix macaroni, shrimp, eggs and vegetables.
